title: trifle
directions: *Can substitute angel food cake.

title: sugarless cookies
directions: Combine dry ingredients, then add orange juice, oil and egg. Mix well; drop by teaspoon on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake for 15 to 20 minutes at 375°.
Makes 32 cookies.

title: blueberry congealed salad
directions: Mix Jell-O, water and pineapple.
Let cool until mixture begins to set.
Add blueberry pie filling.
Let mixture congeal. Mix sour cream, cream cheese, sugar and vanilla.
Blend well.
Top congealed mixture.
Top with chopped nuts.

title: jalapeno bean dip
directions: Blend in a blender the Ranch Style beans and peppers (no seeds).
Add more peppers if you want it hotter.
Put on stove and simmer, stirring so as not to burn.
Add grated Velveeta cheese. When hot, put in fondue pot for 1 1/2 hours before serving. (Start with 1/2 pound cheese; add more if needed.)
Serves 12.

title: roasted rosemary new potatoes & artichokes
directions: Preheat over to 375°.
Combine first seven ingredients in large mixing bowl and stir.
Place mixture in single layer in baking dish; bake until potatoes are fork soft (approximately 45 minutes), stirring every 20 minutes.
Remove from oven and sprinkle with Feta cheese over top.

title: cinnamon kuchen
directions: Mix together milk, sugar and salt.
Add yeast.
Stir in eggs and add shortening.
Add flour.
Knead dough until elastic.
Put in greased bowl and let rise until double, 1 1/2 to 2 hours. Punch down.
Turn over in bowl and let rise about 30 to 45 minutes.
Roll dough to about 1/2-inch thick and put on cookie sheet.
Let rise about 30 minutes.
Punch holes in dough, but not all way through.
Sprinkle with brown sugar, cinnamon and about 1/2 can condensed or evaporated milk.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: vicky's cappuccino mix
directions: Combine all ingredients; mix well.
Store in airtight container.

title: creamy rice pudding(no baking)
directions: Combine rice and water.
Cook on medium heat for 10 minutes. Add 4 cups milk, raisins, sugar and salt.
Cook slowly for about 25 minutes.
Stir frequently.
When rice is very tender, add egg yolks mixed with remaining 1/4 cup milk.
Stir constantly.
Stir until slightly thick and mixture coats spoon.
Remove from heat. Add vanilla and butter; cool.
Dust with nutmeg when serving. Makes lots.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: chili
directions: Brown ground beef and onions.
Add remaining ingredients; cook together for 45 minutes.

title: peach cobbler
directions: Melt oleo in pan. Add peaches.
Beat together milk, sugar and flour.
Pour over peaches.
Bake at 325° for about 45 minutes.

title: chocolate pound cake
directions: Cream sugar, shortening and margarine. Add eggs, one at a time. Mix well. Sift dry ingredients together 3 times. Alternately add milk and dry ingredients to sugar mixture 3 times. Add vanilla last. Bake at 325° for 80 to 90 minutes or until done.

title: company beef
directions: Whisk together soups and wine.
Add beef and mushrooms.
Cook 3 hours in 300° to 350° oven or cook in crock-pot 5 to 6 hours on low.
Serve over egg noodles.

title: curry dip
directions: Very simple.
Just mix all ingredients up and chill for 1 hour before serving.
This is a great dip for fresh vegetables, such as cauliflower, celery, carrot sticks and squash.

title: monkey bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease Bundt pan.
Cut each biscuit into quarters (easiest with scissors).
Combine 3/4 cup sugar and 1 tablespoon cinnamon.
Coat each quarter piece in mixture.
Place in Bundt pan evenly.
Add nuts and raisins, intermittantly.
Boil 1 cup sugar, butter and cinnamon.
Pour over biscuit pieces evenly. Bake 35 to 40 minutes.
Watch closely to avoid burning.
Turn out of pan immediately.
Happy picking!

title: "squasage" casserole
directions: Wash, slice and cook squash until it breaks apart easily with a fork.
Drain.
Add beaten egg, onion, crumbled crackers, margarine and sausage which has been broken in pieces, fried and drained.
Mix well.
Top with Velveeta slices or 2/3 cup shredded Cheddar.
Bake in regular oven at 350° until bubbly.
Do not cover.

title: sour cream cake
directions: Heat oven to 350°. Grease a square pan. Mix all ingredients. Beat 1 minute. Bake for 35 minutes.

title: wintertime soup
directions: Saute and drain ground meat and onion.
Add other ingredients and simmer for about 30 to 45 minutes.
If desired, serve with Fritos and grated cheese.

title: queen elizabeth cake
directions: Pour boiling water over dates and baking soda.
Let stand while mixing other ingredients.
Add all together.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes in a 9 x 12-inch pan.

title: homemade beef stick
directions: Mix well.
Refrigerate in covered bowl for 3 days.
Mix daily. On fourth day, shape into 5 logs.
Place on broiler pan.
Bake at 160° for 8 hours.
Wrap in Saran and foil.
Keeps in refrigerator a month or can be frozen indefinitely.
Slice to serve.
(Do not substitute on ingredients.)

title: winter's day bean soup
directions: Rinse beans.
Place in large pot.
Cover with water.
Add salt and soak overnight.
Drain.
Add 2 quarts water and ham or sausage.
Simmer for 2 1/2 or 3 hours.
Add onion, garlic, chili powder, tomatoes and lemon juice.
Simmer 45 minutes.
Add salt and pepper, if desired.
Yields 2 quarts.

title: peach cobbler
directions: Pour peaches and syrup into a 2-quart baking bowl or pan.

Cut peach slices into small pieces. Mix flour, sugar, melted margarine and milk together in another bowl. When mixed together smooth, pour into baking bowl with peaches and stir together. Put into oven and bake at 350° for 35 minutes or to golden brown. Take out and cool.

title: chocolate-dipped treats
directions: Cut chocolate block(s) into small pieces.
Put a few pieces into a bowl.
Melt the chocolate in the microwave on Low; stir periodically as it is melting.
Monitor chocolate carefully; it takes just a few minutes to melt it.
Remove bowl of chocolate from microwave.
Dip ingredients into chocolate, one at a time, and place them on cookie sheets covered with wax paper.
Place in refrigerator for a few minutes to harden chocolate.
Items may be covered with chocolate totally or half-way.
Continue melting chocolate and dipping items until desired amount is achieved. Great for parties!

title: never fail pie crust
directions: Combine flour and salt in mixing bowl.
Add shortening.
With cool fingertips, work into flour to make fine crumbs.
Combine egg, vinegar and water; stir to mix, then add to crumbs and stir with a fork to mix.
Divide dough into 4 parts (makes enough for 2 double crust pies).
Roll out each portion on lightly floured board.

title: pimento sandwich filler
directions: Melt cheese, mayonnaise and butter over low heat. Add beaten egg and chopped pimentos. Stir constantly until cheese is completely melted and mixed thoroughly. Keep refrigerated.

title: danish bars
directions: Layer 1 package of rolls in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Blend cream cheese and sugar together.
Spread over rolls.
Put 2nd package of rolls on top of cream cheese.
Dot with butter.
Bake 20 to 30 minutes at 350°.

title: easy no fail biscuits
directions: Combine flour and salt.
Pour buttermilk and oil into flour mixture; stir until you can handle it.
Pour out dough onto a floured surface.
Knead a few times.
Roll out, cut and put in greased pan.
Turn each biscuit so both sides are covered with oil.
Bake 20 to 25 minutes or until done.

title: peanut-butter cookies
directions: Mix flour, salt and baking soda.
Set aside.
Mix margarine and peanut butter.
Add both sugars.
Mix well; add eggs and beat well.
Stir flour mixture into peanut butter mixture.
Drop dough from a teaspoon onto baking pan.
Flatten with fork.
Bake at 375° for 10 to 15 minutes.

title: tuna noodle casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cook noodles, drain and return to pot. Stir in tuna, sour cream, milk, mushrooms, salt and pepper.
Pour into ungreased 2-quart casserole dish.
Mix bread crumbs, cheese and margarine.
Sprinkle over casserole and bake uncovered 35 to 40 minutes or until bubbly.

title: corn salad(club member: keisha hudson)
directions: Mix all ingredients together; let set in refrigerator 2 hours.

title: lil's m&m's cookies
directions: Sift together flour, soda and salt.
Cream butter and both sugars.
Add egg and vanilla, beating until fluffy.
Gradually add dry ingredients to creamy mixture.
Add candy and nuts, if desired.
Drop by spoon on slightly greased pan and bake for 7 minutes at 350°.

title: crunchy cranberry relish
directions: Mix all ingredients in a medium-size serving bowl.
Cover and refrigerate at least 1 hour before serving.

title: dump cake
directions: Pour pie filling into 9 x 12-inch glass dish and spread evenly.
Add all other ingredients, one at a time, in order, spreading each evenly without mixing.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour.

title: granola
directions: In a large baking pan, melt the margarine and stir in the honey.
Stir in oats, sunflower seeds and cinnamon and bake in a preheated oven for about 15 minutes.
Stir several times.
Stir in wheat germ and bake 10 minutes longer or until the mixture is lightly browned.
Remove mixture from oven, stir in raisins and cool completely before transferring to a storage container.

title: saucy baked pork chops
directions: Brown chops in hot fat.
Season with salt and pepper.
Drain off excess fat.
Combine remaining ingredients.
Pour over chops. Cover and bake in moderate oven at 350° for 45 to 60 minutes or until chops are done.
Serves 6.

title: individual fruit cake balls
directions: Mix all ingredients; shape into balls.
Grease cookie sheet or pan and bake in 300° oven for 20 to 25 minutes.
Remove from pan while hot (reshape into balls).

title: down south barbecue
directions: Put one sliced onion in bottom of crock-pot.
Add meat, cloves and water.
Cook overnight on low.
Remove meat from bone and return meat to crock-pot, adding barbecue sauce.
Cook additional 2 hours on low, stirring occasionally.
Serve from crock-pot onto large buns.

title: fat-free biscuits
directions: Roll and cut out.
Bake at 500° until brown.
Makes 10 large biscuits.
Each contains 85 calories and 0 fat.

title: layered cheeseburger casserole
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Cook macaroni in 6 cups boiling water, salted (4 teaspoons), 8 minutes and drain.
Cook and stir ground beef, celery and onion until beef is light brown; drain.
Stir in seasoned salt and pepper.
Grease baking pan 9 x 9 x 2-inch or baking dish 11 3/4 x 7 1/2 x 1 1/3-inch.
Spread macaroni in pan; top with beef mixture.
Beat sauce mix and remaining ingredients (sauce mix will be slightly lumpy); pour over beef mixture.
Bake uncovered until knife inserted in center comes out clean, 40 to 50 minutes.
Let stand 5 minutes before serving.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: macaroni salad
directions: Cook macaroni until done.
Rinse and drain well.
Add onion, pepper and tuna; mix well with salad dressing.
(Use more salad dressing, if needed.)
Sprinkle with paprika.
Keep in refrigerator.

title: shrimp dip
directions: Mix all ingredients and chill 1 hour. Heat in oven at 450° until cheese is bubbly. Serve with rye bread.

title: helado de mango(mango sherbet)
directions: In a saucepan, combine water, 1/2 cup sugar and salt.
Cook for 5 minutes; cool.
In blender container, combine mangos and cream.
Cover; blend until smooth.
Stir in cooled syrup and lemon juice.
Freeze in one 6-cup or two 3-cup freezer trays until partially frozen.

title: long lasting slaw
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients and cook, stirring, until sugar is dissolved.
Let cool and pour over vegetables.
Let stand overnight in refrigerator.
This can be frozen.

title: dijon chicken
directions: Place chicken in Tupperware dish.
Mix all other ingredients and spread on the chicken.
Cover and refrigerate 2 to 4 hours. Then grill, broil or bake.

title: pickled beans
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Make a day ahead.
Will last up to 2 weeks.

title: fall surprise
directions: Mix together pie mix, eggs and milk.
Pour into greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Sprinkle cake mix over this mixture.
Slice 1 stick butter over top of cake mix.
Add 1 cup crushed pecans and 1/2 cup whole pecans.
Slice remaining stick of butter over pecans.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.
Serve at room temperature.

title: chicken d. k.
directions: Pat out chicken breasts with mallet.
Sprinkle with garlic. Put cream cheese on each breast.
Put mushrooms over cream cheese. Roll chicken breasts.
Wrap each roll with bacon.
Sprinkle with bread crumbs.
Put in greased dish or pan.
Bake at 350°
for approximately 45 minutes.

title: carol's dessert
directions: Mix together and press firmly into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake 15 minutes at 350°.
Cool completely.

title: baked macaroni and cheese
directions: Cook pasta according to package directions; drain.
Melt butter in a Dutch oven over low heat; whisk in flour until smooth. Cook 1 minute, whisking constantly.
Gradually whisk in milk; cook over medium heat, whisking constantly, until thickened and bubbly. Stir in 2 cups cheddar cheese and next 3 ingredients. Stir in pasta.
Spoon mixture into a lightly greased 13-inch by 9-inch baking dish.
Top with remaining 1 cup cheddar cheese, and sprinkle breadcrumbs over cheese.
Bake casserole at 350° for 30 minutes, or until hot and bubbly.

title: chocolate chip caramel rolls(microwave)
directions: In a
small
bowl
combine
brown
sugar, 2 tablespoons butter and corn syrup.
Cook
on 100% power for 1 to 2 minutes or until butter
is melted and brown sugar is dissolved.
Stir to combine. Evenly divide mixture among six (6-ounce) custard cups;
set aside.

title: dilly baked potatoes
directions: Scrub potatoes.
Slice each into 3 or 4 slices.
Between each potato slice, place a 1/4-inch slice of onion.
Place each potato and onion on a double thickness of heavy duty aluminum foil. Sprinkle with salt, pepper and dill weed.
Dot with butter.
Wrap tightly.
Place in a 400° oven for 1 1/2 hours.
Turn once or twice during cooking.

title: cinnamon rolls
directions: Scald milk and pour it over sugar, salt and shortening. Dissolve yeast in lukewarm water.
Add beaten eggs.
When milk has cooled to lukewarm temperature, add the yeast and beaten eggs. Beat well.
Add flour gradually, beating well.
Knead lightly, working in just enough flour so that dough can be handled.
Place dough in greased bowl; cover and let stand in warm place 2 hours.

title: pineapple cake
directions: Mix ingredients together and pour into 9 x 13 greased cake pan. Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes or until done.

title: corn casserole
directions: Heat milk, oleo and corn until warm.
Add beaten eggs and rest of ingredients.
Pour into greased casserole.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: waldorf salad
directions: Mix the first 6 ingredients in a bowl and serve mixture on lettuce leaves.

title: best ever potato salad
directions: Boil potatoes with peelings on.
Drain when done; while slightly warm, remove peelings.
In large bowl, slice potatoes thin; grate the hard-boiled eggs and add to potatoes.
Add diced celery and onion; add salt and pepper.
Toss lightly.
Then in a separate bowl add mayonnaise, sugar, oil and mustard.
Mix well; pour over potato.
Mix well; sprinkle with paprika.

title: mexican dish
directions: Cook noodles while browning meat, onion and bell pepper; drain.
Mix chili powder, mashed tomatoes and Ro-Tel and add to meat mixture.
Add noodles and corn and let simmer.
Into a large baking dish, put a layer of meat mixture, then cheese layer alternately, until all is used, leaving enough cheese to put on top.
Put in oven until cheese is melted on top.

title: oatmeal-honey bars
directions: Stir together brown sugar, honey, vanilla and margarine.
Add oatmeal and pecans.
Stir very well.
Press into a jelly roll pan. Bake 10 minutes at 425° to 450°.
Score lightly with silver knife as soon as removed from oven.
Let cool slightly before cutting. Cool almost completely before taking from pan.
I cut into 72 small squares.
You may use any kind of nuts, chopped.

title: chicken scampi
directions: Cut chicken cutlets (breast) into bite size pieces.
Melt butter.
Saute garlic, oregano, garlic powder and salt until garlic is soft (simmer).
Use more or less garlic to taste.
Put chicken in and saute.

title: hardee's biscuits
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Roll out onto a floured surface.
Cut into biscuits and place onto a greased baking sheet. Bake at 400° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: pretzel dessert
directions: Place pretzels in bottom of 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Melt butter with sugar and pour over pretzels.
Bake at 400° for 10 minutes.
Cool.
Blend remaining ingredients.
Pour over pretzel crust.
Top with pie filling.
Refrigerate.

title: beef burgundy
directions: Mix all of the ingredients (except the mushrooms) in a Corning Ware dish. Cover and bake at 325° for 3 hours.
After 2 hours, add the whole mushrooms and bake for the additional hour.

title: firehouse jambalaya
directions: Stir and cook chicken in skillet until lightly browned.
Add green pepper, onion, celery and sausage.
Cook until vegetables are just starting to become tender.
Stir in tomatoes and water, bringing to a full boil.
Slowly stir in Tabasco sauce, rice and salt.
Cover.
Remove from heat; let stand for 10 minutes.

title: meatballs in spaghetti sauce
directions: Cook onion and garlic over medium heat in olive oil until tender.
Stir in tomatoes, paste, parsley, seasonings and sugar; simmer gently about 3 hours, adding meatballs and sausage (if desired) during the last
hour.
Serve over spaghetti.
This recipe serves 6.

title: medium rare beef roast
directions: Preheat oven to 500°.
Salt and pepper the roast.
Insert garlic cloves in small slits.
Put roast in oven for 5 minutes per pound.
Turn off oven and leave roast in oven until ready to slice.
Do not open oven after putting roast in.

title: chocolate eclair cake
directions: Mix vanilla pudding, milk and sugar.
Fold in Cool Whip.
In a 9 x 9-inch pan, layer graham crackers, half of mixture, graham crackers, mixture and graham crackers.
Frost with chocolate frosting.
Jell for about 4 hours.

title: martha washington candy
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients; beat until creamy.
Blend in pecans.
Roll into balls the size of walnuts, using additional powdered sugar on hands in rolling balls.
Melt chocolate and paraffin in top of double boiler over low heat.
Dip balls into chocolate mixture, one piece at a time, holding each with a toothpick.
Drop onto waxed paper.

title: low-fat lasagna
directions: Cook noodles as directed and set aside.
Heat oven to 350°. Brown ground beef, onions and garlic.
Drain. Stir in parsley, salt, basil, oregano, fennel seed, anise and tomato sauce. Simmer 10 minutes, stirring occasionally.

title: sweet potato biscuits
directions: Combine egg, sweet potatoes, sugar, butter and shortening in a mixing bowl; mix well.
Stir in enough flour to make a soft dough. (Dough will be softer than regular biscuit dough.)
Turn out on a floured surface; knead lightly a few times.
Roll to 1/4-inch thickness; cut with a 2-inch biscuit cutter.
Place on an ungreased baking sheet and bake at 350° for about 15 minutes. Yields about 16 biscuits.

title: french onion soup
directions: Cook first 3 ingredients for 15 minutes in a covered pan.
Add salt and sugar.
Cook 30 to 40 minutes (or until golden brown) over low heat.
Blend in flour and cook for 3 minutes.
Blend in boiling beef broth.
Add vermouth and salt and pepper to taste. Simmer 30 to 40 minutes.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: turkey casserole
directions: Mix and pour into casserole dish.
Cover with bread crumbs. Bake 30 minutes at 350° until brown and bubbly.

title: salami
directions: Combine all ingredients. Mix well.
Refrigerate 24 hours.
Mix well again and refrigerate 24 hours.
Make short rolls and place in broiler pan and bake 5 hours at 200°.

title: potato skins
directions: Fry in bacon fat onion, green pepper and mushrooms.
Fill potatoes with onion and mushroom mixture and top with bacon and cheese.
Warm in oven, if needed.
Very delicious!

title: low-fat pesto
directions: Put the basil, garlic, pine nuts and Parmesan cheese in a blender or food processor.
Turn the machine on and drizzle in the lemon juice.
Continue to puree until a smooth paste is formed. Makes 3/4 cup pesto.
Fat per 1/2 tablespoon = 1.1 grams.
Calories per 1/2 tablespoon = 14.

title: bar-b-q's (sloppy joes)
directions: Brown hamburg and onion.
Add other ingredients and serve on hamburger rolls.

title: baked fish with vegetables
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Grease baking dish lightly with oil. Place fish, flesh side up, in greased baking dish.
Sprinkle with salt and pepper. Spread mixed vegetables over fish.
Place onion and tomato slices over vegetables.
Sprinkle lightly with salt and pepper. Top with bacon. Bake for 30 to 45 minutes or until fish flakes easily.
Yields 4 servings.

title: spritz cookies
directions: Cream shortening until soft.
Add sugar gradually.
Add egg and extract, then beat.

title: sugar cookies
directions: Cream butter and sugar together.
Add eggs, extract and milk; blend well.
Sift or stir together dry ingredients; blend in. Chill dough, if necessary.
Roll out on floured board or surface; cut into desired shapes.
Decorate as desired; bake on an ungreased cookie sheet in a 375° oven for 10 to 12 minutes, or until edges just start to turn golden.
Remove to a rack to cool.

title: baked apples
directions: Core and slice (do not peel) the apples and put into a baking dish.
Sprinkle with sugar and dot with butter.
Add cinnamon, if desired.
Bake, covered, at 375° for 30 to 40 minutes until apples are tender and juicy.

title: lemon custard pudding cake
directions: Combine flour, margarine and 1 1/2 cups sugar in a bowl.
Beat egg yolks; add to mixing bowl along with milk and lemon peel.
Mix well.
Add lemon juice.
In another bowl, beat egg whites until stiff, slowly adding remaining 1/2 cup of sugar while beating. Fold into batter.
Pour into a 2 quart greased baking dish.
Place in a shallow pan of hot water and bake at 350° for 55 to 60 minutes.
Serve warm or chilled, dusted with confectioners sugar. Yield:
6 to 8 servings.

title: soda pop show-off
directions: Blend cake mix, soda pop and eggs until moistened.
Beat as directed on package.
To deepen color, add food coloring as desired.

title: tuna pecan salad
directions: In a large bowl, combine all ingredients, coating well.
If salad is dry, add more mayonnaise.
Serve as a sandwich or as a salad on a bed of lettuce.

title: chili
directions: Brown ground beef; drain.
Mix remaining ingredients together. Bring to a boil.
Reduce heat and simmer for at least 15 minutes. Serve.

title: glory cake with paradise icing
directions: Blend Crisco with sugar and eggs.
Beat until fluffy.
Add lemon. Sift dry ingredients. Add alternately with milk.
Blend well. Bake in 3 layer pans 20 to 25 minutes at 350°.
Cool cake.

title: grandma irene's lime pickles
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients together (cucumbers, lime and water). Soak 24 hours.
Stir occasionally.
Rinse well.
Cover with cold water.
Soak 3 hours.
Drain.
Mix remaining ingredients and cover cucumbers with mixture.
Soak overnight.
Add green food coloring. Boil 35 minutes in jars.
Seal while hot.

title: meat loaf supreme
directions: Preheat the oven to 375°.
Mix milk with torn bread; stir until bread is soaked in milk before adding to meat loaf.
In large bowl, mix all ingredients and form into loaf.
If too much liquid, add more crushed crackers.
Cover entire loaf with catsup. Add a tiny bit of water around loaf if using extra lean ground chuck.
Bake at 375° for about 45 minutes.
Cut through center of loaf or even slice entire loaf to ensure even baking and let bake another 20 minutes.
Ovens vary so check after 15 minutes.

title: easy irish stew
directions: If lamb or beef is in large chunks, cut into bite size pieces. Quarter the potatoes.
Cut the carrots into 2-inch sections.
In large saucepan, combine 2 1/2 cups of the broth, the tomato paste, garlic, bay leaf and pepper.
Add the pearl onions; bring the mixture to a boil over medium-high heat.
Add lamb or beef, potatoes and carrots; return to a boil.
Reduce the heat to medium-low; cover and simmer until the vegetables are tender, about 20 minutes.

title: oven-fried potatoes
directions: Cut potatoes in lengthwise wedges.
Place in 2 shallow baking pans, cut side down.
Mix remaining ingredients together and brush over potatoes.
Bake at 375° for 45 minutes or until potatoes are golden brown and tender, brushing occasionally with oil mixture.

title: turkey tetrazzini(makes 6 to 8 servings)
directions: Cook onion and pepper in butter until tender.
Blend in flour and milk.
Cook, stirring constantly, until smooth.
Add salt, 1/2 cup cheese, turkey, mushrooms, peas and pimiento.
Alternate layers of sauce with cooked, drained spaghetti in a greased 2-quart casserole.
Sprinkle with remaining cheese.
Bake in 400° oven 20 minutes.

title: homemade ice cream
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Mix with electric mixer. Pour into mixer.
Add milk to fill line.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Mix the chicken, soup, peas, onion, milk, salt and pepper together.
Melt the butter.
Add the herb seasoning mix.
Line baking dish with 3/4 of this.
Add the other mixture.
Sprinkle rest of seasoning mix on top.
Bake about 1 hour at 300°.

title: coconut dream pie
directions: Prepare whipped topping with 1 cup of milk and vanilla as directed on package in large bowl.
Add remaining 1 3/4 cups milk and pie filling.
Beat at high speed for 2 minutes, scraping bowl. Spoon into pie shell.
Sprinkle with toasted coconut.
Chill.

title: spaghetti sauce italian style
directions: Puree tomatoes in a blender, then strain well.
Add tomatoes to tomato paste and cook on medium-high.
Do not burn.
Mix salt, 1 teaspoon pepper, 1 tablespoon basil leaves and 3 tablespoons garlic powder with tomato mixture.
Stir and reduce heat to medium-low and cook for about 1 hour before adding meat.
Combine ground beef, eggs, 1 teaspoon pepper, 1 tablespoon garlic powder and enough salt to season.
Mix well.
Add water-soaked bread and milk; knead well.
Roll into 1-inch balls and brown in oil over medium heat.
Drain well.
Cut sausage in links and brown.
Add sausage and meatballs with drippings to tomato sauce.
Cook for 3 hours over low heat, stirring occasionally.
Avoid burning sauce.

title: butternut squash pie
directions: Mix all together and pour into unbaked 9-inch or 10-inch pie shell.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: chocolate velvet dessert
directions: Mix crumbs and margarine and put in a 9 x 13-inch pan. Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.

title: pineapple casserole
directions: Pour pineapple, juice and all into a buttered 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish.
Combine flour and sugar.
Sprinkle over pineapple. Cover with cheese.
Spread crumbled Ritz crackers over cheese. Pour melted butter over all.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: potato soup
directions: Melt butter and brown onion.
Add potatoes, carrot, water, salt and pepper.
Bring to a boil and add farina.
Cook on low for 20 minutes.
Stir in milk and parsley and bring to a boil. Garnish with sour cream.

title: baked acorn squash
directions: Place squash halves, cut side down, in baking dish in small amount of water.
Bake at 400° about 20 to 30 minutes or until almost tender.
Saute celery and apples in butter in skillet for 5 minutes.
Stir in crumbs, cheese, salt and pepper.
Turn squash halves; fill and bake 10 to 15 minutes or until tender.

title: zucchini bread
directions: In large bowl, mix flour, sugar, baking powder, salt and walnuts.
Add coconut, if desired.
In small bowl, beat eggs slightly.
Stir in grated lemon peel, salad oil and shredded zucchini.
Combine bowls; pour mixture in 2 greased loaf pans. Bake for 1 hour at 350°; let bread cool for 10 minutes before serving.

title: microwave fudge
directions: In a glass bowl, combine the confectioners sugar, cocoa, salt, milk and vanilla; stir.
Melt the butter; pour on top.
Do not cover.
Cook on "High" for 3 minutes.
Remove from microwave and stir until smooth.
Blend in nuts.
Pour on waxed paper and refrigerate until firm.

title: almond cream frosting
directions: Cream butter; blend in powdered sugar. Add cream cheese and almond flavoring. Fold in finely chopped almonds.

title: chinese chews
directions: In a medium size cake pan, pat evenly and bake 15 minutes.

title: squash casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients except crackers.
Put in baking pan that has been sprayed with Pam.
Sprinkle with crumbs.
Bake in 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: richard simmons' quick and easy chicken breasts
directions: Skin, rinse and pat dry the chicken breasts.
Dip in egg and milk which have been mixed.
Mix flour and spices in Ziploc or paper bag.
Shake chicken in this to coat.
Dip chicken back in liquid, then in the crushed cereal and cheese mixture.
(More than 1 cup of cereal may be needed for a good coating.)
Bake, uncovered, for 1 hour in a 350° oven.

title: hamburger hot dish
directions: Mix and put in 9 x 13-inch pan the ground chuck and onion soup mix.
Spread the frozen mixed vegetables over meat.
Mix the hash browns, sour cream, soup and butter and spread over veggies.
Top with grated cheese.
Bake 1 1/2 hours at 350°.

title: cheese broccoli soup
directions: Saute chopped onion in margarine.
Add soups, broth and milk. Heat until warm.
Add grated Cheddar cheese and frozen, chopped broccoli (drained).
Cook until cheese melts and soup is hot.

title: baked spaghetti pie
directions: In 9 x 13-inch greased baking dish, mix cooked spaghetti, margarine, Parmesan cheese, salt, pepper and egg.
Spread mixture evenly in the dish.
Brown hamburger and onion.
Drain fat.
Mix in spaghetti sauce and spices.
Pour over spaghetti.
Sprinkle cheese over top.
Bake at 325° for 30 minutes.
Makes 8 servings.

title: shrimp with mushrooms
directions: Cook pasta according to package directions.
Drain and set aside.
Melt butter in large skillet over medium-high heat.
Add garlic and basil and cook 1 minute.
Stir often.
Add shrimp, mushrooms and pepper.
Cook 5 mintues, stirring occasionally. Serve over angel hair pasta.
Yields 2 to 3 servings.

title: sour cream bread
directions: Dissolve yeast and sugar in warm water in small mixing bowl; let stand 5 minutes.
Combine sour cream, salt and soda in a large mixing bowl; add yeast mixture, mixing well.
Gradually add flour and mix well.
Turn dough out on a lightly floured surface and knead 1 to 2 minutes or until smooth and elastic.
Shape into a ball; place in a greased bowl, turning to grease top.
Cover and let rise in a warm place, free from drafts, 1 1/2 hours or until doubled in bulk.
Punch dough down and divide in half.
Place each half in greased 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pan.
Cover and let rise until doubled in bulk (about 1 hour).
Bake at 375° for 35 to 40 minutes.
Yields 2 loaves.
(I make rolls from dough instead of bread.)

title: miss rose's spaghetti sauce
directions: Saute Onions in Oil.
In a separate pan, brown the Hamburg; drain and add to onions.
Add the remaining ingredients and mix well.
Bring to a boil, stirring constantly.
Reduce heat and simmer all day, stir occasionally.

title: cold pasta salad
directions: Cook pasta; cool.
Add remaining ingredients, except Parmesan cheese.
Mix or toss.
Add Parmesan to salad when ready to serve.

title: molded pear salad
directions: Stir
boiling
water over Jell-O; add pear juice, lemon juice, ginger and salt.
Mix cheese, nuts and salt.
Form into small balls.
Put
pears into mold and fill with cream cheese balls. Pour Jell-O over top. Chill.

title: pudding delight
directions: You will need 6 parfait glasses.

title: cucumber relish
directions: Slice onion and cucumbers.
Place in a dish.
Heat to boiling point, but do not boil sugar, vinegar, salt and dill weed.
Stir constantly.
Pour over onion and the cucumber, mix well.
Chill in refrigerator.

title: velveeta cheese chocolate fudge
directions: Melt together Velveeta and margarine in the top of a double boiler.
Then, add cocoa, sugar, vanilla and chopped nuts. Continue stirring until the sugar is dissolved.
Pour into 9 X 13 pan.
Let cool and cut into squares.

title: chicken spaghetti casserole
directions: Cook spaghetti in
chicken
broth,
add all ingredients and cook on top of stove until desired thickness.

title: chocolate drops
directions: Pour butter over coconut and mix well. Add next 5 ingredients. Mix well and chill about 3 hours. Shape into balls. Put in freezer for about 45 minutes. Melt wax and chips in double boiler. Dip balls in chocolate mixture and place on wax paper to cool. Use toothpicks to dip.

title: oriental chicken salad
directions: Mix and pour over salad. Let stand at least four hours. Enjoy, especially on a hot summer day.

title: vanilla wafer cake
directions: Cream the butter and sugar.
Beat in eggs, one at a time.
Add the vanilla wafers alternately with the milk. Fold in coconut and pecans.
Pour into an ungreased tube pan. Bake at 325° for 1 hour and 15 minutes. Serve with dollops of whipped cream.
Cake may be frozen.

title: shrimp butter
directions: Mix and chill.
Serve with crackers, bread cubes, etc.

title: margaret's irish breakfast scones
directions: Sift dry ingredients together and cut with butter until small crumbs.
Add cream or milk, eggs and raisins.
Dough will be sticky.

title: appetizer vienna bread
directions: Cut 3 lengthwise slits in bread. Cut 1-inch slices crosswise. Do not cut through bottom crust.
Melt margarine. Add onion, poppy seed and dry mustard. Add grated cheese and mushrooms.
Mixture will be gloppy. Spoon into sliced bread.
Use all of mixture. Wrap in heavy foil.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes on oven rack.
Now cut through bottom crust.

title: pizza
directions: Brown sausage in skillet.
Be sure to stir and break up in small pieces.
Add cheese, ketchup, Worcestershire sauce and oregano.
Cook over low heat for 5 or 10 minutes or until cheese has melted and other ingredients are mixed well.
Spread sausage mixture over bread.
Bake at 350° for 7 minutes.
After they cool, you can stack them up and freeze them.

title: sweet potatoes
directions: Drain potatoes; save juice.
Mash until smooth.
Melt oleo and add to potatoes.
Then add spices, sugar and enough juice to make like thick mashed potatoes.
Cover with chopped nuts.
Bake 1 hour, covered, at 375°.
Remove cover and brown for about 5 minutes.
Add marshmallows, if wanted.

title: poppy seed bread
directions: Mix all together and divide into two greased loaf pans.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: shrimp scampi
directions: Over moderately high heat, melt 1 tablespoon butter in saute pan.
Add garlic; saute for 1 minute.
Add shrimp; saute until shrimp are almost cooked.
Add diced tomatoes and onions.
Saute for 1 to 2 minutes.
Add seasonings and white wine.
Allow liquid to reduce to approximately 1/2 volume.
Add last tablespoon butter, swirling pan until melted.
Serve over rice or pasta. Makes 1 to 2 servings.

title: herb seasoning for meat
directions: Use 1 teaspoon on each piece of meat.

title: hot crabmeat bake
directions: Mix all ingredients except nuts.
Put mixture in casserole dish.
Sprinkle nuts on top.
Bake at 375° for 15 minutes.
Serve hot with crackers.

title: beet relish
directions: Mix all ingredients in a 3-quart pan.
Heat through.
When boiling, pour into 3 sterilized jars to within 1/2 inch of top. Put caps on.
Screw bands firmly tight.
Process in boiling water bath for 5 minutes.

title: microwave peanut clusters
directions: Place white chocolate and chocolate pieces in a 2 1/2-quart microwave-safe bowl. Cook, uncovered, in a countertop microwave oven on High about 2 1/2 minutes or just until mixture becomes smooth when stirred. Stir in peanuts. Drop peanut mixture from a teaspoon onto a baking sheet lined with waxed paper.
Chill about 30 minutes or until firm. Store tightly covered in refrigerator. Makes about 36 pieces.

title: freezer cole slaw
directions: Mix sugar, vinegar, salt, celery seed and mustard seed and boil 1 minute.
Cool and add to the cabbage mixture.
Freeze.
Eat as soon as it is thawed.

title: broccoli soup
directions: Saute onion and celery in butter.
Cook broccoli in broth. Combine all ingredients, except cream and mushrooms and refine in a blender.
Return mixture to pot and add cream and mushrooms. Heat and serve.

title: baptist wine
directions: Use a gallon jug or any large container; mix ingredients. Chill and serve.
Nice for holiday dinners or anytime.

title: sausage pinwheels
directions: Blend shortening with dry ingredients.
Add milk and mix well. Turn onto a floured surface and knead about one minute.

title: surprise potatoes
directions: Pare potatoes.
Roll in melted butter, then in cracker crumbs or crushed corn flakes.
Sprinkle with paprika and salt.
Place in covered casserole and bake at 375° for 1 1/4 hours.

title: toasted pecans
directions: Bring water to a rolling boil.
Add salt and pecans. Stir and boil for 5 minutes. Take off stove and pour into
a colander. Drain well. Do not rinse.
Put on a cookie sheet and place into oven set at 400° for 15 to 20 minutes. Keep stirred. Reduce oven to 250° for 1 hour.
Stir often.

title: crabmeat-broccoli casserole
directions: Thaw broccoli and cut into bite-size pieces.
Melt butter in pan and stir in flour and seasoning.
Add milk and cook on medium heat until thick.
Add crabmeat, onion and pimento.
Arrange broccoli in baking dish and spoon sauce over top.
Sprinkle almonds over sauce.
Bake at 375° for 20 minutes or until bubbly.

title: strawberry salad
directions: Mix and press in baking pan or dish; bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: chicken cashew casserole
directions: Stew chicken until tender.
Remove from bones and leave in fairly large pieces.
Saute onions and celery in butter.
Add soups, broth, seasonings and chicken.
Simmer all together for a few minutes.
Pour into 2-quart casserole.
Sprinkle with noodles and nuts and store in refrigerator overnight.
Bake in 350° oven for 45 minutes or until brown and bubbly.

title: louisiana shrimp
directions: Place all ingredients, except shrimp, in pot and heat until butter melts.
Place shrimp in single layer in glass dish.
Pour butter mixture over and bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: shrimp hors d'oeuvres
directions: Heat soup, gelatin and cream cheese in double boiler, stirring until smooth and creamy.
Cool.
Add vegetables and 1 pound small shrimp, chopped.
Chill in ring mold.

title: butterfinger cake
directions: Bake cake as directed on box.
Beat egg yolks, powdered sugar and oleo.
Fold in Cool Whip.
After cake cools, crumble 1/2 into large bowl, cover with 1/2 of Cool Whip mixture.
Cover this with 1/2 crushed candy bars.
Repeat layers.
Chill overnight, then serve.

title: orange cream salad
directions: Drain all canned fruits.
Combine and set aside.
Combine dry pudding mix, milk and frozen orange juice concentrate.
Beat until blended.
Mix in sour cream.
Fold into fruit mixture.
Cover and chill.

title: vanilla wafer cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add egg yolks and vanilla wafers. Stir well.
Add milk, coconut, nuts and vanilla.
Beat egg whites until stiff.
Fold whites into the mix.
Bake at 325° in tube pan for 1 1/2 hours.
Sprinkle powdered sugar on top.

title: forgotten chicken
directions: Grease 9 x 13-inch baking dish and place rice in the bottom. Combine soup and water.
Pour half of the soup mixture over rice and let stand a few minutes.
Place chicken over rice.
Add salt, pepper and remaining soup mixture.
Top with dry onion soup mix. Cover with foil and bake at 350° for 1 1/2 to 2 hours.

title: penuche
directions: Mix all the ingredients thoroughly.
Cook slowly until mixture forms a ball in water.
Add butter, nuts and vanilla.

title: yummy pork chops
directions: Brown chops in a non-stick electric frypan.
Remove from pan. Melt margarine in frypan.
Brown onion.
Remove from pan.
Place potato slices in bottom of frypan.
Lay pork chops on top of potatoes.
Spread onions on top of pork chops.
Pour cans of soup on top and then water over soup.
Cover, reduce heat to simmer and cook for 1 1/2 hours. Serves 6.

title: strawberry pecan cake
directions: Mix together cake mix and Jell-O.
Add other ingredients and mix until a soft batter is formed.
Pour into three (9-inch) greased and floured cake pans.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes (test with a toothpick).
Cool before frosting.

title: english tea cakes
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Cream butter and other shortening.
Add sugar, then eggs.
Mix dry ingredients and add to this mixture, alternating with the milk and vanilla.
(Just enough flour to make a soft dough may be added, if needed.)

title: spaghetti fruit salad
directions: In a saucepan, combine sugar, eggs, lemon juice and salt. Cook and stir over medium heat until temperature reaches 160° and mixture is thickened, about 4 minutes. Cool completely. Cook spaghetti according to package directions. Drain and rinse in cold water. Place in a large bowl. Drain pineapple, reserving juice. Pour juice over the spaghetti. Stir in the apples. Toss gently. Drain. Stir in the egg mixture and pineapple. Cover and refrigerate overnight. Fold in whipped topping before serving. Garnish with walnuts and cherries. Makes 12 to 14 servings.

title: vongoli casino(clams casino)
directions: Scrub clams in very cold water.
Dry and open.
Remove top shell and leave meat in bottom half.
Mix cheese, parsley, basil, garlic and cracker crumbs.
Sprinkle heaping tablespoon over clams.
Broil for about 3 to 5 minutes.
Do not burn.
Serve hot.

title: hummingbird cake
directions: Mix dry ingredients, then mix other ingredients.
Next, mix together gently.
Do not beat!!
Makes 3 layers.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: berries with honey yogurt cream
directions: Combine yogurt and sour cream. Spoon into a colander lined with cheesecloth or paper towels. Place over a bowl to drain for 30 minutes. Turn gently with rubber spatula. Continue to let drain for 4 hours. Transfer to a bowl. Stir in honey and refrigerate until ready to use. If using strawberries, cut in halves. Makes 8 servings.

title: porcupine meat balls
directions: Blend meat, rice and seasonings; form into 24 balls.
Place in baking dish.
Add tomato sauce, soup and water.
Cover and bake at 325° for 1 1/4 hours.
Serves 12.

title: frosted brownie-mallow bars
directions: Melt margarine with chocolate; remove from heat.
Add sugar; mix well.
Add flour, salt and baking powder, blending well.
Add eggs; beat well.
Mix in nuts and flavoring.
Pour into a greased and floured pan.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.
Top with marshmallows; return to oven for 2 to 3 minutes, or until marshmallows are soft; cool.

title: cream cheese frosting
directions: Combine all ingredients and beat until light and fluffy. Spread on cool cake.

title: crab puffs
directions: Mix everything.
Spread mixture on muffins and then cut in fours.
Broil 6 to 8 minutes.

title: deborah nelson's macaroni and cheese
directions: Bake 20 to 30 minutes at 400°.

title: chicken enchiladas
directions: Put oil to cover bottom of skillet and heat to medium.
Place one tortilla at a time in oil just long enough to soften (about 2-3 seconds) on each side.
Drain on paper towels.
Mix next 4 ingredients, adding a small amount of milk if it seems too thick. Place 6 tortillas in the bottom of a 9
x 13-inch baking dish, over lapping edges.
Spoon 1/2 of chicken mixture over tortillas and cover with cheese.
Place the next layer of tortillas on cheese, add remaining chicken mixture and top with cheese.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes or until bubbly.
Garnish and serve hot.

title: garnet's yellow squash relish
directions: Coarse grind squash, peppers, onions, tomatoes and cucumbers, using coarse blade/setting for grinder.
Add to mixture 1/2 cup salt and let stand for 1 to 2 hours.
Drain and rinse in cold water; drain again and put in large kettle with remaining ingredients.
Bring to boil and simmer, uncovered, stirring occasionally.
Cook 30 minutes or until desired consistency.
Pour into 6 to 8 pint jars and seal.
Process 5 minutes.

title: toasted pumpkin seeds
directions: Place seeds in a strainer and rinse well; drain. Melt butter and add to pumpkin seeds and stir to coat.
Arrange one layer deep in shallow baking pan. Sprinkle with salt. Bake in oven at 250°, stirring 2 to 3 times until golden brown, 30 to 40 minutes. Yields about 4 servings of 1 cup each.

title: cinnamon biscuits
directions: Melt margarine in a bowl; then dip each biscuit in melted margarine and then in sugar/cinnamon mixture.
Place in a pie pan and bake at 400° until done.

title: cream cheese pound cake
directions: Cream butter and cream cheese; add sugar and mix well.
Add eggs one at a time to creamed mixture.
Gradually add flour and flavoring.
Mix well.
Pour into a 10 inch tube pan or pound cake pan.
Bake for 1 hour and 15 minutes at 325 degrees.

title: chips chili and cheese squares
directions: Combine chilies, cheese, and green onions and spoon into a lightly sprayed 8 inch square cake pan.
Sprinkle tortilla chips over top.
Combine eggs, milk, and Tabasco and beat well.
Pour over chilies and cheese mixture.
Bake at 325 degrees for 30 to 35 minutes.
Serve warm or at room temperature.
Cut into small squares.
Makes about 3 dozen.

title: good chocolate cake
directions: Pour ingredients into mixing bowl in order given and mix well. Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.
Makes 1 (8 or 9-inch ) cake.

title: mini cinnamon rolls
directions: Unroll dough and separate into 4 rectangles.
Pinch seams to seal.
Stir together sugar and cinnamon and sprinkle evenly over rectangles.
Roll up starting with short side.
Press edges to seal.
Cut each log into 5 pieces and place in lightly greased 8-inch round cake pan.
Bake 12 -15 minutes at 350.
Stir together powdered sugar, milk, and vanilla and drizzle over rolls.

title: the great spam scam
directions: Dice Spam into 1/2-inch pieces. Cut onion into 1/8 or small portions. Slice, dice or press garlic cloves as desired.
If hot chili peppers are used, they may be introduced whole, sliced or diced or even squished.

title: broccoli-cauliflower salad
directions: Remove flowerets from broccoli and cauliflower. Cut into bite size pieces. Combine broccoli and cauliflower flowerets, pepper, mushrooms and celery. Toss lightly. Combine sugar, dry mustard, salt, vinegar, onion, oil and poppy seeds. Mix well and pour over vegetables. Chill for at least 2 hours, stirring occasionally.

title: seafood newburg
directions: Melt butter.
Blend in flour.
Add cream.
Cook and stir until thick and bubbly.
Stir small amounts of hot mix into yolks. Return to hot mix.
Cook and stir until thick.
Do not boil.
Stir in seafood.
Heat through.
Stir in wine, juice and salt. Sprinkle with paprika.
Serve over Pepperidge Farm pastry puffs or rice.

title: chocolate chip cake
directions: Mix last 2 ingredients together.
Cream butter, vanilla and eggs.
Add sugar, flour, baking powder and baking soda.
Mix well.
Fold in sour cream and chocolate chips.
Pour into a tube pan; spread evenly.
Top with sugar and cinnamon mixture.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: no fail pie crust
directions: Sift flour, salt and sugar into large bowl; blend in shortening by hand pastry blender.
Mix water, juice, beaten egg and mix in with fork by making 3 or 4 holes in flour mixture and pouring equal parts in each.
Bring all together in a ball with hands; put 1/2 on 2 wax papers and form into 2 tight balls.
Put in refrigerator until chilled.
Each ball makes 2 crusts; cut in half and roll between 2 sheets of wax paper.

title: no fail pie crust
directions: Makes six single crusts or enough for 3 double-crust pies.

title: spaghetti sauce and meat balls
directions: Mix together ingredients; roll individually. Put balls in cake pan and bake at 350° for 35 to 45 minutes.

title: kim chi
directions: Chop cabbage into bite size pieces and wash several times in colander.
Seal with salt layering and set in sun.
Leave 4 hours and toss or turn upside down each hour.
Cabbage will dehydrate after 4 hours.
Wash cabbage thoroughly and add green onions and garlic.
Pour vinegar over and toss cabbage sprinkling with cayenne and then sugar and adjust seasoning to taste.
Let set in refrigerator until meal.
This will keep well for several days.

title: easy hamburger quiche
directions: Brown meat in skillet over medium heat. Drain.
Blend next 4 ingredients until smooth.
Stir in meat, cheese, green onion and pepper.
Turn into pie shell. Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes or until golden brown on top and knife inserted in center comes out clean.

title: oatmeal raisin cookies
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Drop by teaspoon on a greased cookie sheet.
Flatten with a glass dipped in sugar.
Bake at 350° until done.

title: lasagne
directions: Cook noodles; set aside.
Brown hamburger.

Add Ragu sauce. Layer as follows in a 13 x 9-inch pan: sauce on bottom, layer of noodles, half of Ricotta cheese, meat sauce, 1 cup Mozzarella, layer of noodles, half of Ricotta, meat sauce, Mozzarella and American cheeses and Parmesan cheese.
Bake at 350° to 375° for 45 minutes to an hour.
Can make ahead of time.

title: baked beans
directions: Mix all ingredients, except bacon.
Place bacon over top. Bake in casserole dish at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: sensational pumpkin pie
directions: Stir in pumpkin and spices with wire whisk.
Mix well.
Spread over cream cheese layer.
Refrigerate at least 3 hours.
Garnish with additional whipped topping and nuts, if desired.

title: spaghetti salad
directions: Cook spaghetti; drain.	While still warm, add Italian dressing.
Add pimentos, olives and 1/3 cup onions.
Mix well.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Boil sugar and evaporated milk for 3 minutes.
Take off stove and add marshmallow cream and peanut butter.
Whip and put in greased pan.

title: breakfast souffle
directions: Butter 8 slices of bread on both sides.
Cube in tiny squares. Cook bacon or ham and break into pieces.
Beat together 8 eggs and 3 cups milk.
Add remaining ingredients.
Place in casserole pan and let stand overnight.
In morning, bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until knife or toothpick comes out clean.

title: cherry cobbler
directions: Put cherries and pineapple in bottom of casserole.
Combine pecans and cake mix; sprinkle over.
Pour melted butter over cake mix.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: chicken cacciatore
directions: Brown chicken in little oil.
Remove chicken.
Brown garlic and add cut up tomatoes and tomato sauce.
Add Italian seasoning and basil.
Simmer.
Add chicken; simmer until chicken is tender. Fifteen minutes before serving, add white wine.
Brad Staven

title: heavenly chik casserole
directions: Saute celery, onion and mushrooms in small amount of oil.
Mix all ingredients and put into greased casserole.
Sprinkle with paprika.
Bake 45 to 60 minutes at 350°. (For the last 15 minutes of baking, sliced almonds may be sprinkled over casserole.)

title: cauliflower cheese puff
directions: Cook cauliflower in salted boiling water until barely tender. Drain.
Put in a greased shallow baking dish.
Make white sauce; add cheese.
Beat egg yolks, sugar, salt and pepper.
Add to white sauce.
Beat egg whites until very stiff and fold into white sauce.
Pour over cauliflower.
Bake at 350° for about 20 minutes or until sauce is firm.

title: savory meat loaf
directions: Soften oats in milk.
Dice onion, green pepper and celery. In a large bowl, add vegetables and oats to ground beef.
Add salt and pepper; mix well.
Shape mixture into a loaf to fit a 2 x 8 x 8-inch lightly greased baking pan.
Mix catsup and water; spoon over the meat.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Serve hot or slice to be filling for sandwiches.

title: mexican "fried" ice cream
directions: Fry tortilla, sprinkle with some of the cinnamon/sugar mixture. Put the remainder of the cinnamon/sugar mixture into the cornflake crumbs. Roll the scoops of ice cream in the corn flake mixture. Put some whipped cream in the middle of the tortilla, set the ice cream in the middle of the tortilla, and garnish with whipped cream, (optional toppings) and a cherry.

title: hunter-style chicken
directions: In a large skillet, heat together butter and oil.
Cook chicken pieces over medium heat about 25 minutes, turning to brown.
Remove chicken to a 12 x 7 1/2 x 2-inch baking dish and keep warm.

title: cherokee casserole
directions: Brown meat; add onions and cook until tender.
Stir in ingredients in order given except 3 of the olives and cheese. Bring to a boil, reduce heat and simmer for 5 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Spoon into baking dish and top with cheese.
Broil until cheese is melted.
Garnish with olives.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: lemon barbecued meat loaves
directions: About 50 minutes before serving, preheat oven to 350°.
In a large bowl, combine ground chuck, bread, lemon juice, onion, egg and salt.
Mix well and shape into 6 individual loaves.
Place in a greased 13 x 9-inch baking pan. Bake 15 minutes.

title: meat balls recipe
directions: Mix well and form into balls; brown in skillet, turning constantly, so they will keep their shape.
Drain and add to sauce.

title: raspberry vanilla pudding(makes 4 servings)
directions: I double the recipe.

title: oriental cabbage salad
directions: Crush noodles slightly; place in colander.
Pour boiling water over noodles to soften very slightly.
Drain well.
In a large bowl, combine noodles, cabbage, onions and sesame seed.

title: ham and noodle casserole
directions: Cook noodles in salted water and drain.
Beat eggs and sour cream together with salt and pepper.
Butter a 2-quart casserole dish; add noodles, mixed with ham and pour sour cream mixture over the ham and noodles.
Add pieces of butter on top.
Bake, covered, at 350° for about
1 hour.
For a crisp texture, remove cover for the last 15 minutes.

title: orange peach cake
directions: Mix all together in an ungreased 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake at 350° approximately 40 to 45 minutes.
You can use any flavor cake mix and any flavor pie filling to make different combinations.

title: cake-a-plenty
directions: Prepare cake mix according to directions.
Bake in cookie sheet 15 minutes.
Spread pineapple on cooled cake.
Mix together pudding, cheese and milk.
Pour over pineapple.
Spread on topping. Sprinkle with coconut.
Refrigerate.

title: fresh berry soup
directions: Mix the first 3 ingredients.
Chill.
At the time of serving, sprinkle with fruit.
Garnish with sprig of mint.

title: low-fat apricot muffins
directions: Pour boiling water over apricot pieces; let set.
Meanwhile, sift the dry ingredients together.
Stir together the eggs, oil and juice.
Mix together the wet and dry ingredients alternately to just moisten.
Place in paper cups in muffin pan.
Bake for 20 to 25 minutes at 375°.

title: watergate salad
directions: Mix all together.
Add dry jello and mix again.
Chill 1 to 2 hours and serve cold.

title: "yum-yum" dum-dum cake
directions: Make cake as directed on box and bake for 20 to 25 minutes in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Prepare the cream cheese with milk and slowly cream together well.
Add pudding and crushed pineapple.
Spread mixture over cooled, baked Jiffy cake.
Top off with Cool Whip. Sprinkle with sliced nuts (almonds and walnuts).
Chill for 12 hours.

title: potato casserole
directions: Combine ingredients.
Place in a greased casserole.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes.
Serves 8.

title: party chicken
directions: Place rice, soups (mixed with water), salt, Accent (m.s.g.) and pepper in bottom of casserole dish.
Dip chicken in margarine; place on top of rice mixture.
Sprinkle with salt.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.
Serves 8 adults.
Serve with green vegetable and fruit salad.

title: dirt cake
directions: Crush cookies.
Mix butter, cheese and sugar.
Mix milk, pudding and Cool Whip.
Combine mixtures.
Use 8-inch terra cotta planter; line with foil.
Layer cookies and cream mixture alternating with cookies; save some cookies for top layer and place bouquet of silk flowers and gummy worms (optional). Refrigerate.

title: orange balls
directions: Mix.
Roll in balls size of walnuts.
Roll in finely chopped walnuts.
Work rapidly and the walnuts stick better to the balls.

title: zucchini frittata
directions: Beat eggs with salt and pepper.
Stir in cheese, squash, parsley and basil.
Preheat broiler.

title: best yet hot rolls
directions: In bowl, dissolve yeast in water.
Add milk, sugar, salt, egg, shortening and half of the flour to yeast.
Mix with spoon until smooth.
Add remaining flour and mix until smooth.
Turn dough onto lightly floured working area; knead until smooth (5 minutes). Round up in greased bowl.
Bring greased side up; cover with Handi-Wrap.
Let rise in warm place (85°) until double, about 1 1/2 hours.
Punch down and let rise again until almost double (about 30 minutes).
Shape dough into rolls.
Place in greased baking pan and let rise.
Bake at 450°.

title: ham and potato au gratin
directions: Combine potatoes, ham and onion in a greased 1-quart casserole.
Set aside.
In a saucepan, melt the butter and stir in flour until thick and smooth.
Gradually, add milk, stirring constantly, until thick and bubbly.
Add cheese, salt and pepper and stir until cheese melts.
Pour over potato mixture and gently stir to mix.
Garnish with parsley.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: forgotten chicken
directions: On bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan, spread rice.
Place pieces of chicken over rice.
Mix soup and water together.
Pour over chicken.
Sprinkle paprika over top.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: blueberry muffins
directions: Cream butter and sugar, add eggs and salt.
Alternate flour and baking powder.
Add berries.
Put in muffin pans.
Sprinkle tops with sugar.
Bake 20 to 30 minutes at 375°.
Let cool before removing from pan.
Will have a nice crusty top.
(Test for doneness and don't fill too full.)
Makes about 18.

title: wassail
directions: In large saucepan, heat cider and cinnamon stick to boiling, reduce heat.
Cover and simmer 5 minutes.
Uncover, stir in remaining ingredients, except orange slices.
Simmer 5 more minutes.
Serve warm in punch bowl with floating orange slices.

title: spring supreme cake
directions: Mix together cake mix, 2 eggs and oil. Add pecans and coconut. Press mixture into greased 13 x 9-inch pan. Beat the cream cheese, 2 remaining eggs and powdered sugar.
Pour over top of cake mixture. Bake at 300° for 1 hour.

title: williamsburg sally lunn bread
directions: Put yeast in warm milk.
Cream together butter and sugar.
Add beaten eggs and mix well with flour to which salt has been added. Alternate with milk and yeast.
Let rise 2 hours in warm place, then beat well.
Pour into well-buttered tube cake pan.
Let rise again 1 hour before baking in moderate oven at 250° to 300° for 45 minutes.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Combine sweet potatoes, sugar, eggs, vanilla, milk and 1/2 cup margarine.
Beat with electric mixer until smooth.
Spoon into a greased 2-quart casserole dish.

title: crunchy granola
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Mix the first 6 ingredients in a large bowl.
In small pan bring to boil the honey, oil and cinnamon. Pour the honey mixture over the dry ingredients and mix thoroughly.
Spread on 2 greased cookie sheets or jelly roll pans. Bake 25 to 30 minutes, stirring often.
Watch closely the last 10 minutes so it doesn't get too brown.
Cool undisturbed and crumble.

title: low calorie cream cheese frosting
directions: Mix altogether.
Covers 1 (8-inch) round cake or 10 cupcakes. Contains 60 calories; 1/2 bread plus 1/2 fat exchange.

title: money saver soup(bean)
directions: Soak dried beans overnight in water to cover.
Drain.
Cook for 1 1/2 hours in 6 cups fresh water on simmer.
Add all other ingredients and simmer for 30 to 45 minutes longer.
Serve.
This soup freezes well and is even better the next day.

title: mary suddarth's potato soup
directions: Cook celery, onions and carrots until done in the water.
Add potatoes; cook until just tender.
Add milk and evaporated milk. Cook until this boils.
You may want to thicken slightly.

title: enpanadas(a mexican baked pastry)
directions: Mix ingredients thoroughly; add water until a firm dough is reached.
Make biscuit size patties and roll out.
Fill with filling and fold in half, pressing edge with fingers or fork. Bake on cookie sheet in oven at 350° until brown.

title: grilled sea scallops
directions: Whisk lime juice, oil, garlic, cumin, chili powder, salt and cayenne.
Skewer scallops and tomatoes. Drip on marinade.
Place in refrigerator and baste after 30 minutes. Grill over charcoal. Baste with marinade occasionally. Don't turn skewers.
Serve after 5 to 7 minutes with lime.

title: shepherd's pie casserole
directions: Line a pie pan with 1 cup mashed potatoes.
Mix corn and ground beef together, adding 1 cup mashed potatoes.
Pour into lined pie pan.
Cover all with last cup of mashed potatoes.
Bake at 325° for 20 minutes until potato top starts to brown.
Let set 5 minutes.
Cut into slices.
An excellent casserole.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: *These come in rolls and are hard to find.
I substitute a 2 pound box of Velveeta and garlic powder to taste.
Be careful if you use garlic salt.

title: creole garlic bread
directions: Spread bread slices with margarine.
Place on baking sheet. Sprinkle with garlic powder, pepper, cheese and parsley.
Broil until lightly browned.
Yields 6 to 8 servings.

title: crunchy grams
directions: Line cookie sheet with crackers.
Cook butter and brown sugar 5 minutes.
After reaching a boil, turn down to medium.
Add pecans and pour over crackers.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes. Remove to wax paper and cool.

title: scalloped potatoes
directions: Scald enough milk to cover 3/4 of potatoes.
Layer potatoes. In between layers add salt, pepper, chopped onion, butter and flour.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes covered 1 1/2 hours or until brown.

title: maryland crab cakes
directions: Note:
Use real mayonnaise, diet does not work.

title: southern crab cakes
directions: Mix first 7 ingredients together.
Press mixture into 8 firm cakes.
Chill well.
Just before serving, dip cakes in flour, then in bread crumbs.
Melt small amount of butter in frying pan; saute cakes quickly over high heat until golden brown, turning once.
Serve on warm platter.
Makes 4 to 5 servings.

title: spicy meat loaf
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Melt butter in medium saucepan.
Add next 5 ingredients and saute until vegetables begin to brown (about 5 minutes).
Set aside.

title: party mix
directions: Heat oven to 250°.
Combine cereal, crackers, pretzels and nuts in oblong pan, 13 x 9 1/2 x 2-inches.
Blend butter and seasonings; pour over cereal mixture.
Stir thoroughly.
Bake 30 minutes.
Makes about 6 cups.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Sift dry ingredients together 3 times.
Beat eggs.
Add all other ingredients at once and mix well.
Pour into 2 well-greased loaf pans.
Bake 1 hour at 325°.

title: oriental shrimp salad
directions: Mix together and refrigerate.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Melt oleo.
Mix with stuffing mix.
Place 3/4 of mixture in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Add layer of chicken.
Mix soups, celery, onion and lemon juice.
Pour over chicken.
Add remainder of stuffing mix.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: chicken cordon bleu
directions: Spread breasts flat; fold cheese and ham slices to fit on top. Fold breasts over filling; fasten with toothpicks.
Mix flour and paprika on waxed paper; coat chicken pieces.
Place in covered roasting pan.
Pour over wine and dissolved bouillon mixture. Bake at 350° for 1 1/4 hours, turning chicken over after first 30 minutes.
Remove chicken; thicken liquid with mixture of cream and cornstarch.
Serve over top of chicken.

title: spaghetti-quick!
directions: Stir all together and simmer 15 minutes.
We prefer this over egg noodles or fettucini instead of the traditional spaghetti noodles.

title: better than robert redford
directions: Mix butter, flour and chopped pecans.
Press into a 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan and bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Cool.

title: dietetic strawberry pie
directions: Combine grape juice, water and cornstarch in a saucepan.
Cook over medium heat until clear.
Mixture will not thicken.
Remove from heat.
Stir in jello until dissolved.
Chill in bowl in refrigerator until partially set.
Stir in strawberries.
Spoon into pie shell.
Chill in refrigerator for 2 to 3 hours, until set.

title: 7 layer cookies
directions: In a 9 x 13-inch pan, melt 1 stick butter; then sprinkle rest of ingredients over it in order listed.
Drizzle 1 can condensed milk over top.
Bake for 30 minutes at 350°.
Cool and cut.

title: corn and tomato casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients except crumbs, butter and cheese. Pour into casserole dish.
Sprinkle cheese and crumbs over mixture and dot with butter.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Serves 4.

title: crepes
directions: For Crepes Suzette:
Prepare and cook same way. After cooking, take a can of fruit, drained, and roll some in the crepe.
Cover with whip cream.

title: banana nut bread
directions: If using self-rising flour, omit soda and salt.

title: justin wilson chicken
directions: Place in a large roasting bag.
Roast in a 325° oven for 1 1/2 to 2 hours.
Salt generously.

title: macaroni salad
directions: Cook macaroni according to directions.
Drain.
Rinse with cold water and drain.
Chill at least 1 hour.
Cook meat in skillet until brown; drain.
Stir in taco seasoning and French dressing; cool.
Combine macaroni, beef mixture and remaining ingredients in large bowl, tossing well.
Serve salad immediately.

title: peach pudding(this is a peach of a pudding.)
directions: In a greased baking dish, place peaches.
Mix the rind with the orange juice and add to peaches.
In a bowl, sift the dry ingredients.

title: bacon stuffed mushrooms(appetizer)
directions: Wash mushrooms well; remove stems, and dry.
In a 1 1/2-quart casserole, place chopped stems and chopped onion.
Cover and microwave at High power for 4 minutes.
Stir after 2 minutes.
To the hot mixture, add cream cheese; mix well.
Stir in bread crumbs and bacon.

title: sweet potato pie
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Pour into the pie crust.
Bake at 350° for an hour.

title: pie filling
directions: Cook until bubbly.
Remove from heat and add 3 drops yellow food coloring.
Slice apples and peel in quart jar.
Pour in mixture and seal 20 minutes in water bath.

title: chicken tetrazzini
directions: Heat
butter in large sauce pan.
Add flour and seasonings. Stir until smooth and bubbly.
Remove from heat; stir in broth and cream, add spaghetti, chicken, and mushrooms.
Then add cheese and return to heat until cheese melts.
Serve hot.

title: preserving friendship
directions: Remove all judgment.
Finely chop all criticism.
Add all ingredients and mix well.
Cover and simmer slowly over low heat, occasionally adding encouraging words.
When right consistency, pour into warm hearts and seal with hugs.

title: sour cream banana bars
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Grease and flour pan.
Mix sugar, sour cream, butter or oleo and eggs.
Beat in the bananas and vanilla; beat in flour, salt and baking soda.
Stir in nuts, then spread in jelly roll pan.
Bake until light brown.

title: steak and veggie stew
directions: Heat oil in 4-quart container; add meat and stir 4 to 5 minutes until browned.
Stir in veggies and thyme.
In small bowl, mix well water and gravy mix.
Mix together in pan; bring to boil. Reduce heat; cover and simmer until all tender (8 to 10 minutes). Enjoy.
Good health!

title: taco dip
directions: Brown hamburger and drain.
Add taco seasoning and beans; heat until warm.
Spread in pan or flat bowl.
Mix sour cream and taco sauce and spread on top.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Bake at 325° until hot and cheese melted.
Serve with tortilla chips.

title: lemon tea cake
directions: Mix together with mixer.
Pour into greased bread loaf pan. Bake for 55 minutes at 350°.
This is an excellent and very easy pound cake.
You can serve with fruit, whipped cream or ice cream.

title: chocolate oatmeal cake
directions: Mix oats and boiling water together and set aside.
Cream shortening with sugar and eggs.
Add the oatmeal mixture.
Add the flour, cocoa, baking soda, salt, and vanilla, and beat until smooth.
Pour into a greased and floured oblong cake pan and bake at 350 degrees for 35 minutes.

title: charlotte's no-fault 100 percent whole wheat bread
directions: Place whole wheat flour in a large mixing bowl and set it in the oven at the lowest temperature for 20 minutes.
While the flour is warming, dissolve the 2 yeast packages in 1 cup warm water.
Add the honey to mix and set aside while the flour is being warmed. When the flour has been warmed, combine yeast, molasses and salt; add to flour.
Stir, don't knead, slowly adding 2 1/2 cups of remaining water to produce a sticky dough.
Oil your pans, filling them between 1/3 and 1/2 full.
Let dough rise for 1 hour.
Bake in preheated 375° oven for 35 to 40 minutes.
Yields 2 large loaves.

title: chicken and rice
directions: Roll chicken pieces in seasoned flour.
Heat oil and butter in large skillet.
Brown chicken pieces in oil.
Remove to a plate. Add onion, peppers, celery, mushrooms, tomatoes and garlic.
Cook until soft.
Add soup and water.
Bring to a boil.

title: different dip
directions: Cut cheese in strips.
Chop onions with stems.
Blend all ingredients with electric mixer until well mixed.
Serve on platter or in bowl garnished with sliced onions, paprika and parsley.
Excellent with a variety of crackers.

title: sierra ski brunch
directions: Butter bread and set aside.
In a skillet, brown mushrooms and onions in melted butter.
Cook 5 to 8 minutes, or until tender. Cut sausage into bite-size pieces and saute in separate skillet until done.
Set aside.

title: chicken tetrazzini
directions: Place chicken in deep boiler with water to cover.
Simmer until tender.
Remove chicken and reserve 1 cup of broth.
In remaining broth, cook the spaghetti according to package instructions.
Cut chicken into bite-sized pieces.
Cook bell pepper and onion in the reserved cup of broth until tender.
Combine spaghetti (which has been drained), diced chicken, bell pepper and onion with the 1 cup broth.
Add the remaining ingredients except half the cheese and all the almonds.
Place in baking dish.
Sprinkle with the remaining cheese and almonds.
Bake at 400° for 20 minutes.
Serves 12 to 15.
Freezes well.

title: sweet potatoes
directions: Mix all together and place in buttered 9 x 12-inch baking pan.

title: parmesan potatoes
directions: Preheat oven to 350 degrees. Melt margarine in 9

X 13 pan while preheating. Put flour, parmesan cheese, salt and pepper in baggie. Place a few diced potatoes at a time in bag and shake to coat. Place potatoes in single layer in pan. Bake for 1 hour; turn once during baking.

title: fresh strawberry pie
directions: Combine flour and oleo with pastry cutter.
Press dough into pie pan with fingers.
This crust cannot be rolled.
Bake at 400 degrees for 10 - 12 minutes until lightly brown, cool.

title: spinach apple toss
directions: In a 10-inch skillet, cook bacon over medium-high heat, stirring occasionally until browned.
Drain off fat.

title: crowd pleaser vegetable casserole
directions: Mix and pour in casserole sprayed with Pam, vegetables, cheese and soups.
Top with Ritz crackers; dot with margarine. Top with slivered almonds.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: spaghetti michael
directions: Cook and drain spaghetti accordingly.
Saute ham, onion, pepper and mushrooms in 2 tablespoons butter until onion is clear. Butter a 2-quart casserole.
Put a layer of spaghetti in bottom of casserole, follow with a layer of ham mixture, Cheddar cheese and then a layer of tomatoes.
The top layer should be cheese. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: refried nacho dip
directions: Spread beans in 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Sprinkle with taco seasoning.
Layer sour cream, chili peppers and olives.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Add cheese and bake 10 minutes more.
Serve with tortilla chips.

title: seashore casserole(kids can make this)
directions: Combine all ingredients except cheese and chips; mix well. Place in a casserole.
Sprinkle cheese and chips evenly on top. Bake in a preheated 350° oven for 30 minutes.
Serves 4.

title: spaghetti pie
directions: Cook spaghetti according to package directions; drain.
Toss with butter.
Beat together eggs and first 2 cheeses.
Stir into spaghetti.
Form spaghetti into crust in pan.
Spread Ricotta over bottom of spaghetti crust.
Top with spaghetti sauce.
Bake uncovered for 25 minutes at 350°.
Top with shredded Mozzarella and bake 5 minutes more.
Cool 10 minutes.
(Use greased 10-inch pie plate).

title: layered spinach salad
directions: Wash spinach; tear into bite size pieces.
Drain well.
Slice mushrooms and onions.
Beginning with spinach, layer in large salad bowl.
Add a layer of frozen peas.
Bacon bits may be added next, or if you prefer them crunchy, sprinkle on top before serving.
Mix the sour cream and mayonnaise; spread over top, sealing completely to the edges.
Sprinkle grated cheese over top. Cover and refrigerate overnight.

title: millet pudding
directions: Place all ingredients into blender bowl.
Blend until smooth. Pour into bowl or bowls and chill.
Will congeal into nice pudding.

title: chili cheese steaks
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In cup combine flour, salt, chili powder and pepper.
Trim excess fat from meat.
Cut into six pieces.
Place meat on board and sprinkle with flour mixture. Pound into meat on both sides.

title: polish goulash
directions: Cut Polish sausage into desired lengths.
Cut potatoes into quarters.
Slice cabbage, pepper and onions.
Put oil and water into large saucepan.
Cook all ingredients together over medium-low heat until well done.
(Can be prepared on grill.)

title: broccoli cornbread
directions: Combine all ingredients and pour into a greased shallow casserole dish or can use muffin pan.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until golden brown.

title: 7-minute frosting
directions: Combine all ingredients, except vanilla, in top of double boiler.
Place over boiling water and beat with rotary beater or mixer until mixture stands in stiff peaks (takes a good 7 minutes).
Scrape bottom and sides of pan occasionally.
Fold in vanilla.

title: strawberry dip
directions: Mix together and beat all ingredients. Chill and serve with fresh fruit slices.

title: million dollar fudge
directions: Blend together in saucepan sugar, milk and butter or margarine. Cook on medium-low, stirring until mixture has boiled gently 5 minutes.
In a large mixing bowl, break the chocolate bar; add chocolate bits, Marshmallow Creme and unsweetened chocolate.
Add cooked mixture, blending well, then vanilla and nuts.
Beat until creamy and all marshmallow streaks have disappeared.
Pour into a buttered pan (9 x 14-inches or 11 x 16-inches), depending upon thickness of fudge desired.
Place in refrigerator to cool.
This fudge may be frozen and taken out and thawed at room temperature. Cut in pieces and leave in pan, but wrap securely, leaving it wrapped to unthaw.

title: raspberry cream salad
directions: Dissolve jello in boiling water.
Add pineapple and chill until partly set.
Add banana and nuts.
Combine soft cream cheese with mayonnaise and whipped cream.
Fold into jello mixture and chill.

title: beef stew
directions: Brown meat in hot oil.
Add other ingredients.
Cover and simmer 1 1/2 hours, stirring occasionally.
Remove bay leaf.
May be thickened by mixing 1/4 cup cold water and 2 tablespoons flour, then adding to stew.
Simmer 5 minutes more.

title: soda cracker pie
directions: Beat egg whites and cream of tartar until stiff. Gradually add sugar and vanilla.
Blend in crackers and pecans.
Bake in pie plate at 350° for 20 minutes. Cool and top with whipped cream.

title: lo-cal dessert
directions: Heat pineapple and gelatin until gelatin dissolves.
Let cool, then add remaining ingredients.

title: cabbage salad
directions: Put into pan the oil, vinegar, sugar and celery seed.
Boil for 2 minutes.
Let set 5 minutes.
Pour over shredded cabbage. Do not stir.
Let set 24 hours.

title: old-fashioned bread stuffing
directions: Cook onion and celery in butter until tender.
Mix seasonings together and sprinkle over bread cubes.
Add onion and celery mixture and water.
Mix well.
Makes 8 cups.

title: cheese spaghetti
directions: Cut up bacon and fry.
(Do not drain bacon fat.)
Add sauce. Bring to a boil. Cut up cheese. Drop into sauce mixture.
Let cheese melt.
Cook noodles.
Drain and rinse.
Add sauce and noodles together. Stir.

title: salmon loaf
directions: Save juice from flaked salmon to go with the cup of milk.
Mix all together.
Put in a loaf pan.
Set pan in another larger pan of water to bake.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 60 minutes.

title: mamaw's banana nut bread
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs, crushed bananas and milk; mix well.
Add flour and nuts and stir well.
Pour into a greased loaf pan and bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Allow to cool in pan 10 minutes, then place bread on cooling rack.
This is wonderful eaten warm and with cream cheese.
Makes 2 loaves.
Could also be made into muffins, baking 10 to 15 minutes.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients in a large bowl and mix well.
Pour into greased casserole.
Sprinkle with paprika.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: fudge
directions: Bring to a boil first 3
ingredients.
Boil 2 minutes; let stand for 20 minutes.
Beat in peanut butter and vanilla.
Pour in greased pan.

title: dainty lily cookies
directions: Cream the cream cheese, butter and flour.
Roll dough out on a floured board.
Cut with a 2-inch round cookie cutter.
Form round into a cornucopia by bringing 2 rounded edges together and letting them overlap.
Press gently to shape like
a lily.
Fill open part with marmalade.
Bake at 375° for 15 minutes.
Cool, then drench with powdered sugar.
Yields 6 dozen.

title: lime jello salad
directions: Mix jello using directions on package.
Then add remaining ingredients and mix well.
Cool until set.

title: freezer fruit sherbet
directions: Combine bananas, pineapple and cherries in container of an electric blender; blend until smooth.
Pour mixture into large mixing bowl.
Combine remaining ingredients in container of electric blender.
Blend until smooth; add to blended fruit.
Mix all ingredients well, cover and freeze until firm.
Yields about 2 quarts.

title: fig preserves
directions: Pour boiling water over figs.
Let stand 15 minutes.
Drain; rinse figs in cold water.
Prepare syrup by mixing sugar and water.
Boil rapidly 10 minutes and skim, then drop figs into syrup a few at a time.
Cook rapidly until figs are transparent. Lift out and place them in shallow pans.
Boil syrup down until thick.
Pour over figs and let stand 6 to 8 hours.
Sliced lemon or sliced preserved ginger may be added during 10 minutes boiling. Fill jars to within 1/2 inch of top.
Put on cap; screw lids firmly tight.
Process in boiling water bath 10 minutes.
Yields 20 (8 ounce) jars.

title: caesar salad
directions: Rub wooden bowl with garlic bulb or use garlic press.
Add oil, lemon juice, wine vinegar, Parmesan cheese and egg (coddled for 1 1/2 minutes in boiling water).
Add salt, pepper and dry mustard.
Mix.
Add lettuce and croutons; toss.
Anchovies may be served on the side.

title: beef and potato mix
directions: Brown steak in hot oil, add next 14 ingredients.
Cover and simmer 45 minutes.
Add mushrooms, cook another 35 minutes. Remove cinnamon sticks, combine flour and 3/4 cup water in jar. Shake.
Stir in stew, cook until thickened.
Pour into 4-quart casserole dish.
Stir Parmesan cheese into hot mashed potatoes. Spoon potatoes around casserole.
Sprinkle with paprika.
Bake at 375° for 50 minutes.

title: tetrazzini
directions: Saute vegetables in butter; mix in remaining ingredients (except cheese).
