Place in 2 quart casserole dish; sprinkle Parmesan cheese on top, and bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: strawberry fruitcake
directions: Wash berries. Set a few aside for garnish and slice the rest. Add sugar and set aside. Sift flour, baking powder, salt and 2 tablespoons sugar. Cut in Crisco until well blended. Stirring quickly, add enough milk to make a soft dough. Turn out onto floured board and shape into 2 rounds, 1/2-inch thick and 7-inches in diameter.
Transfer to greased baking sheets and bake 15 minutes at 400°.
Place one hot layer on serving platter and butter well. Spread with sweetened berries.
Place second layer on top and top with whipping cream and garnish with whole strawberries.
Cut into wedges and serve.

title: santa claus cake
directions: Mix eggs
and
dry ingredients together.
Add fruit and nuts; mix well.
Pour
into greased and waxed paper lined tube pan. Bake at 300° for 1 to 1 1/2 hours.

title: olive nut spread
directions: Mix softened cream cheese.
Add the salad dressing and blend well.
Add the chopped pecans and olives.
Add the olive juice; stir well.
Store in container and refrigerate several hours or overnight.
Spread on whole wheat bread or rye.
Very good.

title: big time bonbons
directions: Using a melon ball scoop, make 30 to 35 small ice cream balls. Place on a chilled baking sheet lined with waxed paper and place in freezer.
Melt butter and chocolate in small saucepan over low heat.
Stir in evaporated milk.
Allow to cool as ice cream hardens in freezer for about 2 hours.
Remove ice cream balls and dip them, one at a time, into chocolate sauce.
Press miniature Valentine's Day heart onto each chocolate covered ice cream ball. Replace on waxed paper and return baking sheet to freezer to reharden before serving.

title: broccoli rice casserole
directions: Brown onion in	2 teaspoons butter; add rice, broccoli, chicken soup, milk and chicken broth.
Sprinkle cheese on top. Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes. Serves 8 to 10.

title: angel biscuits
directions: Heat shortening and buttermilk in small saucepan until melted (buttermilk will separate). Cool to lukewarm.

Transfer to large bowl. Dissolve yeast in warm water in cup. Let stand until bubbly, 5 minutes. Stir into buttermilk mixture with sugar. Combine flour, baking powder and salt in medium bowl. Stir into yeast mixture. Cover and refrigerate overnight. Grease two cookie sheets. Divide dough in half. On floured surface with floured rolling pin, roll to 15 X 12 inch rectangle, 1/4 inch thick. Brush dough with half of melted butter, fold in half to make two layers. Cut with biscuit cutter and place close together on cookie sheet. Cover and let rise (about 1 hour). Preheat oven to 400 degrees. Bake biscuits 12 - 14 minutes until golden brown. Cool on wire rack or serve immediately. Can be made ahead of time. Wrap well and freeze up to 1 month. Reheat on cookie sheet in preheated oven at 400 degrees for 10 minutes.

title: banana pudding
directions: Mix pudding as directed. Add Eagle Brand milk and 9 ounces of Cool Whip to pudding.
Pour over wafers and bananas. Top with Cool Whip and vanilla wafer crumbs. Chill.

title: cherry salad
directions: Dissolve jello in hot water.
Add softened cream cheese and mix well.
Add marshmallows.
Place mixture in top of double boiler.
Stir until marshmallows and cream cheese are melted. Cool.
Add milk, pecans, pineapple and bananas.
Pour into salad mold; refrigerate until firm.

title: cheese ball
directions: Combine
first 3 ingredients.
Roll into ball.	Roll in chopped pecans and refrigerate.

title: cole slaw
directions: Chop cabbage and carrots very fine. Combine sugar, salt, pepper, milk, mayonnaise, buttermilk, vinegar and lemon juice; beat until smooth. Add cabbage and carrots.
Refrigerate 2 hours.

title: old fashion sweet potatoes
directions: Mix all ingredients together with mixer.
Pour into 9-inch shells (mixture will be loose).
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes. Makes 2 pies.

title: stuffed chicken breast
directions: Saute onions, mushrooms in butter or oil; do not drain. Add enough stuffing to onion/mushroom mixture to fill four chicken breast. Cover one side of each breast with mixture and roll or fold over. Fasten with toothpicks. Place in baking dish. Add cream of chicken soup. Sprinkle with paprika and parsley. Bake at 350 degrees for 1 hour.

title: applesauce cake
directions: With a pastry blender, blend together flour, brown sugar and softened margarine.
Reserve 1 cup of this mixture for topping. To the remainder, add applesauce, egg, salt, cinnamon and soda mixture.
Mix together and pour into a buttered 9 x 13-inch pan. Into the reserved cup of mixture, add coconut, chopped pecans and chocolate chips.
Sprinkle over cake and bake at 325° for 50 to 60 minutes.
Cool and cut into squares to serve.

title: shrimp or crawfish etouffee(for a crowd!)
directions: Saute chopped seasonings in 1 block butter.
Add lemon juice. Process Rotel in food processor.
Add Rotel, mushrooms and soup. Add 5 cups water.
Place peeled shrimp or crawfish in pot with 1 block butter and saute until firm.
Add to mixture and cook on medium heat.
Mix 1/2 cup cornstarch in 1 cup water.
Add to etouffee.
Cook 30 minutes more.
Serve hot over rice.

title: english tea cakes
directions: Measure 8 cups flour, keeping 1 cup of this separate because you won't need too much of the 8th cup.
Scald milk; remove from heat and add the shortening, sugar and salt.
Stir until shortening is melted and sugar is dissolved.
Pour milk mixture into mixing bowl and cool to lukewarm.
While this is cooling, dissolve yeast in lukewarm water and add a scant tablespoon sugar to it.* Add beaten eggs to milk mixture, then add the yeast mixture.
Blend well, then add the 7 cups flour, beating well after each addition so dough will be smooth.
You'll be able to use all 7 cups and possibly a little bit of the 8th, before you'll be able to knead the dough without having it stick.
Dough should be soft, so use just enough flour to keep it from sticking.
Knead raisins into dough and continue kneading for 6 to 8 minutes, until smooth and you can see air bubbles break on the surface.

title: frozen fruit salad
directions: Drain fruit cocktail.
Combine cream cheese and sugar.
Thin with small amount of the juice from cocktail.
Fold in fruit. Spread in ice cube tray and put into freezer for several hours. Cut into squares and serve on lettuce.
This keeps very well and may be made several days in advance.

title: pie dough #4(for 5 single crusts)
directions: Mix all together. Should be very pliable and easy to work with. Roll out to size of pie pan. This recipe will make 5 single crusts.
Also use for miniature (small cupcake tins) quiches, or other hors d'oeuvres.

title: strawberry trifle
directions: Beat cream cheese until soft; add 1 can condensed milk and fold in medium carton of Cool Whip.
Layer in large glass bowl: cake, sauce and strawberries.
Finish with sauce on top.
Decorate with strawberries.

title: ohio buckeyes
directions: Mix well the butter, powdered sugar and peanut butter; form into balls.
Chill.
Mix the chips and paraffin in double boiler. Dip balls in chocolate; leave enough not covered so it looks like a buckeye.

title: dirty cake
directions: Beat softened cream cheese with margarine.
Mix pudding with milk.
Add Cool Whip.
Put foil or wax paper on bottom of pan. Layer cookies and pudding.
(Last layer should be cookies.) Sprinkle with gummy worms if you wish.

title: cheese straws
directions: Allow cheese
and
oleo
to
warm
to room temperature. Sift flour, salt
and baking powder.
Mix with hands, the oleo and cheese.
Add
Tabasco
sauce, cayenne and flour; mix well. Press in cookie press
or
chill	and roll out thin and cut in shapes. Bake on
ungreased	cookie	sheet at 300° for 10 minutes.
Lower oven
to
and
cook
until
crisp (about 10 minutes).
Makes about 120 Cheese Straws.

title: perfect lemon cake
directions: Mix all ingredients. Bake at 350 degrees for 1 hour 10 minutes.

title: mexican wedding balls
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Mix thoroughly butter, sugar and vanilla. Work in flour, salt and nuts until dough holds together.
Shape dough into 1-inch balls and place on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake 10 to 12 minutes or until set, but not brown.
While warm, roll in powdered sugar.
Cool and roll in sugar again.

title: 1-2-3-4 cake
directions: Cream shortening, sugar and eggs.
Mix and sift flour, baking powder and salt.
Add alternately with milk.
Flavor as desired. You can use lemon.
Bake in loaf or angel food pan.
Bake at 380° to 400° for 20 to 45 minutes.

title: fried green tomatoes
directions: Slice tomatoes about 1/4-inch thick.
Beat egg in a small mixing bowl until light and fluffy.
Set aside.
Combine corn meal, seasoning and pepper on a sheet of aluminum foil or waxed paper.
Dip tomato slices in egg.
Coat with cornmeal mixture. Heat oil and margarine in a large skillet.
Fry slices until golden brown on both sides.
Remove from pan.
Drain on paper towels.
Serve immediately.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: zucchini casserole
directions: Cook squash and onion 5 minutes in preheated water; drain well. Combine soup and sour cream.
Fold into drained squash and onion. Melt oleo and combine with stuffing mix.
Spread 1/2 of stuffing in bottom of greased casserole dish.
Spoon in squash and onion, then top with rest of stuffing.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes. Serves 6.

title: cheese blintz
directions: Cream the cream cheese, egg, 1/8 cup sugar and vanilla (mixture will be a little lumpy).
Set aside.
Cut crust off bread and roll out to flatten.
Spread cream cheese mixture onto bread liberally and roll jelly roll style.
Roll each roll in the melted butter and then in a mixture of 1 cup sugar and 2 teaspoons cinnamon.
Place on cookie sheet and freeze.
When frozen, take out of freezer and slice into slices and refreeze.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes and serve hot (if thawed, bake for 10 minutes).

title: boston cream
directions: Cook the first 3 ingredients until soft ball (234° to 240°). Beat until creamy and thick.
Add nuts, if desired.
Pour out into buttered pan.
Stir until sugar dissolves, then no more. Cool; cut into squares.

title: peach bread
directions: Plunge peaches into boiling water to blanch for 45 seconds. Remove and run under cold water.
Skins will slip off easily. Slice into sections.
Place the peaches and 6 tablespoons sugar in blender.
Blend or process until pureed.
Combine flour with all dry ingredients, except remaining sugar.
Cream sugar and shortening.
Add eggs, one at a time, mixing well.
Add peach puree, nuts and vanilla, stir well.
Add dry ingredients, mix well. Spoon batter into 2 well-greased and floured loaf pans (9 x 5 x 3-inch).
Bake at 325° for 1 hour or until toothpick comes out clean.

title: peanut brittle(microwave)
directions: Combine sugar, corn syrup, salt and peanuts in glass baking dish; mix well.
Microwave on Medium-high for 8 minutes or until light brown, turning dish once.
Add butter and vanilla; mix well. Microwave for 2 1/2 minutes longer or to 300° on candy thermometer (hard crack stage).
Stir in soda.
Pour on buttered baking sheet.
Cool.
Break into pieces.
Store in airtight container.
Yield:
1 pound.

title: beef brisket
directions: Dampen roast slightly and sprinkle with meat tenderizer and lightly with seasoned salt and garlic salt.
In Pyrex dish, marinate in liquid smoke and Worcestershire sauce.
Cover with foil and refrigerate overnight.
Bake 5 to 6 hours at 250° for medium size roast.

title: french toast scramble
directions: Beat eggs with milk and salt.
Pour over bread cubes and toss. Heat margarine in skillet.
Add bread-egg mix.
Fry, turning occasionally, until browned.
Serve with butter and syrup.

title: easy scalloped potatoes
directions: Slice potatoes thin.
Arrange in layers in buttered casserole dish alternating with soup diluted with milk and ending with soup. Bake at 350° for about 45 minutes or until done.

title: cheese straws
directions: Grate cheese.
Combine all ingredients until it forms a ball. Cut into 3/8-inch strips after rolling out dough.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Cool on a rack.

title: fried chicken
directions: Toss raw chicken with vinegar.
Sprinkle generously with seasoned salt and pepper.
Place on colander on a plate and and let chill in refrigerator for at least 1 hour.
When ready to fry, heat oil (approximately 1-inch) in deep frying pan (you could use a deep fryer).
Do not let smoke.
Shake chicken in flour and shake off excess.
Carefully place in hot oil, skin side up, and fry over medium heat until golden brown.
Turn occasionally. Chicken is done when juices run clear.

title: icebox fruit cake
directions: Roll graham crackers out with a rolling pin.
Mix in pan with raisins and nuts.
Put the can of milk and marshmallows in double boiler.
Melt marshmallows and stir up with milk.
Pour this mixture into pan of ingredients.
Mix well.
Turn some out on powdered sugared doughboard with wax paper on it.
Work into a roll about 3 inches in diameter and about 7 or 8 inches long. Work and pat it with powdered sugar, then wrap each roll in separate wax paper.
Makes about 8 rolls.
Keep in refrigerator for a couple of days before using.

title: chocolate pudding dessert
directions: Bake in a 9 x 13-inch pan at 350°, stirring occasionally until slightly browned.
Reserve a few crumbs for top.
Press crust into pan.

title: slovak crepes
directions: Beat eggs until fluffy.
Add salt, sugar, milk and flour. Beat until smooth.
Drop pancake sized thin coatings of batter onto a hot, well-greased griddle.
Brown slowly on both sides. Spread evenly with marmalade or cottage cheese.
Roll up and drizzle with melted butter.
Serve warm.
Serves 6.

title: mom gordon's five bean bake
directions: Combine all beans in a large casserole.
Brown beef and 1 onion in skillet.
Add to casserole.
Chop the other onion raw into mixture.
Combine ketchup, brown sugar, water and Worcestershire sauce.
Mix into casserole.
Cover with bacon strips.
Bake, uncovered, in a 350° oven for 1 hour.

title: basil brie in pastry(yields: 12 servings)
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Grease cookie sheet.
Mix Parmesan cheese and basil.
Cut cheese round
horizontally into 2 layers.
Spread basil mixture evenly over cut surface.
Reassemble cheese round. Roll puff pastry into rectangle 15 x 9-inches on lightly floured surface.
Cut out 2 circles,
8 1/2 x 6-inches.
Place 8 1/2-inch circle on cookie sheet.
Place cheese in center.
Place 6-inch circle on top and press gently around edge and seal.
Cut decorations from remaining pastry, if desired.
Moisten with water to attach.
Bake about 25 minutes or until golden brown.
Cool on wire rack 30 minutes before serving.

title: curly noodles with gorgonzola and tomatoes(serves 4-6)
directions: Saute onion and garlic in oil.
Stir in tomato and basil. Cook 20 minutes until thick.

title: cole slaw
directions: Alternate cabbage and thinly sliced onions.
Top with 7/8 cup sugar.
Do not stir.
Bring to a boil the vinegar, salad oil and seasonings.
Pour over cabbage and let stand covered for 4 to 6 hours to cool, then refrigerate 24 hours.
Will keep for 2 to 3 weeks.

title: cream cheese-date ball
directions: Soften cream cheese at room temperature for awhile, then mix together with dates and form into a ball.
Serve with crackers of your choice.

title: better than homemade chicken noodle soup
directions: Boil chicken (you may not want to add salt to your water because the soup mix is plenty salty; add pepper, if desired). When chicken is done, remove from broth and debone.
Meanwhile, cook the soup mix and vegetables in the chicken broth about 10 minutes.
Add the chicken.
Serve with crackers or cornbread.

title: veg-all beef casserole
directions: Cook noodles until tender in 1 1/2-quarts boiling water to which 1 1/2 teaspoons salt have been added.
Lightly brown onion in oleo.
Add ground beef and cook slowly until brown.
Blend in flour; add cooked noodles.
Add Veg-All, including liquid, tomatoes, salt and pepper. Pour into a greased baking dish.
Bake 20 to 30 minutes.
May top with cheese.

title: sugar free strawberry pie
directions: Mix Jell-O, cornstarch, Equal, and water in a small saucepan. Cook over low heat until clear and thick. Let cool. Place strawberries in pie shell and pour mixture over berries. Let chill in refrigerator for at least 2 hours. Serve with cool whip on top.

title: chocolate pie
directions: This recipe makes 2 pies when using regular size pie shells.

title: lazey-dazey cake(hot milk)
directions: Combine flour, baking powder and salt.
In separate bowl, beat eggs; add sugar gradually, then add vanilla.
Heat milk and butter or margarine over medium heat until scalding.
Beat into egg mixture; add combined dry ingredients quickly.
Bake for approximately 30 minutes at 350° in greased and floured cake pans.

title: shrimp with garlic
directions: Prepare linguine according to package directions; drain.
Heat oil in large skillet over medium heat.
Add bell pepper and garlic; cook 6 minutes or just until tender.
Add shrimp, lemon juice, crushed red pepper, salt and black pepper; cook 10 minutes or until shrimp is pink and opaque.
Sprinkle with parsley.
Add shrimp mixture to cooked linguine in large bowl and toss well.
Serve immediately.

title: microwave no bake cookies
directions: Slowly melt butter in microwave on defrost.
Stir in cocoa until well mixed.
Add milk and sugar; mix well.
Do the following 4 times:
Set mixture in microwave; cook for 1 minute and 11 seconds, mixing well between each session.
Remove from microwave and stir in vanilla and peanut butter until the peanut butter is well blended.
Stir in oatmeal and allow the mixture to set 5 minutes.
Spoon onto wax paper and allow to harden for at least 1 hour (if you can!).

title: meat loaf
directions: In large bowl, mix thoroughly 1/2 cup of tomato soup, beef, onion soup mix, bread crumbs, celery and egg.

title: impossible bacon pie
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Grease a large pie plate.
Sprinkle bacon, cheese and onion in plate.
Beat remaining ingredients until smooth.
(Blender:
15 seconds; or 1 minute beaters.)
Pour into plate.
Bake until knife comes out clean.
Cool 5 minutes before cutting.

title: snickerdoodles
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Mix 1 1/2 cups of sugar, margarine, shortening and eggs in a large bowl.
Stir in flour, cream of tartar, baking soda and salt.
Shape dough by rounded teaspoonfuls into balls.
Mix 3 tablespoons sugar and the cinnamon; roll balls in mixture.
Place about 2 inches apart on ungreased cookie sheet. Bake until set, 8 to 10 minutes.
Immediately remove from cookie sheet.
Makes about 6 dozen cookies.

title: fluffy lemon pie
directions: Beat sugar, juice, egg yolks and lemon peel together.
Cook in double boiler until thick.
Cool.
Beat egg whites and fold into mixture.
Put into pie crust and bake at 350° until slightly brown.
Serve with whipped cream on top.

title: apple-raisin bread
directions: Sift flour, baking powder, soda, salt and spices.
Add sugar, eggs and applesauce.
Beat until well blended.
Stir in oats, raisins and oil.
Spoon into greased 9 x 5-inch loaf pan.
Bake 1 hour in 350° oven.
Remove from pan immediately and cool.
Slices better the second day.

title: chocolate chess pie
directions: Mix sugar and cocoa together thoroughly.
Add remaining ingredients and mix.
Pour into 9-inch unbaked pie shell.
Bake for 50 to 60 minutes.

title: candy peanuts
directions: Put all ingredients in frying pan.
Stir constantly. Don't burn.
Mixture will cook down and crystallize onto the nuts. As soon as liquid is gone, put nuts on greased cookie sheet.

title: vegetable salad
directions: Drain all vegetables and mix together.

title: hot chocolate mix
directions: Combine all ingredients together.
Blend approximately 2 cups at a time in blender until blended thoroughly.
Store in an airtight container.
Stir 2 to 3 heaping teaspoonfuls into a boiling cup of water.

title: bell pepper dip
directions: Drain pineapple, reserving juice.
Combine pineapple, cream cheese, onion, green pepper, pecans and seasoned salt in bowl; mix well.
Add enough pineapple juice to make of desired consistency. Serve with chips or crackers.
Yield:
96 servings.

title: quail or chicken casserole
directions: Boil quail or chicken until tender. Debone and break into pieces. Mix with other ingredients. Bake in covered dish at 350° for 1 hour.

title: lime salad
directions: Mix jello with boiling water.
Place in refrigerator until it begins to set, then add remaining ingredients.
Place in refrigerator and let it set until firm.
This makes a large salad. Serve on lettuce leaf with a scoop of Cool Whip and a cherry on top.
Can be used as a dessert this way.

title: mexicali surprise
directions: Combine softened cream cheese and taco seasoning.
Blend well. Fold in picante and optional veggies.
Give mixture a short squirt of lemon juice.
Mix well and chill.
Best if chilled at least 1 hour before serving.

title: red velvet cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar; add eggs.
Combine food coloring, cocoa and vanilla.
Stir into cream mixture.
Mix flour, salt and buttermilk.
Add to creamed mixture.
Combine soda and vinegar; ad to creamed mixture.
Mix well.
Pour into 3 (9-inch) round pans. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: sourdough starter
directions: Dissolve yeast in 1/2 cup warm water.
Put into large glass jar.
Add flour, sugar and remaining water.
Mix well.
Loosely cover.
Let stand in warm place for 3 to 5 days.
Feed every 7 days with 1/4 cup sugar, 1 cup milk, 1 cup flour.
Do not use until 24 hours after feeding or else before you feed it.
Always keep at least 1 cup to feed so it will stay live.

title: corn casserole
directions: In a pot, cook onion and bell pepper in oleo.
Cut fire off. Add all other ingredients.
Mix well and pour in buttered dish. Put grated cheese and paprika on top.
Bake at 350° for 30 or 35 minutes.

title: easy chocolate fudge
directions: In heavy saucepan, over low heat, melt chips with sweetened condensed milk and salt.
Remove from heat. Stir in nuts and vanilla. Spread evenly into foil lined 8 or 9-inch square pan. Chill 2 hours or until firm.
Turn fudge onto cutting board.
Peel off foil and cut into squares. Store loosely covered at room temperature.
Makes about 2 pounds.

title: fresh vegetable soup
directions: Combine all ingredients except spaghetti and Parmesan in a large soup kettle.
Bring to a boil; reduce heat and simmer, covered, for about 50 minutes.
Add the 1 cup of cooked pasta and simmer 10 minutes more.
Serve sprinkled with Parmesan cheese.

title: christmas punch
directions: Mix all
ingredients
except
ginger
ale and cherries. Chill. Add ginger ale and cherries when ready to serve.

title: rotel dip
directions: Combine all ingredients and heat until cheese is melted. Serve with tortilla chips or potato chips.
Can be made in microwave.

title: chicken and broccoli stroganoff
directions: Cook broccoli according to package directions.
Cook onions in butter.
Add flour, salt and pepper, stirring until smooth. Gradually add chicken broth, stirring well, until thick.
Stir in broccoli, chicken and mushrooms until heated through.
Stir in sour cream until heated through.
Serve over noodles.

title: six weeks bran muffins
directions: Mix dry ingredients well in bowl.
Add buttermilk, oil and eggs. Mix well again.
Store in refrigerator as long as 6 weeks. Fill muffin tins 2/3 full.
Bake at 400° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: chicken with lemon
directions: Sprinkle chicken pieces with pepper and salt to taste.
Melt butter (or oil) in a skillet and brown the chicken, skin side down.
When golden, turn the pieces and brown other side. Sprinkle with shallots and parsley.
Arrange lemon slices over the chicken.
Cover and cook 5 minutes.
Pour off fat and add wine. Cover and cook 15 minutes or until tender.
Serve with juices and fluffy rice.

title: stuffed shells primavera(serves 6)
directions: Simmer tomatoes, oil, basil, garlic, salt and pepper; cook 20 minutes.
Heat oven to 350°.
Saute broccoli, zucchini and mushrooms.
Season with nutmeg and pepper.
In large bowl, combine Ricotta cheese and vegetables; mix well.
Spoon 1 cup pasta sauce evenly on bottom of 13 x 9-inch baking dish.
Fill shells with vegetables and cheese mixture.
Arrange over sauce in dish.
Spoon remaining sauce over shells.
Bake, covered, 45 minutes and uncovered 10 minutes until bubbly and serve.

title: taco dip
directions: Soften the cream cheese and spread into glass pie dish. Spread warm chili on top of the cream cheese.
Top with grated Cheddar cheese, olives, tomatoes, peppers, sour cream of salsa. Serve with tortilla chips or crackers.

title: strawberry cheese pie
directions: Cream the cheese and sour cream together; spread over baked pie shell.
Prepare strawberries.
Place 1 cup of strawberries in a saucepan with the water and simmer for 5 minutes.
Combine sugar and cornstarch; mix with cooked berries, stirring constantly. Cook until syrup is clear and thick.
Add lemon juice and cool. Put rest of uncooked berries on top of cheese.
Pour cooked strawberries and syrup on top of strawberries.
Chill and serve with ice cream or Cool Whip.

title: mama's sketti
directions: Blend tomatoes with juice in blender; pour in a large pan. Add sugar and celery.
Turn on low heat and begin to simmer.

title: maple chiffon sponge cake
directions: Put cream of tartar in egg whites and beat until stiff.
Also add 1/2 cup sugar last.

title: bread pudding
directions: Scald milk; add bread that has been broken into crumbs.
Soak 5 minutes.
Add melted oleo, salt and sugar.
Mix and then add slightly beaten eggs, vanilla, spice and floured raisins.
Mix well.

title: barbecue sauce
directions: Combine all ingredients in saucepan over low heat.
Heat until well blended.
Good for chicken or pork.

title: macaroni and cheese
directions: Cook macaroni and onion until tender.
Stir in tablespoon of margarine and flour.
Cook on low heat and stir in milk.
Cook until bubbly and thick.
Add cheese and stir until melted.

title: strawberry marmalade
directions: Peel outer layer of oranges and lemons; set aside.
Remove the white membrane from fruit and discard.
Set the fruit aside.
Chop peels; place in a large saucepan.
Add water and baking soda; cover and bring to a boil.
Simmer for 10 minutes.
Meanwhile, section oranges and lemons, reserving juice.
Add fruit and juice to saucepan; cover and simmer for 20 minutes.
Add strawberries. Measure fruit; return 4 cups to the saucepan (if have more than 4 cups, discard any extra; if less, add water to equal 4 cups).
Add sugar and mix well.
Boil, uncovered, for 5 minutes.
Remove from the heat; stir in pectin.
Stir for 5 minutes to cool; skim off foam.
Pour into half-pint jars or freezer containers, leaving 1/4-inch headspace.
Adjust caps.
Process for 10 minutes in a boiling-water bath or store in the freezer.
Serve with toast or biscuits.
Yield:
about 10 half-pints.

title: chocolate-peanut crispies
directions: Combine sugar and corn syrup in a Dutch oven.
Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly, until sugar dissolves and mixture begins to boil.
Remove from heat and add peanut butter, stirring until smooth.
Gradually stir in cereal and peanuts. Stir in chocolate mini morsels.
Press mixture into a lightly greased 15 x 10 x 1-inch jelly roll pan.
Let cool and cut into 1 1/2-inch squares.
Yields 5 dozen.

title: italian taco salad
directions: In a medium skillet, cook ground meat until brown. Remove and drain. In a large bowl, combine ground beef, tortilla chips, Mozzarella cheese, Cheddar cheese, and salad greens. Toss with salad dressing and serve.

title: skillet dinner
directions: Brown ham and onion in bacon drippings in a skillet. Add uncooked spaghetti and tomatoes. Cook until done. Place cheese over the mix and let melt. When melted, mix together and serve right from the skillet.

title: grandma's spaghetti sauce
directions: Take pork and chuck roast and cut in large pieces. Brown in oil or salt side (which has been melted down) with salt, pepper, onion, garlic and parsley.
After thoroughly browned, add tomatoes and tomato paste.
Cook slowly for 3 or 4 hours.

title: ginger cookies
directions: Grease baking sheets lightly.
Start oven 10 minutes before baking at 375°.
Sift flour; measure and re-sift 4 times with next 3 ingredients.
Cream butter and shortening until smooth; stir in flavorings.
Then add sugar in 2 or 3 portions, creaming well. Beat in egg until fluffy, then stir in flour mixture and the cream alternately in 2 or 3 portions, mixing just until smooth after each.
Roll out on a floured pastry cloth about 3/16-inch thick. Cut out with a 2 1/2-inch cutter or decorated cutters.
Place on prepared sheet and bake 13 to 15 minutes.
Remove from pan to rack immediately.

title: fruit cake
directions: Cover raisins and soda with 3 cups boiling water.
Cover and let stand overnight.
The next day, mix raisins with all other ingredients.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour.
Reduce heat to 300° for 1/2 hour or until toothpick comes out clean.
This makes 2 tube pan cakes.

title: mexican barbecue gator
directions: Salt and pepper meat.
Work oil into meat and fry in hot skillet until done.
Drain off oil; add onion, scallion, garlic and saute until vegetables have cooked down, then add tomatoes. Cook until all liquid has evaporated and sauce has formed.
Serve on buns or on flour tortillas.

title: homemade dog biscuits
directions: Dissolve yeast in 1/4 cup warm water.
Stir in broth and molasses.
Add 1 cup all-purpose flour, the whole wheat flour, cracked wheat, cornmeal, dry milk, garlic and 2 teaspoons salt. Mix well.

title: chicken salad
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in boiling water.
Add salt and onion.
Chill until partially set.
Whip until foamy.
Add remaining ingredients and beat well.
Pour into mold and refrigerate.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Cream margarine and sugar well.
Beat eggs and add to first mixture.
Add bananas, milk and vanilla.
Add dry ingredients and mix well.
Pour into 2 medium size loaf pans.
Be sure to grease pans well.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes.

title: pickled squash
directions: Soak squash, peppers, onion and pimentos in ice water for 1 hour. Bring to boil vinegar, sugar and spices. Drain squash and other ingredients. Add in vinegar mixture and bring to a boil. Place in jars and seal.

title: mimosas
directions: Serves 15 people.
This nice to serve at a brunch.

title: blueberry pie
directions: Heat all ingredients together, except clear jel and the little amount of cold water.
Mix clear jel and cold water together.
Mix them; add to the blueberry mixture and continue cooking until thickened.
Pour into unbaked pie shell.
Add top sheet of dough and bake at 425° until done.

title: childs play cobbler
directions: In medium roasting pan, put 2 cans fruit pie filling.
Cover evenly with 2 boxes cake mix.
Dot with 1/2 cup soft margarine. Bake in oven at 375° for 30 minutes.

title: zucchini nut bread
directions: Stir together flour, cinnamon, nutmeg, soda, salt and baking powder.
Set aside.
Beat together sugar, oil, egg and zucchini. Add lemon peel; mix well.
Stir flour mixture into zucchini mixture.
Fold in nutmeats.

title: cherry crumb dessert
directions: In a mixing bowl, cut butter into cake mix as for pastry dough.
Set aside 1 cup.
Pat remaining crumbs onto the bottom and 1/2-inch up the sides of a greased 9 x 13 baking pan.
Spread pie filling over crust.
Combine walnuts with remaining crumb mixture; sprinkle over top.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.
Serve warm with whipped cream or ice cream.

title: reception orange balls
directions: Mix all ingredients, except coconut.
Roll into small balls. Roll in coconut.
Store in airtight container in refrigerator. Yields 100 balls.

title: hamburger casserole
directions: Fry the meat and onion in the margarine.
Cook the noodles until tender and drain.
Put in a 9 x 12-inch baking pan.
Add the peas and soup.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until brown.
Very good for a crowd.

title: sweet-sour sausage appetizer
directions: Cut sausage into appetizer size pieces, about 1/2-inch.
Brown sausage in medium skillet; drain on paper towel.
Drain pineapple; reserve juice.
Combine brown sugar and cornstarch in medium saucepan.
Add soy sauce, vinegar and reserved pineapple juice; stir until well blended.
Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly, until clear and thick.
Add pineapple, green pepper and sausage; heat thoroughly.

title: edwards mansion orange muffins
directions: Mix together all dry ingredients.
Add butter, shortening, eggs, milk and orange juice.
Mix thoroughly.
Spoon batter into greased muffin tins until 2/3 full.
Top each muffin with an orange section and slivered almonds, if desired.
Bake at 375° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Makes 3 dozen muffins.

title: east side salad
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients.
Blend mayonnaise, sugar and juice well.
Pour over salad and mix well.
Chill at least 4 hours.

title: peanut brittle
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients in heavy skillet and cook until peanuts stop popping.
Add soda; stir until foamy and brown in color.
Pour immediately into buttered pan.

title: hot cranapple cider
directions: Heat ingredients to boiling.
Reduce heat and simmer 15 to 20 minutes.
Strain.
Makes 25 (1/2 cup) servings.

title: strawberry delight
directions: Drain pineapple well.
Mix Cool Whip, strawberry Jell-O, cottage cheese and drained pineapple in a large bowl.
Cut strawberries in small chunks and fold into mixture carefully. Chill for about 1 hour.
Serve cold.

title: crab toastees
directions: Melt margarine and cheese.
Then add rest of ingredients. Spread on muffins, cut in quarters.
Freeze overnight on cookie sheet.
Bake in oven at 400° for about 15 to 20 minutes or until lightly browned.

title: baked date pudding
directions: Mix together and spread into 8x8-inch pan.
Top this mixture with:
2 cups boiling water mixed with 1 1/2 cups firmly packed brown sugar.
Pour over batter and bake at 350° for 30 minutes. Serve plain or with whipped cream.

title: orange sauce
directions: Bring ingredients to a boil.
Stir occasionally.
Serve over waffles.
Makes about 1 cup.

title: basic frosting for decorating
directions: Cream butter until very soft.
Gradually beat in some of the sugar.
Add the egg white and salt; mix well.
Then, slowly add remaining sugar while stirring.
Thin, if necessary, with cream. Divide into small portions; color each portion as desired.
This frosting is put through a pastry tube.

title: house dressing
directions: Dice onion and parsley.
Place onion and parsley in a large mixing bowl with all other ingredients.
Mix well.

title: maryland lady crab cakes
directions: Remove all cartilage from crabmeat.
In a bowl, mix bread crumbs, egg, mayonnaise and seasonings.
Add crabmeat and mix gently but thoroughly.
Shape into 6 to 8 cakes.
Pan-fry in small amount hot oil (350°) until browned on both sides.

title: ham rolls
directions: Whip together the first 5 ingredients.
Spread on rolls. Layer cheese and ham on top.
Wrap in foil and bake at 400° for 10 minutes.

title: crab-stuffed chicken breasts
directions: Place chicken breasts, one at a time, between 2 sheets of wax paper or plastic wrap.
With flat side of mallet, gently pound breasts until each is about 1/4-inch thick; set aside.
Melt butter in a wide frying pan over medium heat.
Add onions and mushrooms and cook, stirring until onions are soft.
Stir in flour and thyme and continue cooking and stirring until bubbly. Gradually pour in milk, wine and broth; cook, stirring until sauce boils and thickens.
Season to taste with salt and pepper.

title: cottage enchilada
directions: Drain chiles, remove seeds and cut into 12 strips.
Cook tortillas according to package directions.
Combine sour cream, cottage cheese, salt and pepper; reserve 1/2 c. of mixture.
Spoon remaining on 12 tortillas.
Top each with a strip of green chile and a strip of cheese.
Place seam side down in casserole dish. Mix 1/2 cup reserved mixture with enchilada sauce and pour over top.
Bake at 350 degrees for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: squash dressing
directions: Saute onion, pepper and celery in butter until tender.
Add to cornbread and stir well.
Stir in remaining ingredients, mixing well.
Pour into a greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish.
Bake at 400° for 50 minutes until lightly browned.

title: corn pudding
directions: Combine all ingredients and bake in 1 1/2-quart casserole dish at 325° for 1 hour or until firm in the middle.

title: 100% parmesan chicken(makes 6 servings)
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Spray a 15 x 10 x 1-inch baking pan with nonstick cooking spray.
Dip chicken in margarine; coat with combined remaining ingredients.
Place in prepared pan.
Bake for 20 to 25 minutes, or until tender.

title: green enchilada casserole
directions: Mix beef, bell pepper and chili powder together and cook until meat is brown; drain.
Add soup, water, enchilada sauce, chopped chilies and some cheese.
Mix well.
Layer tortillas, meat mixture and grated cheese until all is used.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.
This recipe will serve 10 to 12.

title: cheese ball
directions: Let cream cheese soften at room temperature. Mix other ingredients well to cream cheese. Shape into ball.
Serve with crackers.

title: frozen salad
directions: Mix together strawberries, pineapple, bananas and pecans. Beat cream cheese and sugar together. Blend with the first mixture. Fold in Cool Whip, then freeze. Remove from freezer 1 hour before serving.
Keeps well in freezer. Can be made several days ahead.
Also makes a good dessert.

title: quick appetizer pizza
directions: Spread each toasted muffin half with pizza sauce.
Top with 3 slices pepperoni and then with cheese.
Place 4 halves on microproof serving plate in circle.
Cook on 70 (Roast) for 3 to 4 minutes or until cheese is melted.
Let stand 3 minutes before serving.
Repeat with remaining muffins.

title: pumpkin chocolate chip muffins
directions: In large mixing bowl, combine the first eight (8) ingredients. In another bowl, combine the egg, egg substitute, pumpkin, applesauce and canola oil. Stir into dry ingredients just until moistened.

Stir in chocolate chips. Coat muffin tins with cooking spray. Fill 2/3 full. Bake at 400° for 18-22 minutes or until toothpick comes out clean. Cool in pan for 5 minutes until removing to wire rack. cool - Yield 2 dozen.

title: grilled vegetable salad
directions: Combine first 7 ingredients in a large bowl.
Set aside.
Cut remaining vegetables into large pieces and add to vinegar mixture, tossing to coat.
Let stand 30 minutes, stirring occasionally. Drain, reserving vinegar mixture.
Arrange in a grill basket. Cook, covered with grill lid, over medium-hot coals (350° to 400°) for 15 to 20 minutes, turning occasionally.
Return vegetables to reserved vinegar mixture, tossing gently.
Cover and refrigerate overnight.
Makes 6 cups.

title: pepsi cake
directions: Grease a Bundt pan and sprinkle the nuts over the bottom of the pan.
Mix the remaining ingredients together and beat for 2 minutes, then pour over the nuts.
Bake at 325° for 50 to 60 minutes.

title: ratatouille
directions: Sprinkle tomatoes with thyme.
Let stand. Saute remaining vegetables and garlic until barely tender. Add bay leaf.
Pour into nonstick casserole. Arrange tomato wedges on top.
Sprinkle with cheese and black pepper. Bake at 350°, covered, 30 minutes. Remove bay leaf before serving. Serves 8. Contains 48 calories per serving and 1 gram fat.

title: lemon knot cookies
directions: In large bowl, mix all ingredients together and knead.
Place on floured board.
Do not overknead.
Cut off piece and roll like rope.
Make a knot in dough.
Bake on an ungreased sheet for 10 to 12 minutes at 400°.

title: pumpkin cookies
directions: Mix in above order. Drop by spoonfuls onto cookie sheet. Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.

title: meat casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Pour into casserole dish.
Bake for 45 minutes at 350°.

title: italian style kale
directions: Boil kale; drain.
Place in pan with crushed tomatoes, olive oil, chopped onion, potatoes (halved), salt and pepper.
Cook until tender.

title: congo squares
directions: Mix and sift flour, baking powder and salt.
Melt shortening and add brown sugar.
Stir until well mixed.
Allow to cool slightly.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Add dry ingredients, then nuts and chocolate chips. Pour into greased pan about 9 x 13 x 2-inch.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Cut into 2 x 2-inch squares when almost cool. Yields 48 squares.

title: pizza casserole #1
directions: Cook linguini; drain and toss with butter.
Place in a 9 x 13 x 2-inch deep casserole dish.
Cook hamburg, onion and green pepper (optional); drain.
Sprinkle 1/2 of hamburg mixture over noodles. Spread 1 can of sauce over hamburg and onion mixture.
Layer 1/4 pound of pepperoni and 1/2 pound of Mozzarella cheese.
Repeat layers.
Bake at 325° for 45 minutes.
Cool and heat again to serve.

title: potato chip cookies
directions: Cream butter. Add sugar. Continue to beat. Add flour. Add vanilla. Add chips. Mix until all flour disappears. Drop onto ungreased cookie sheet. Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes. Watch cookies. Sprinkle with powdered sugar.

title: veggie dish
directions: Mix veggies together; pour boiling water over veggies to separate, then drain.
Melt 1/2 stick of butter with Velveeta cheese.
Mix cheese and butter with veggies.
Crush crackers. Melt remaining 1/2 stick of butter and mix with crushed crackers. Spread butter/cracker mixture over veggies in casserole dish. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: chocolate dessert
directions: Crust:
Combine margarine, flour and nuts.
Mix well.
Press into bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes. Cool.

title: pumpkin squares
directions: Mix until crumbly.
Sprinkle on top.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes or until done.
Serve with whipped topping.

title: heavenly garlic cheese biscuits(like red lobster)
directions: Preheat oven to 450°.
Line baking sheet with parchment or waxed paper; spray with nonstick cooking spray.
In a medium bowl, sift in flour, baking powder, soda and salt.
Add 2 tablespoons of margarine and blend with pastry cutter until mixture resembles coarse crumbs.
Add buttermilk and cheese; combine with fork, handling dough as little as possible.
Drop
by spoonfuls onto baking sheet.
Bake until lightly browned, 8 to 10 minutes.
While biscuits are baking, in small microwave bowl, add remaining tablespoon margarine; microwave on High until margarine is melted, 5 to 10 seconds.
Stir in garlic powder; set aside.
When biscuits are done, remove and brush with margarine mixture.

title: easy cobbler
directions: Melt margarine or butter in medium casserole dish.
Mix flour, sugar and milk thoroughly.
Pour over melted butter and add fruit.
Bake covered at 350° until golden brown, usually about 45 minutes.

title: snow ice cream
directions: Mix until blended, eat with spoon.

title: apple butter
directions: Mix ingredients and put in 350° oven for 2 hours.

title: sweet rolls(heritage recipe)
directions: In large mixer bowl combine yeast, 2 cups flour, sugar, and salt. Mix well, heat milk, water and butter until warm (120 - 130 degrees). Add to flour mixture.
add eggs, beat 3 minutes at medium speed.
Gradually stir in enough remaining flour to make a soft dough.
cover and let rise in warm place for 15 minutes.

title: strawberry kiwi trifle
directions: Prepare pudding according to package using 1 3/4 cups skim milk.
Let thicken.
Add yogurt and stir.
In a glass bowl, layer 1/3 of cake, 1/3 of pudding and 1/3 of fruit.
Repeat two more times.
Refrigerate.

title: nancy's macaroons
directions: Mix thoroughly all the ingredients; drop by teaspoonful on well-greased pan.
Bake for 10 minutes at 350°.
Remove from pan immediately.
Store in airtight container.

title: peanut butter cups
directions: Mix cracker
crumbs,
butter,
peanut butter and sugar. Form into balls.
Then dip in chocolate and drop on wax paper.

title: purple heart
directions: In a blender, blend yogurt and grape juice until creamy and smooth.
Pour into a tall glass.
Garnish with grape cluster. Serves one.

title: bread pudding(microwave)
directions: Line casserole dish with bread.
Sprinkle sugar and raisins over bread.
Melt butter with milk in microwave (High) for 4 minutes.
Add eggs, salt, vanilla and nutmeg to milk; pour over bread.
Bake for 35 minutes at 30% setting.

title: spiced carrot strips
directions: Place carrots in a saucepan; cover with water.
Cook until tender, about 8 to 10 minutes.
Drain.
Combine butter, sugar, salt and cinnamon; pour over carrots and toss to coat.
Serve immediately.
Yields 4 to 6 servings.

title: pasta chicken salad
directions: In medium bowl combine vinegar, olive oil, soy sauce, sesame oil, garlic powder, ginger, pepper, red pepper flakes and cilantro or parsley.
Dressing can be made ahead and refrigerated for up to one week.
Bring to room temperature before using.

title: cranberry jello salad
directions: Dissolve jello in 1 cup boiling water.
Let cool.
Using a food processor or grinder, grind cranberries, oranges (cut in 4ths or 8ths), and walnuts and mix together in large bowl.
Stir in crushed pineapple (including juice), sugar and marshmallows. Refrigerate until chilled or slightly firm.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Cream oleo; add sugar.
Beat in eggs one at a time.
Sift dry ingredients together.
Add alternately with buttermilk.
Add vanilla and bananas and nuts.
Bake in loaf pans (2 big ones or 4 small ones).
Bake at 350°.
When cake is done, cake will turn loose from side of pans.

title: mashed potato casserole
directions: Prepare mashed potatoes.
Set aside.
Melt butter and cheese. Add remaining ingredients. Pour mixture over mashed potatoes and mix.
Spoon into a greased casserole dish.
Bake uncovered at 400° for 45 minutes.

title: wassail
directions: Tie first 3 ingredients in cheesecloth.
Warm all together. Simmer 20 minutes.
Remove packet.
Float cored apple and lemon slices; add a dash of nutmeg.
Serve warm.

title: chocolate pie
directions: Separate eggs.
Beat yolks well.
Mix cocoa and sugar in saucepan.
Add hot water, butter and eggs.
Dissolve cornstarch in a little water.
Mix and stir.
Cook over medium heat until thick. Pour in cooked pastry pie shell.
Top with meringue.
Makes 2 (9-inch) pies.

title: chicken pot pie
directions: Combine potato soup, cream of chicken soup, Veg-All, chicken, milk and black pepper; spoon into 1 of the pie crusts.
Cover with other pie crust, crimp edges and brush top with egg.
Bake at 375° for 40 minutes.
Cool for 10 minutes.

title: thumbprint cookies
directions: Mix together thoroughly the margarine, brown sugar, egg yolk and vanilla.
Sift flour and salt into mixture; mix well.
Roll into 1-inch balls; dip in slightly beaten egg white.
Roll into nuts (optional).
Place about 1 inch apart on cookie sheet with parchment paper on it.
Bake at 375° for 5 minutes.
Remove from oven; quickly press thumb* gently on top of each cookie.
Return to oven and bake 8 minutes longer.
After cooled, place jelly or icing in the thumbprints.

title: washington candy (applets)
directions: Combine 1 cup applesauce with gelatin.
Add 1 1/2 cups applesauce to sugar.
Combine with gelatin mixture.
Cook 15 minutes at medium-high heat.
Remove from heat and add vanilla and nuts.
Pour into buttered pan.
Cool.
Cut and roll in powdered sugar.
Yields 4 dozen.

title: spinach dip
directions: Mix all ingredients together except bread or crackers and chill overnight.

Just before serving, hollow out center of bread. Place dip in the center and use bread that was removed from the center to dip out spinach dip. When bread is gone, use bowl and all or simply use crackers.

title: chocolate fondue
directions: In top of double boiler, melt chocolate bars.
Add vanilla. Add whipping cream to mixture.
Heat to dipping consistency.

title: old-fashioned banana pudding
directions: Mix flour, salt and half of sugar.
Put in top of double boiler and add milk slowly.
Stir constantly over boiling water until thickened.
Occasionally stir while cooking, 15 minutes more.
Beat egg yolks in bowl and stir into custard mixture, gradually.
Return to heat.
Stir constantly and cook 5 minutes more.
Remove from heat and add vanilla.
Line bottom of 1 1/2-quart casserole dish with cookies, bananas and custard mix.
Repeat twice, ending with custard on top.
Beat egg whites until stiff, not dry.
Slowly add 1/4 cup sugar.
Whip until stiff peaks are formed.
Spread on pudding and bake at 425° for 5 minutes or until delicately brown.

title: spiced tea mix
directions: Combine all ingredients and blend well.
Store in tightly covered jar.
For 1 serving, combine 1/2 cup each: water and apple juice in saucepan and bring just to a boil.
Pour over 1 well rounded teaspoon tea mix in mug and stir until dissolved.
Serve hot or over ice.

title: snickerdoodles
directions: Mix sugar, shortening and eggs.
Add dry ingredients.
Drop by spoonfuls on cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° until done.

title: winter warmer
directions: In a small saucepan, whisk together cocoa mix, coffee, cream and rum extract until cocoa is dissolved.
Heat through.
Top each serving with whipped topping and sprinkle with cinnamon if desired.

title: cashew chicken
directions: Repeat eggs and flour to coat chicken pieces twice.
Deep fry chicken in skillet until brown.

title: cheese 'n tuna crescents
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
In small bowl, combine tuna, onion, 1/2 cup shredded cheese (reserve 1/4 cup) and 5 tablespoons soup. Separate crescent dough into 8 triangles.
Place 2 tablespoons tuna mixture on wide end of each triangle.
Roll up.
Start at shortest side of each triangle and roll to opposite point.
In small saucepan, heat remaining soup, reserved cheese and milk until bubbly.
Pour 1/2 mixture into ungreased 8 to 9-inch square pan. Arrange filled crescents over soup.
Bake 25 to 30 minutes until golden brown.
Serve with remaining sauce.

title: vegetable casserole
directions: Combine Veg-All vegetables, mayonnaise, celery, salt, sugar, chicken soup, onions, water chestnuts and pepper.
Pour into a 9 x 12-inch baking dish.
Melt margarine in pan and crush Ritz crackers.
Add to melted butter.
Spread crumbs over vegetables and bake at 300° until bubbly.

title: modern sausage and potatoes
directions: Boil sliced potatoes until almost tender (about 5 minutes). Drain.
Heat oil in large, nonstick skillet; add sausage and potatoes.
Season to taste with onion salt and pepper.
Cook over medium heat, turning frequently until sausage is browned and potatoes are tender (about 20 minutes).
Normally serves 3 to 4, but 2 extremely hungry people can finish it off!

title: low-fat meat loaf
directions: Preheat the oven to 350°.
Combine all ingredients. Mix well. Press firmly into ungreased 8 1/2 x 4 1/2 x 2 1/2-inch loaf pan. Bake 50 minutes. Cool 5 minutes and slice.
Makes 8 servings.

title: pumpkin squares
directions: Mix in a large bowl eggs, sugar, oil and pumpkin until light and fluffy.
In a separate bowl, combine flour, baking powder, cinnamon, salt and baking soda.
Add pumpkin mixture and mix thoroughly.
Spread in an ungreased 15 x 10-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: pumpkin cookies
directions: Mix first 6 ingredients all together.
Mix all dry ingredients together.
Combine all ingredients together.
Drop by tablespoon. Bake at 350° for 10 to 11 minutes.

title: chocolate crispy cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Stir together flour, soda and salt; set aside.
Beat margarine and sugar until smooth.
Beat in eggs and vanilla.
Mix in flour mixture.
Gradually stir in cereal and semi-sweet morsels.
Drop by level tablespoon onto greased baking sheets.
Bake at 350° about 10 minutes or until lightly browned. Yield:
About 7 dozen, 2 1/2-inches in diameter.

title: apple fritters
directions: In a bowl, combine milk, egg, sugar and melted margarine. Add the orange juice, rind, chopped apples and vanilla.
Add flour, salt and baking powder.
Stir with a spoon until blended. Do not overmix!
Preheat oil in a skillet to 350°.
Drop off end of tablespoon into hot oil.
Fry to a golden brown.

title: cottage cheese roast
directions: Mix well and bake until brown at 350° for about 45 minutes in greased flat pan.

title: chicken nuggets
directions: In a shallow bowl, combine the first 6 ingredients. Place melted butter in another. Dip chicken in butter and roll in crumbs. Place on a greased baking sheet and bake uncovered at 400° for 15 to 20 minutes or until juices run clear. Serve with your favorite dipping sauce.

title: deluxe dog bones
directions: Cut livers into 1-inch chunks and add 1 cup water.
Bring to a boil, cover and simmer about 5 minutes until no longer pink.
Drain off liquid and add water to make 1 cup.
Put livers in food processor; break in eggs (including shells).
Puree, adding reserved liquid as needed to keep mixture moving.
Scrape into bowl; mix in remaining ingredients.
Turn onto board and knead until not sticky.
Clean board; dust with flour.
Dust ball of dough with flour.
Roll out 1/4-inch thick.
Shape bones by hand or use cookie cutter.
Bake 1 hour at 300°.
If not hard when cooled, return to oven and bake 10 minutes longer.
Store in airtight container or freeze.

title: good luck soup
directions: Cover beans with water and soak 3 hours or more.
Drain, add more water, ham and simmer 1 1/2 hours.
Saute all veggies, add to beans and simmer until beans are tender.
Add seasonings (you may need to adjust seasonings according to taste).
Serve with rice and/or corn bread.

title: easy skillet beef stroganoff
directions: Brown beef, onion and mushroom together in skillet until onion is tender.
Drain.
Add soup, cooked noodles, milk, sour cream and seasoning.
Cook in skillet until heated thoroughly.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Mix pumpkin, sugar, oil, water and eggs well, then set aside. Sift together the flour, salt, soda, cinnamon, nutmeg and cloves. Combine both mixtures; mix well.
Grease and flour a bread pan. Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours, or until bread springs back when lightly touched.

title: quiche
directions: Mix the first six ingredients.
Pour into baked pie shell. Preheat oven to 350°.
Bake for 45 minutes (knife inserted should come out clean).
Let stand for 15 minutes before serving.

title: "quick cheese" cake
directions: Mix cream cheese, vanilla and sugar at medium speed with electric mixer until well blended.
Add eggs; mix well.
Pour into prepared crust.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes or until center is firm.
Refrigerate 4 hours or overnight.
Top with fruit before serving.

title: potato casserole
directions: Heat oleo with soup and blend in onions, cheese and sour cream.
Stir in potatoes, pour into a buttered casserole dish. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: corn and cucumber salad
directions: Peel and thinly slice cucumbers and onion.
Drain corn, reserving liquid for other recipe uses.
Combine all other ingredients except parsley.
Pour over cucumbers, onion and corn in salad bowl.
Chill.
Toss and garnish with parsley sprigs.

title: mama's irish potato casserole
directions: Boil potatoes until tender (about 15 minutes).

Slice in medium slices and put 1 layer of potatoes in casserole dish. Sprinkle cheese over potatoes and pour cream of chicken soup over cheese, continue layers of potatoes, cheese and soup, as desired. Bake at 300° until lightly brown.
Serve hot.

title: breakfast casserole
directions: Melt butter in bottom of 9 x 13 pan. Place hash browns in dish. Mix eggs, milk, salt, pepper and onions together and pour over hash browns. Use any kind of browned meat and spread over top and slightly press in. Bake at 350° for 1 hour. Check with knife. Grate cheese over top and bake until melted.

title: marble cheesecake
directions: Preheat oven to 400 degrees.
In a bowl, mix flour, sugar, and salt.
Cut in butter until the mixture resembles coarse crumbs.
Stir in 2 tablespoons of melted chocolate.
Press mixture into the bottom of a 9-inch spring form pan.

title: hot dog casserole
directions: Cook hot dogs (boil).
Slice cooked hot dogs lengthwise. Place them in bottom of 13 x 9-inch pan.
Place uncooked green beans on top of hot dogs.
Place cheese over entire dish.
Spread mashed potato on top of entire dish.
Bake for 1/2 hour at 350°.

title: pasta salad
directions: Mix first 9 ingredients in jar and let set 24 hours.
Cook macaroni twirls as directed on package; drain and let cool.
Pour mixture in jar over macaroni and add onion, bell pepper, cucumber and pimento.
Let set additional 48 hours in refrigerator.
Will keep for several weeks.

title: chewy bread
directions: Mix all ingredients and bake in a greased 9 x 13-inch pan. Bake for 30 minutes at 350°.

title: old fashioned bread pudding
directions: Add sugar to beaten eggs.
Mix well.
Pour hot milk over eggs gradually, stirring constantly.
Add vanilla, salt and cinnamon. Arrange bread in a 9 x 5-inch pan.
Pour mixture over bread. Place in a larger pan 1/4 filled with hot water.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: broccoli and grape salad
directions: Mix together the broccoli, grapes, celery and onion.
Mix with salad before serving the almonds and bacon.
Mix together and add just before serving the mayonnaise, sugar and vinegar.

title: pizza casserole
directions: Brown hamburger, sausage and onion.
Drain grease.
Cook and drain noodles.
Mix all ingredients together except Mozzarella cheese.
Bake 45 to 55 minutes at 350°, covered with foil.
Add grated cheese on top and bake until cheese is melted and slightly browned variations.
Add sliced mushrooms.
Top with sliced green olives, black olives, green peppers, Cheddar cheese or other favorite pizza topping.

title: clam dip 2
directions: Mix together.
Bake at 350° until golden, about 45 minutes. Best with Ritz crackers.

title: bacon bites
directions: Soften butter and cheese spread at room temperature.
Mix together with mayonnaise and garlic powder.
Add bacon.
Spread on split English muffins.
Freeze 10 minutes if for immediate use. Broil until bubbly crisp.
Cut into squares.
May be made ahead and frozen.

title: potato casserole
directions: Mix together soup and milk.
In casserole layer potatoes, onion, pimentos and soup mixture.
Top with grated cheese and dot with pimento.
Bake at 350° covered for about 45 min and uncover last 15 minutes.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: lollipop cookies
directions: You will need 20 to 24 wooden sticks with rounded ends.

title: hershey's chocolate cake
directions: Heat oven to 350 degrees.
Grease and flour two 9 inch round pans.
Combine dry ingredients in large bowl.
Add eggs, milk, oil and vanilla.
Beat for two minutes on medium speed.
Stir in boiling water.
(Batter will be thin.)
Pour into pans.
Bake 30 - 35 minutes.
Cool 10 minutes.
Remove from pans to wire racks. Cool completely.
Frost.
10-12 servings.

title: overnight caramel french toast
directions: Combine sugar, butter and corn syrup in a small saucepan. Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly, about 5 minutes. Pour syrup mixture in a 9 x 13-inch cake pan. Cut bread in thick slices and place on top of syrup mixture. Combine eggs, milk, vanilla and salt. Beat well. Pour over bread slices. Cover and chill overnight. Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 40 to 50 minutes or until lightly browned. Serve with warm syrup.

title: sausage pinwheels
directions: Mix Bisquick and milk.
Divide dough in half and roll 1/8 inch thickness.
Spread 1/2 of sausage on dough.
After covering dough, begin at one end and roll up tightly.
Slice about 1/2 inch thick and bake at 375° for 20 to 25 minutes or until brown.
Repeat these steps for second roll.

title: easy chili
directions: Brown meat with chopped onion.
Add all dry ingredients, tomato sauce and beans.
Bring to boil.
Turn to low and simmer for one hour.

title: spaghetti with clams
directions: Melt butter in a skillet and add the olive oil, pepper, oregano, basil, garlic, clams and clam juice.
Simmer for 30 minutes.
Add salt to taste.
Cook the spaghetti, drain.
Put it into a bowl and add the clam sauce.
Toss with cheese and parsley.

title: chicken liver pate
directions: In large skillet melt 1/2 cup butter or margarine.
Add livers, onions, apple, thyme, salt and pepper.
Cook about 10 minutes until livers are grayish-brown and onions are soft.
Spoon mixture into food processor or blender container and process until smooth.
Cut remaining butter or margarine into 4 pieces.
Add with brandy to livers; process until smooth.
Spoon into 4 1/2 cup mold or tureen. Cover and chill.
(Can be made ahead to this point.)
Wrap well and freeze up to 1 month.
Thaw in refrigerator about 24 hours.
I separate the boiled eggs for the garnish.
Chopped yellows around outside, chopped whites around outside of yellow.

title: flame red cake
directions: Cream butter, sugar and eggs.
Make paste.
Add cocoa and food coloring.
Mix in salt, flour and soda and fold in vanilla, buttermilk and vinegar.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: cheese tartlets
directions: Cut bread slices into circles.
Place into greased pan and press dough.
Fill with cheese and ham.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.

title: green beans and potatoes
directions: Cover salt pork with water and cook for 20 minutes.
Break beans into 1/2-inch pieces and add to pot.
Cover with water. Cook for 1 1/2 hours.
Add more water, if necessary, to keep beans covered.
Add potatoes and any water necessary to cover vegetables.
Cook another 30 minutes or until potatoes are done. Serve with ham and corn bread.

title: spaghetti pie
directions: In microwave-safe 10-inch quiche dish, combine zucchini, onion, garlic and basil.
Cover with plastic wrap; vent.
Cook on High 3 minutes.

Add remaining ingredients, 1/2 teaspoon salt and 1/8 teaspoon pepper; mix well. Evenly spread mixture in dish. Cook, uncovered, on High 6 minutes, rotating dish every 2 minutes and with fork, stirring cooked egg around side of dish with mixture in center.
Cook on Medium 12 minutes or until just set in center.
Let stand on counter 5 minutes before serving.
Makes 8 servings.

title: spinach-cheese chicken
directions: Boil chicken in water with bouillon.
Cook spinach according to package.
Place chicken in baking pan. Cut to lay flat.
Scoop spinach on top of chicken.
Season with salt, pepper and garlic powder.
Top with a slice of your favorite cheese.
Broil until cheese melts.

title: taco soup
directions: Brown ground beef with chilies and onion.
Drain.
In crock-pot, put meat and rest of ingredients.
Stir well.
Cook on medium-low overnight or high for 3 to 4 hours.
Freezes great. Serves 6 to 8.

title: mostaccioli
directions: Brown ground beef; pour off grease.
Saute vegetables for 5 minutes.
Add soup and tomatoes.
Heat until it comes to a boil. Cook noodles according to package and drain.
Mix all ingredients together well.
Put into casseroles and bake, covered, in 350° oven for 35 to 45 minutes.

title: calamity's classic
directions: Make reservations and Enjoy!

title: barbecue sauce for ribs
directions: Mix all ingredients until blended.
Parbroil ribs in pan. Place ribs in pan and pour sauce over them.
Bake at 350° for 1 to 1 1/2 hours.

title: tomato fried spaghetti squash
directions: Heat oil in a large skillet or wok.
Saute onion, green pepper and garlic.
Stir in eggs and scramble/fry until eggs are set. Stir in spaghetti squash.
Stir in tomato paste, water or bouillon, basil and parsley.
Simmer a few minutes.
Serve hot.

title: struffoli(honey clusters)
directions: Sift flour.
Make a well in center and break eggs into it. Add salt and knead until smooth.
Roll dough out on lightly floured board until 1/4-inch thick.
Cut into 1/2-inch strips and cut strips into tiny pieces 1/2-inch long.
With the palm of the hands, shape these tiny pieces into balls the size of a filbert. Heat oil to 350° and drop balls in 3 at a time.
Fry until lightly browned, turning them constantly with a wooden spoon.
Remove balls and drain them.

title: coconut cream pie
directions: Mix cornstarch, 2/3 cup sugar and salt in double boiler top. Slowly stir in milk.
Cook over boiling water, stirring constantly, until thick enough to mound slightly when dropped from spoon.
Cover; cook 10 minutes longer, stirring occasionally. Stir a little hot mixture into beaten egg yolks, then stir all into remaining hot mixture.
Cook for 2 minutes, stirring constantly.
Remove from boiling water.
Stir in vanilla and 3/4 cup coconut.
Cool to room temperature.
Turn into pastry shell.

title: pork chop and apple skillet
directions: Brown pork chops in frying pan in a little oil.
Take pork chops out of pan and set aside.
Add apples and onions to pan; brown.
Add pork chops.
Add all sauce mixture.
Simmer 1 hour on stove.
May serve with wide noodles or rice.

title: grilled spareribs
directions: Wrap ribs in double thickness of foil.
Bake for 1 1/2 hours in a 350° oven.
Unwrap and drain.
Combine remaining ingredients and pour over ribs.
Marinate at room temperature for 1 hour, or refrigerate 2 hours.
Lay ribs on grill for 30 minutes, 4 inches above coals.
Turn often and baste with sauce.

title: chattanooga, tennessee apple cake
directions: Let apples and sugar stand for 15 or 20 minutes.
Beat oil and eggs well.
Add to apples and blend.
Mix all ingredients well. Put into a greased and floured Bundt pan or a 9 x 12-inch pan. Bake for 1 hour at 350°.
Check center with a toothpick.

title: chicken and dumplings
directions: Boil hen until tender; set aside. Mix 1 cup flour with 1 egg to a dough consistency. Knead well. Roll very thin and cut into strips. Cut chicken into chunks or pieces. As the broth boils cut and

add strips of dough. Do not stir. Keep separated with fork. Add the remaining two eggs after boiling by chipping small into the mixture to add color. This makes a generous portion. If you see that more dough is needed, mix another eggs and flour and use the same procedure.

title: romano green bean pasta bake
directions: Cook pasta; drain.
In skillet, cook onion, mushrooms and basil in oil until onion is tender.
Add tomatoes and tomato sauce and cook, uncovered, over medium-high heat.
Stir in pasta, green beans and 1/2 cup cheese.
Season with salt and pepper.
Pour into baking dish (8 x 12-inch) and top with remaining cheese.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes or until heated through.

title: ann's tuna burgers
directions: A traditional barbecue delicacy is lamb testicles. Place the meat immediately in brine for about 30 minutes. Remove thread and cut. Wash in clean water.
Place in boiling water and boil until the lamb's testicles are "dry."
Add butter, salt and freshly ground black pepper. Stir-fry in a saucepan until brown and crisp. The dish can be served cold.

title: macaroni salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Chill and serve.

title: dirt cake(made in a flowerpot)
directions: Blend cookies in blender (makes crumbs).
Put small amount in bottom of flowerpot.
Mix the margarine, Cool Whip, cream cheese and powdered sugar.
Mix the pudding, milk and vanilla together. Mix the two mixtures together.
Spread in alternate layers with cookie crumbs until pot is full, ending with crumbs.
Chill.

title: elvira's tomatoes stuffed with corn
directions: Scoop
out
and
drain
tomatoes.
Reserve
pulp, saute onions and
peppers
in butter until tender. Add tomato pulp, bread crumbs
and seasoning.
Cook until very thick. Add corn that has been cooked and cut from the cob.
Sprinkle inside of each tomato with a pinch of salt and stuff with corn mixture. Cover tops
with bread crumbs, dot with bits of butter.
Bake for 15 to 20 minutes or until brown. Serves 6.

title: wacky-wacky chocolate cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In 9 x 13-inch cake pan, stir all ingredients with a fork until well mixed.
Bake 30 minutes.
Top with favorite icing.
Eat!

title: baked beans
directions: Fry bacon and drain.
In bacon drippings, saute onion, celery and green pepper.
Add to the pork and beans.
Stir in ketchup, molasses, Tabasco and brown sugar, mixing well.
Top with the fried bacon, crumbled.
Bake at 375° for 30 minutes.

title: impossible pumpkin pie
directions: Mix all in a blender. Pour into 9-inch pie pan.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes until done.

title: pie crust
directions: Blend shortening with first 3 ingredients.
Mix all ingredients and work dough on floured board.
Makes 4 crusts.

title: sourdough pancakes
directions: Combine all ingredients and mix thoroughly.
Using 1/4 cup batter for each pancake, pour onto a well-greased griddle.
Yields 10 to 12 pancakes.

title: spinach casserole
directions: Saute onion and garlic in margarine.
Add drained spinach. Remove from heat.
Add cottage cheese and nutmeg.
Pour into baking dish that has been sprayed with no stick cooking spray and bake in 375° oven for 20 to 25 minutes until cottage cheese is melted.

title: peaches and cream shake
directions: Place peaches and 1/4 cup milk in a blender. Blend until smooth.
Spoon in ice cream.
Blend until softened. Add 3/4 cup milk; mix until blended. Sweeten with sugar, if desired.
Pour into tall glasses.

title: peanut crunch clusters
directions: In a small saucepan, combine carob powder and cornstarch, mixing well.
Add about 2 tablespoons of the milk and stir until mixture is very smooth.
Gradually add remaining milk, one tablespoon at a time, mixing well after each addition.
Stir in honey or maple syrup.
Bring mixture to a boil over medium-low heat, stirring constantly.
Continue to cook, stirring, for 1 minute.
Remove from heat and stir in vanilla extract.
Spoon ice milk or ice cream into serving bowls and top with hot sauce. Makes 4 servings (2 tablespoons of sauce for each serving). Excellent.

title: yellow rice
directions: Add spices to water and rice.
Cook according to directions. Salt and pepper to taste.

title: coronado casserole
directions: Brown ground beef in skillet.
Drain off excess fat.
Add onion and cook until tender.
Blend in tomatoes, tomato paste, salt and chili powder.
Spread half of meat mixture in 1-quart casserole dish.
Arrange half of cheese slices over meat mixture. Top with remaining meat mixture.

title: pea soup
directions: Simmer all ingredients except cream and butter for 20 minutes. Pour in blender and process until smooth.
Put back into pan. Warm and add cream and butter.
Serve with croutons if you like.

title: ashley's drink
directions: Whirl all ingredients in blender.
Serve over crushed ice. Garnish with slices of lemon or lime in each glass.
Yields 4 servings.

title: seafoam salad
directions: Heat 1 cup pear juice; dissolve Jell-O.
Set aside to cool. Moisten cheese with 8 tablespoons pear juice.
Mash pears and add cream cheese, then add to cooled Jell-O.
Fold in whipped cream; add cherries that have been cut in quarters.
Pour in 11 x 7-inch pan.

title: hot fudge sauce
directions: In heavy saucepan, stir cream and butter and melt to barely a boil; stir in sugar until dissolved.
Reduce heat; with wire whisk, stir in salt and cocoa until smooth.
Serve over ice cream and store in glass jar.
Reheat 1 to 2 minutes.

title: copper pennies
directions: Scrape and slice carrots in rounds and cook in salted water until tender.
Combine ingredients and marinate for 24 hours. Serve cold.

title: spaghetti with american cheese and milk
directions: Cook spaghetti.
As it cooks, make a sauce of the other ingredients.
Sauce should be fairly thick, but thin enough to coat spaghetti.
So add cheese and milk until this works.
Drain spaghetti and then dump into sauce.
Serve hot.
(Use a pretty large pot to make the sauce.)

title: cauliflower salad
directions: Fry bacon and crumble.
Tear lettuce and layer on bottom dish. Layer bacon on top of lettuce then onion, cauliflower broken in bits, mayonnaise and cheese.
Can be made the night before.
Toss just before serving.

title: cucumber-cottage cheese ring
directions: Dissolve gelatin in hot water.
Cool.
Add rest of ingredients.
Pour into ring mold and chill until firm.
Makes 12 to 16 servings.

title: hash(two and one-half gallons)
directions: Boil pork and beef (save broth).
Grind up meat.
Add other ingredients.
Simmer all day adding broth as needed.

title: chocolate gravy
directions: Mix the sugar, flour, cocoa and salt and stir in the milk. This makes a thick paste.
Add vanilla.
Stir in enough hot water to make thin sauce.
Bring water to a boil; add cocoa and mix. Cook, stirring until thick.
Serve at once.

title: chocolate chess pie
directions: Melt butter.
In separate bowl, mix sugar, flour and cocoa. Add butter.
Stir to mix.
Add eggs, one at a time, stirring after each one.
Add milk and vanilla.
Pour into pie shell; bake at 350° for approximately 40 minutes until set.
May add chopped pecans, if desired.

title: my favorite punch
directions: Boil water and sugar.
Add all together plus 10 cups water. Before serving, add 1 quart ginger ale.

title: baked beans
directions: Brown ground beef and onion; then drain.
Add beans and mix well.
Mix all other ingredients together and pour over beef and bean mixture.
Stir and put into an ovenproof bowl.
Bake for 2 hours at 300°.

title: easy apple cake
directions: Place apples in a 9-inch round, well buttered baking dish. Sprinkle 1/2 cup sugar and cinnamon over the apples. Next, sprinkle the walnuts over the apples. In a mixing bowl, sift together the flour, 3/4 cup sugar, baking powder and salt.
Set it aside. In another bowl, combine the egg, water, evaporated milk and melted butter. Add the egg mixture all at once to the flour mixture.
Mix until smooth.
Pour the batter over the apples. Bake approximately an hour (or until golden brown) in a 325° oven. A great breakfast cake. Can be served warm or cool. Kids love it.

title: chicken and dumplings
directions: Put water or broth, butter and milk in large pot and heat to simmering; roll biscuits in flour and cut into strips and drop into simmering mixture one at a time.
Add flour for thickness, salt and pepper for taste.
Add chicken; heat through.

title: citrus cooler punch
directions: Combine all ingredients into large punch bowl. Let ice cream melt a little before serving.

title: mexican dip
directions: Mix together and refrigerate overnight the cream cheese, sour cream and taco seasoning.
(I spread it in the bottom of a 9 x 13-inch pan.)
Just before serving, spread taco sauce over refrigerated mixture, then layer with shredded lettuce, shredded cheese and cut up tomatoes and olives.
Serve with nachos.

title: nut balls
directions: Cream oleo; add sugar, vanilla and water.
Mix well.
Add flour and salt; mix well.
Add crushed nuts.
Shape into bite size balls.
Bake on ungreased cookie sheet for 8 to 10 minutes at 325°.
When cool, roll in powdered sugar.

title: mexican casserole
directions: Brown ground beef; drain fat.
Layer corn chips, ground beef, green chilies and mushroom soup mixture in casserole dish.
Repeat until all is used.
Pour sauce over top and bake at 350° until bubbly.
Top with Cheddar cheese.

title: dressing for banana croquettes
directions: Be sure to add in order and beat well after each item. Especially the vinegar.
Cook until thick, stirring constantly. Cool well before using.

title: potato pancakes
directions: Combine potatoes with egg and vegetables in bowl.
Season to taste.
Make patties and pat with flour.
Brown slowly in butter. Use heavy skillet.

title: cottage cheese salad
directions: Dissolve jello in hot water; let cool.
Mix all other ingredients together.
Add to jello and chill.

title: creamy rice pudding
directions: Heat milk first.
Cook rice in milk slowly.
In second pan, heat egg yolks, half and half and sugar.
Mix the mixtures together.
Cook about another 15 minutes.
Add vanilla and cinnamon.

title: mixed seafood casserole
directions: Mix
together
all
ingredients.
Place in baking dish. Top with buttered fresh bread crumbs and 1/2 cup chopped nuts. Bake for 20 minutes or until bubbly at 375°.

title: hot spicy wings
directions: Boil wing joints for 5 to 10 minutes.
Drain well.
Crush garlic cloves and add chopped onion, green onions and carrots. Stir well.
Add 1/2 cup soy sauce, sesame seed, sesame oil and red pepper.
Cook for approximately 5 to 10 minutes, stirring occasionally.

title: million dollar pie
directions: Mix all ingredients and divide into two graham cracker crusts.

title: good guacamole
directions: Spoon avocado out of peel.
In a bowl mash avocado until smooth.
Add onions and tomatoes and lemon juice.
Mix well.
Add garlic salt and Season-All to taste.
Mix well and refrigerate for at least 1 hour.

title: orange creamsicle cake
directions: Prepare cake mix.
Bake in a cookie sheet, 16 x 11-inch.
When completely cold, poke full of holes with a fork.
Dissolve Jell-O in hot and cold water; mix.
Pour Jell-O slowly over cake. Refrigerate for 3 to 4 hours.

title: party oyster crackers
directions: Mix oil and spices together in a cup.
Pour over crackers, while stirring.
Bake 10 minutes in preheated 350° oven.

title: skillet cabbage
directions: Saute onion, garlic and ginger in butter in a large skillet 2 minutes.
Add cabbage and carrot; stir-fry over medium heat about 5 minutes or until vegetables are crisp-tender.
Stir in soy sauce, pepper and paprika.

title: beijng biscuits
directions: Chop onions.
Beat 1/2 egg.
Mix the chicken with egg and onion.
Add cornstarch and salt.
Flatten biscuit with hands.
Put 1 teaspoon chicken mix in center.
Put sesame seed on top of biscuits.
Turn oven to 375°.
Add 4 tablespoons oil.
Put biscuits into oil.
Cook 10 minutes.
Remove from oven.
Turn biscuits over.
Add remaining 4 tablespoons vegetable oil.
Cook 10 minutes more.

title: cabbage and beef soup
directions: In a Dutch oven, brown beef.
Add all remaining ingredients. Bring to a boil.
Reduce heat and simmer, covered, for 1 hour. Ground beef can be substituted for 1 (12 oz.) can corned beef.

title: super apple sandwich
directions: Wash apple.
Mix dry milk and peanut butter in small bowl. Slice apple into 4 sections, remove core.
Spread mixture over 1 slice, top with 1 more apple slice.

title: rice pudding
directions: In medium saucepan, bring milk, cinnamon, brown sugar and salt to boiling.
Add some raisins now, if desired.
Stir in rice. Reduce heat to low, cover and simmer for 35 to 45 minutes, or until rice is tender.
Stir occasionally.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Combine first 7 ingredients and pour over remaining ingredients.
Toss and eat.

title: sausage and egg casserole
directions: Remove crusts from bread.
Spread butter on bread slices.
Put butter side down, in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Cook sausage.
Crumble and drain well.
Spoon sausage over bread.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Mix eggs, half and half and salt.
Pour over cheese.
Cover and store in refrigerator overnight.
Remove 15 minutes before baking.
Bake for 45 minutes at 350° or until firm.

title: strawberry pie
directions: Mix all ingredients together and pour into a vanilla wafer or graham cracker crust.
Chill.
Strawberries may be added to top if desired.

title: simple potato salad
directions: Mix together potatoes, onion, celery seed and dill weed. Sprinkle with salt and pepper.
In a separate bowl, blend together mayonnaise, sugar and mustard.
Pour over potatoes.
Refrigerate one hour before serving.

title: cutout sugar cookies
directions: Mix and chill; roll out and cut with cookie cutter.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
Take out while still soft.

title: mustard potatoes
directions: Put potatoes in greased slow cooker.
Saute onion in butter in skillet.
Add mustard, salt, pepper, milk and cheese.
Pour over potatoes.
Cover and cook on low for 3 hours.

title: snow pie
directions: Blend the cornstarch with the first 1/4 cup sugar and salt. Pour the hot milk over this, stirring constantly, until thick. Add 1 tablespoon butter and the vanilla.
Beat egg whites until they are stiff.
Add the last 1/4 cup of sugar and beat until points form.
Fold into cream mixture while it is hot.
