Cool slightly, then heap into a 9-inch baked pie shell.
Cover with a layer of shredded coconut.
Top with whipped cream or meringue. Cool thoroughly before cutting.

title: pretzel salad(dessert)
directions: Mix pretzels and butter; press mixture into 9 x 13-inch dish. Bake at 400° for 10 minutes.
Mix cream cheese and sugar; spread over pretzel bottom.
Spread Cool Whip over cream cheese.
Put in refrigerator 1/2 hour.

title: chicken enchiladas
directions: Brown onion in butter, combine soups, broth, chicken pieces and chilies.
Mix well.

title: vanilla ice cream
directions: Mix all ingredients together except milk.
Pour into freezer. Add enough milk to bring mixture to fill line; freeze.
Remove dasher.

title: easy spaghetti bake
directions: Combine spaghetti, eggs, Parmesan cheese and parsley in mixing bowl; mix lightly.
Lightly grease baking dish.
Place half of spaghetti mixture in baking dish; top with half Mozzarella cheese. Repeat layers.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes until thoroughly heated.

title: applesauce cake
directions: Stir soda and shortening into warm applesauce.
Mix sugar, shortening and applesauce while warm.
Add raisins, walnuts, flour, cinnamon and cloves; mix well.
Bake 1 hour in slow oven (325°).

title: favorite potato casserole
directions: Fry bacon and cut up.
Mix mayonnaise, cheese, milk, olives and bacon.
Layer potatoes, then cheese mixture in 2-quart casserole (use 1-quart casserole for 1/2 recipe).
Bake at 250° for 35 to 40 minutes.
Whole recipe serves 6 to 8.

title: tea cakes #1
directions: Cream together	shortening and sugar; add eggs and beat well. Add baking	soda
(dissolved in vinegar) and salt.	Add flour a little at
a
time	to make a stiff batter.
Roll thin and	cut. Place
on
a greased cookie sheet and bake 10 to 12 minutes at 350°.

title: zucchini pancakes
directions: Mix all together.
Add more cheese if desired.

title: salsa
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Refrigerate several hours before serving with your favorite tortilla chips.
The longer it sits, the hotter it gets!

title: sugar-free apple pie
directions: Heat apple juice.
Thicken with cornstarch.
Add cinnamon, nutmeg and oleo.
Pour over apples.
Toss apples to coat well. Pour in unbaked pie crust.
Top with top crust.
Bake at 400° for 1 hour.

title: squash casserole
directions: Cook squash, carrots and onions until tender and water cooks out.
Turn off heat and add soup, pimentos and sour cream and mix. Melt margarine and mix with stuffing.
Alternate layers of stuffing and squash mixture, starting with stuffing on bottom of casserole.
Cook at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: country style vanilla ice cream
directions: In a large mixing bowl, beat eggs until foamy.
Gradually add sugar; beat until thickened.
Add milk, cream, vanilla and salt. Mix thoroughly.
Chill.
Make in an ice cream freezer.
Yield:
3 quarts.

title: baked chop suey
directions: Brown meat with onion.
Add rest of ingredients, except noodles.
Put in casserole dish. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Mix 3/4 of noodles in casserole.
Spread rest over top.
Bake 15 minutes longer.

title: short order barbecue sauce
directions: Combine all ingredients in saucepan.
Bring to a boil; reduce heat and simmer uncovered for 15 minutes.
Makes about 3 cups.

title: chocolate chocolate chip cake
directions: Place all ingredients in bowl.
Mix by hand until well blended.
Spray 12-cup tube pan (or Bundt pan) with nonstick cooking spray (Pam, etc.).
Pour batter into prepared pan.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 55 minutes or until done.
Do not overbake. Cool in pan.
Remove and continue to cool on rack.
After cooling, sprinkle with confectioners sugar.

title: broccoli cornbread
directions: Mix well and add 1 box (8 1/2 oz.)
Jiffy cornbread muffin mix and a dash of Tabasco.
Heat large skillet very hot with cooking oil.
Cook 25 to 30 minutes at 400° or until golden brown.
Bake thin; when cool, cut into small squares.
Bake in 2 skillets or 2 pans.

title: tangy and easy shrimp spread
directions: Mix cream cheese, sour cream, lemon juice and dressing mix; beat until smooth.
Fold in shrimp.
Chill.
Serve with crackers or vegetables.

title: surprise meatballs
directions: Combine sour cream, onion and 1 teaspoon of the salt.
In a frying pan, cook bacon until crisp and then cut into 1/4-inch pieces.
Discard all but 1 teaspoon of fat.
Cut each olive in quarters.
Shape Blue cheese into 6 balls.
Combine beef, 1/4 teaspoon salt and 1/4 teaspoon of pepper.
Shape into 20 balls. Make an indentation with your thumb in each ball and put in 1 teaspoon bacon or 1/4 olive or 1 ball of cheese.
Press beef around filling to seal.
Saute meatballs in bacon fat over medium heat until brown, 10 to 15 minutes.
Drain and serve with sour cream.

title: cheese balls
directions: Mix well and roll into a ball.
Roll and cover with pecans.

title: hot artichoke dip
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Combine all ingredients, except paprika and mix gently.
Spread into 1 1/2-quart baking dish.
Sprinkle with paprika.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Serve as a dip with crackers, chips or raw vegetables.

title: salisbury steak
directions: Lightly mix beef, half and half, onion, salt and pepper. Shape into oval patties.
Heat butter, add mushrooms and cook until lightly browned.
Remove from pan.
Add about 2 tablespoons more butter to skillet.
Add patties and cook until brown on both sides.
Remove patties.
Add flour to drippings.
(If necessary, add more butter.)
Cook until thickened, add beef broth and cooking wine.
Continue cooking until thick.
Return patties and mushrooms to gravy, simmer until meat has finished cooking.

title: strawberry cake
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Pour into greased and floured Bundt pan.
Bake at 350° for approximately 40 to 50 minutes.
Glaze with icing when hot.

title: candied sweet potatoes a la orange
directions: Set peeled
potatoes
in a baking pan.
Combine all the ingredients and pour over the potatoes.
Add the sliced orange that is cut
into
half
moons.
According
to
the age of the potatoes,
cooking time will vary.
After about three-fourth's hour, take out the orange slices.
Potatoes generally take one and one half hour to fully cook.
Baste frequently in the 350° oven. The syrup will caramelize potatoes.
Serve with candied orange as a garnish on top of potatoes.

title: oatmeal chunk chocolate cookies
directions: Combine brown sugar, sugar and eggs.
Add ground oatmeal and vanilla.
Add flour with baking soda and baking powder.
Add the remainder of the ingredients.
Roll into balls and place 8-inches apart on cookie sheet.
Bake 8 minutes at 375°.
Makes 5 dozen cookies.

title: beef and burgundy
directions: In 4-quart heavy kettle, slowly heat about 1 tablespoon oil. Add beef cubes, a few at a time; cook over high heat until well browned on all sides.
Add more oil as needed.
Set beef aside. Add onions to kettle.
Cook, stirring, until slightly browned. Remove onion and set aside.
Remove kettle from heat.
Stir in flour, sugar, salt, pepper and thyme.
Gradually stir in tomatoes and Burgundy.
Add bay leaf, orange peel and browned beef.
Bring to boiling, stirring occasionally.
Reduce heat and simmer, covered, 1 1/2 hours.
Add browned onions and potatoes.
Continue cooking 40 minutes longer or until beef and vegetables are tender. Remove and discard bay leaf and orange strips.
Turn mixture into serving dish.
Garnish with chopped parsley.
Makes 8 servings.

title: wiki-wiki dessert
directions: Mix together cheese and milk; blend in pineapple and mix well. Add pudding and mix for 1 minute or until well blended.
Pour into graham cracker crust and chill.
Top with whipped topping, if desired.

title: smothered okra
directions: In a skillet, cook onion and green pepper in butter for about 5 minutes.
Stir in okra, tomatoes, salt, red pepper and black pepper.
Bring to boil.
Reduce heat.
Cover and simmer for 30 to 35 minutes for fresh okra, 15 minutes for frozen okra or until okra is tender.
Makes 6 servings.

title: pork chops with celery sauce and rice
directions: In a large skillet, pan braise pork chops until brown on each side and cooked through.
Add celery soup to skillet; pour in 1 soup can of water.
Stir.
Add salt and pepper to taste.
Cover skillet and simmer.
While chops are simmering, put rice in saucepan, add water and salt to taste.
Bring to a boil and boil for 1 minute.
Cover saucepan and turn heat to low.
Cook for 14 minutes.

title: orange sherbet jello mold
directions: Mix 1 package of orange Jell-O with 1 cup of hot water.
Stir in orange sherbet until melted.
Place in mold and chill.
Mix 1 package of orange Jell-O with 1 cup of hot water.
Add the juice from the mandarin oranges and enough water to equal 1 more cup. Pour on top of chilled sherbet mixture and add the oranges.
Chill and serve.

title: banana eggnog
directions: In blender, combine 1/2 cup milk, dry instant eggnog and banana. Cover and blend until smooth.

title: party sandwich spread
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Use for sandwiches or cracker spread.

title: sweet roll dough
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Combine 2 sticks melted butter, 3 teaspoons cinnamon and 6 tablespoons corn syrup.
Pour equally into 2 (8-inch) square pans.
Divide the dough in two.
Roll each half out to 1/4-inch thick.
Brush each with milk.
Combine the half cup of brown sugar, 1 1/2 teaspoons cinnamon and half stick of butter.
Spread this mixture equally over the two halves.
Roll them up, jelly roll fashion, and slice into 1-inch pieces.
Place in pans on top of mixture.
Let rise 30 minutes.
Bake at 375° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Take from oven.
Invert a plate over each pan and turn pan upside down so that rolls fall onto the plate.

title: sweet sour sauce
directions: Add pineapple tidbits after thickened.
Can be used with pork or chicken.

title: mexican corn bread
directions: Mix the ingredients all together.
Bake at 400° about 30 minutes or until golden brown.

title: coca-cola cake
directions: Combine flour, soda and sugar together. Stir well and set aside.

title: curry bratwurst
directions: Coat skillet with melted butter (or Pam).
Place bratwurst (sliced) into skillet and fry on all sides.
Meanwhile, peel and dice onion and peel, quarter and core apple, then dice into bite sized pieces.
Add to bratwurst shortly before sausages have finished frying until onion/apple mixture is almost tender.
Then add ketchup and take from skillet.
Once it's been arranged on the plates, season to taste with paprika and curry.
Serve with rolls. Frying time:
approximately 10 minutes.

title: oreo delight dirt pudding
directions: Crumble up 1/2 cookies and put on bottom.
Mix instant pudding and 2 cups of milk in one bowl. In another bowl, mix Cool Whip and cream cheese and 1 cup milk all together.
Then mix with pudding mix.
Pour over cookie crumbs. Then crumble up rest of cookies on top.

title: "hit of the party" punch
directions: Boil water. Add sugar.
Stir.
Blend in other ingredients gradually. Chill entire mixture 1 hour in freezer.
When ready to serve, pour mixture into punch bowl.
Add 7-Up.
Okay if slightly thick.

title: cheesy chicken casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
In small bowl combine chicken and 2 tablespoons cheese.
Separate crescent dough into 8 triangles. Place about 2 tablespoons chicken mixture on wide end of triangle. Roll up, starting at wide end and rolling to opposite point.

title: cheese pudding
directions: Place bread and cheese in bottom of 9 x 13-inch or large casserole.
Mix together remaining ingredients.
Pour over bread cubes.
Cover and bake at 325° for 45 to 50 minutes.

title: cream of onion soup
directions: Saute first 3 ingredients until tender.
Add chicken stock, mace or nutmeg, bay leaf, salt and pepper.
Simmer for 45 minutes. Put soup mixture into blender for a smoother soup.
Return to pan. In a small jar with a lid, place flour and milk.
Shake until mixed.
Pour into soup mixture, stirring until soup is thickened slightly.
Slowly add heavy cream.
Heat through and serve with croutons floated on top.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: hot apple bites
directions: Line a 9 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan with foil; arrange wafers in pan, overlapping slightly.
Mix apple, brown sugar, pecans, margarine and cinnamon; evenly spread over wafers.
Broil 2 to 3 minutes or until hot and bubbly.
Sprinkle with coconut.
Remove wafers from pan.
Serve warm.

title: puffy chile relleno casserole
directions: Remove and discard seeds from chiles; lay half the chiles in bottom of a well-greased 9-inch square baking dish.
Top with half the tortilla strips and half the cheese.
Arrange tomato slices on top.
Repeat layers, using remaining chiles, tortillas and cheese.

title: ranger cookies
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients well.
Next, add flour, powder, soda and salt.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: strawberry soda pop cake
directions: Bake cake according to directions. Just before cake is done, dissolve jello in 1 cup of boiling water. Add soda pop to jello mixture and set aside.
When cake is done, remove from oven. Take a large fork and make holes all over the cake; be sure to get corners. Now pour jello-pop mixture over hot cake. Now place cake in refrigerator to cool.

title: chocolate icing
directions: Mix and boil 6 minutes the margarine, sugar and milk.
Add marshmallows, chocolate chips and vanilla.
Beat until chips are melted and consistency to spread.
Can add nuts, if desired.

title: imitation crab salad
directions: Mix all together and chill.
Serve on crackers.

title: bill stork's chili
directions: Brown the meat for a while with a bit of Lawry's seasoned salt in a pan.
Dump all the juices and stuff into a big ole pot.
Cook it for a while.
Makes 10 quarts.

title: aunt frances' zesty broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli, according to package directions, and drain. Combine soup, cheese, egg, milk, mayonnaise and horseradish together in a mixing bowl.
Stir into broccoli.
Spoon the mixture into a greased 2-quart casserole dish.

title: corn bread dressing
directions: In boiler, add chopped celery and onions, sage, black pepper, onion salt and garlic salt.
Cover with water.
Bake a cake of cornbread.
When cornbread is done and cool, crumble into bowl. When celery and onions are tender, mix with cornbread.
Add more sage to taste.
Bake in oven until top is brown.

title: cheese veggie
directions: Prepare frozen vegetables as directed on package and put into buttered dish.
Slice cheese over vegetables.
Sprinkle crackers on top and add melted butter over top.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes or until cheese melts.

title: super easy steak and gravy
directions: Place steak in greased baking dish.
Cover with cream of mushroom soup and onion soup mix sprinkled on top.
Cover with aluminum foil and bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: broccoli puff
directions: Place broccoli in a shallow baking dish.
Mix other ingredients and pour over broccoli.
Top with 1 tablespoon salted butter and 1/4 cup bread crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: nut roll
directions: Cream together cream cheese, butter and flour.
Combine nuts, sugar and coffee to make filling.
Roll dough out on flour board and spread with filling.
Cut into 5 inch rolls.
Brush with milk. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: mixed vegetable casserole
directions: Combine water, garlic salt and vegetables. Let boil 20 minutes. Mix in rest of ingredients. Bake in 1 1/2-quart casserole dish.
Sprinkle bread crumbs on top. Bake 45 minutes at 325°.

title: four layer dessert
directions: Mix and press in bottom of 12x15 pan.
Bake @ 375 for 15 minutes.
Let cool.

title: pineapple wonder(given to clo fletcher by clara hollingsworth)
directions: Bake cake in an 8 1/2 x 13 1/2-inch pan.
Combine pineapple and sugar in saucepan and bring to boil.
Spread on cake while hot.
When cake is cool, mix cream cheese, pudding mix and milk until smooth.
Spread on cake; do not cook!
Arrange slices of bananas on top.
Frost with Cool Whip; garnish with pecans. Refrigerate.

title: ground beef stroganoff
directions: Saute first 5 ingredients in skillet until beef is browned and onion is tender.
Drain fat; add the next 3 ingredients.
Stir into meat.
Cover and cook over low heat 10 to 15 minutes.
Serve over rice or noodles.
Serves 4.

title: cream puffs
directions: Mix water and margarine.
Add flour when boiling and stir vigorously until it leaves the sides of the saucepan and forms a smooth ball.
Add salt and sugar.
When cool, add eggs one at a time, beating until thoroughly mixed.
Drop on buttered pan.
Cook in 450° oven.

title: applesauce cake
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour a 9 x 13-inch cake pan. Mix all ingredients as given.

title: peanut butter patties
directions: Place cookies in food processor or blender; process until fine crumbs.
Combine crumbs and butter.
Mix until well blended.
Roll mixture into 1-inch balls.
Place peanuts in small narrow bowl. Roll each ball in peanuts, gently pressing peanuts into balls. Store in covered container in refrigerator until ready to serve.

title: fruit salad
directions: Make Jell-O as directed on box with sugar and salt added. When syrupy, add diced apples and bananas into pineapple.
Add to Jell-O and let set until firm.

title: funnel cakes
directions: Combine dry ingredients and sift together in large bowl.
Make a well in center.
Pour in mixture of eggs and milk.
With a large spoon, mix until batter is smooth.
Pour 1 to 1 1/2-inches of oil into heavy 12-inch skillet.
Heat until hot, but not smoking. Place 1/3 cup batter into a funnel, placing finger over tip until ready to dribble.
Dribble batter into hot oil, slowly moving the funnel in a circle.
This will build a snail-like coil of 3 to 4 rings, about 6-inches across.
Fry about 2 minutes on each side, turning only once.

title: strawberry pie
directions: Combine sugar, cornstarch, jello, water, and food coloring. Cook until thick; cool.
Add strawberries and pour into pie crust. Refrigerate until firm.
Serve with whipped cream.

title: fruit salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together and top with Cool Whip.

title: sausage rotel dip
directions: Mix well. Serve with tortilla chips or crackers.

title: corn muffins with jalapeno jelly
directions: Mix flour, corn meal, sugar, baking powder and pepper flakes. Whisk together egg, milk, oil and corn.
Pour liquid mixture over dry ingredients.
Mix lightly.

title: garlic-chive mashed potatoes
directions: Place the potatoes, garlic and paprika in a large saucepan or Dutch over, cover with water and bring to a boil. Reduce heat; cover and cook until potatoes are tender. Drain.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Combine peanut butter, shortening, brown sugar, milk and vanilla.
Beat at medium speed.
Add egg and beat. Combine flour, salt and baking soda.
Add to creamed mixture. Mix until blended.
Drop by tablespoonful onto ungreased baking sheet.
Flatten in crisscross pattern.
Bake at 375° for 7 to 8 minutes.
Cool 2 minutes, then remove from pan.
Yields 3 dozen cookies.

title: scotch cream scones
directions: Sift flour, baking powder and salt.
Cut in butter and add cream.
Knead 5 minutes on lightly floured surface and roll to 1/2-inch thickness.
Cut into small triangles.
Place on lightly greased baking sheet.
Bake in hot oven (450°) for 10 to 15 minutes or until light brown.
Makes about 12 scones.

title: pickled beets(easy spiced beets)
directions: Cook beets until tender; peel and cut into chunks.
Combine all other ingredients (put pickling spice in gauze and tie) and boil 5 minutes.
Add beet chunks; bring to boil and boil 8 to 10 minutes.
Put in sterile jars and seal at once.
Let stand 4 to 6 weeks before serving.

title: beef stew with dumplings
directions: Roll meat in flour; brown in hot fat.
Add hot water; cook slowly 1 1/2 hours.
Add vegetables and seasonings; cook for 30 minutes.
Drop dumplings from spoon; cover tightly and steam without lifting cover for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: jello cake
directions: Bake cherry chip cake mix as directed; let cool completely. Put Jell-O mix in cup of hot water until it dissolves.
Put 3 ice cubes in water.
Let them melt.
Make holes in cake with fork and put Jell-O down in the holes.
Let cake set for 2 hours.
Spread Cool Whip over cake before serving.

title: ball cake
directions: Let bread thaw.
Make into golf size balls.
Dip each into melted margarine, cinnamon, sugar and nuts.
Place in greased Bundt or angle food pan.
Place in layers.
Let rise 1 hour or until at top of pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Pull off in balls.

title: torta paulista(brazil)
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs and vanilla; beat well.
Add whipping cream and mix together well.
Pour mixture between layers of vanilla wafer cookies (cookies, 1/2 of mixture, cookies and 1/2 of mixture).
Freeze well, in an 11 x 7-inch pan.
Meanwhile, remove label from sweetened condensed milk and, without opening, boil the can in a pan of water for 45 minutes.
Remove can, open and pour caramel on top of frozen pie.
Return to freezer and freeze for 1 to 2 hours.
Remove from freezer and let stand 5 minutes before cutting.

title: banana nut muffins
directions: Preheat oven to 350 degrees.
In a large bowl, mix flour, wheat germ, baking soda, rolled oats, brown sugar, baking powder and salt with pastry blender.
Cut in margarine until mixture resembles coarse crumbs.
Stir in egg substitute, walnuts, vanilla extract, bananas and Glucerna Shake until flour mixture is moistened.
Line 15 muffin cups with paper liners.
Fill almost to the top with batter.
Bake for 25 to 30 minutes or until a toothpick inserted into the center comes out clean.

title: better than sex cake
directions: Toss the chocolate chips and the pecans in one tablespoon of the dry cake mix.
Beat the remaining ingredients together for 3 minutes, then fold in the chips and the pecans.
Pour into a greased and floured Bundt pan and bake for 50 minutes at 350° until it tests clean.

title: oven-roasted "new" potatoes
directions: Heat oven to 425°.
Put potatoes in a 13 x 9-inch baking pan. Add olive oil, salt and pepper.
Toss to coat.
Bake 35 minutes, shaking pan twice, or until potatoes are lightly browned and tender. Sprinkle with chives or parsley, if desired.

title: butternut cake
directions: Cream sugar and Crisco oil.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating after each addition.
Add milk with flavoring gradually with flour.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes in well-greased pan.

title: coconut cream pie
directions: Mix the flour, sugar and salt.
Gradually add milk.
Cook over moderate heat, stirring constantly until mixture thickens and boils.
Cook 2 minutes and remove from heat.
Add a small amount of this hot mixture to the egg yolks and stir, then return this egg mixture back to the original mixture and stir.
Cook 1 minute, stirring constantly.
Stir in butter, vanilla and coconut and pour into baked pastry shell.
While this cools, prepare meringue.

title: oatmeal muffins
directions: Beat eggs well and stir in brown sugar, oats and buttermilk. Let stand while combining whole wheat flour, salt, soda and baking powder separately.

title: twinkie cake
directions: Cut Twinkies in half lengthwise and place in 9 x 13 pan, cream side up. Spread pineapple, pudding and bananas and end with Cool Whip.

title: rice pudding
directions: Don't wash rice.
Place rice in 1/2 cup water; bring to a boil.
Turn
heat
down;
let
simmer until all the water is gone, about
minutes.
Pour the milk into the rice; simmer for about
1 hour, stirring once.
Add the remaining ingredients, except the egg;
cook for 8 minutes before adding egg to the hot mixture.
Gradually add egg to the hot mixture.

title: chicken and dressing casserole
directions: Cook until tender in salted water 6 to 8 chicken breast halves or 1 whole chicken.
Cool in broth, the strip meat off bones. Layer chicken in a 2-quart shallow ovenproof dish.
Combine sour cream, cream of celery soup and cream of chicken soup.
Spread mixture evenly over chicken.
Sprinkle 1 package herb dresing mix (enough for 5 to 7 pound turkey) over mixture.
Drizzle 1/2 cup margarine and 1 cup chicken stock over all.
Bake, covered, for 1 hour at 350°.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: hour and a half rolls
directions: Measure flour and pour on waxed paper.
Soak yeast in 1/2 cup warm water for 5 minutes.
Combine milk, sugar and salt in large mixing bowl.
Stir to dissolve. Beat in shortening, yeast mixture and 2 cups of flour with rotary beater until smooth.
Add remaining flour.

title: corn casserole
directions: Mix all together.
Cook at 400° for 1 hour.

title: pancakes
directions: Whiz in
blender.
Bake on cookie sheet or crepe maker. Make thinner batter for crepes.
Makes 5.

title: earthquake cake
directions: Grease and flour an 8 x 14-inch pan.
Spread coconut and nuts on bottom.
Melt oleo and cream cheese, 45 minutes in microwave. Beat until smooth.
Add powdered sugar; set aside.
Mix cake according to directions on box.
Pour over coconut and nuts.
Pour oleo mixture over cake mix.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes in a large baking pan.

title: oatmeal scones
directions: Mix all dry ingredients together in bowl. Mix all wet ingredients in another bowl. Then add to dry ingredients. Mix until just moistened. Plop on cookie sheet. Bake at 425° about 12 to 15 minutes. Makes about 20 to 22.

title: party sausage
directions: You will also need toothpicks.

title: wilted salad
directions: Separate lettuce leaves and dry by rolling in a towel and shaking gently. Tear into bite-size pieces. In a large pan, fry bacon until half done. Add onion and continue cooking over low heat until bacon is done. Remove bacon and onions. Reserve 4 tablespoons of drippings in pan.

title: almond poppy seed bread
directions: Mix all together and beat with mixer.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Makes 2 big loaves or 3 to 4 small loaves.

title: crusty parmesan chicken
directions: Mix first 6 ingredients.
Melt butter.
Dip skinned chicken in butter, then in crumb mixture.
Place chicken in lightly greased baking dish.
Bake at 350° for about 1 hour.

title: nellie's molasses cookies
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Mix well and let stand overnight in refrigerator.
In morning, roll out and bake in moderate oven.

title: spaghetti and meatballs
directions: Mix
first
ingredients and form into balls.
Brown. In saucepan,
prepare tomato soup, 2 soup cans of water, sugar and oregano.
When
sauce
comes to boil, add soda.
Pour over meatballs and
simmer
for
35 minutes to 1 hour, depending on size of meatballs.
Eat with spaghetti.

title: broccoli soup
directions: Cook the broccoli 1 hour and drain. Saute onion and margarine until clear and add green onion and chicken broth.
Cook until boiling. Put cornstarch in small bowl and add a little half and half until cornstarch is blended.
Add remaining amount of half and half to onion, margarine and chicken broth.
Add broccoli, cornstarch mixture.
Season to taste.
Add thyme and cook until it thickens.

title: pecan stuffed chicken breast
directions: Prepare favorite bread stuffing (excluding seasonings such as sage, poultry, etc.).
Mix chopped pecans into stuffing.
Tenderize the chicken breasts and sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Take an egg-sized helping of the stuffing and wrap breast around it.
Brush a mixture of butter and lemon juice over breast.
Bake breasts in 350 degree oven until internal temperature (probe must enter stuffing) equals 170 degrees.
Remove from oven.
Serve with your favorite chicken sauce (cream of chicken soup may be used).

title: sourdough starter recipe
directions: Mix together with wooden spoon in a quart jar.
Let stand, uncovered, on counter at least 5 days.
Stir several times each day.
At end of 5 days, feed again with same proportions of sugar, potato flakes and warm water.
Mix thoroughly.
Allow to stand at room temperature for 8 to 12 hours.
Remove 1 cup to make bread. Refrigerate remainder.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Grease cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: cheese broccoli soup
directions: In 3-quart saucepan (glass casserole if cooking in microwave), cook onion in margarine until tender.
Add flour and milk.
Stir over medium heat until mixture thickens.
Add cream cheese and Velveeta cheese slowly, stirring until cheese is melted.
Add remaining ingredients.
Heat thoroughly, stirring occasionally. Makes 5 (1 to 1 1/2 cup) servings.

title: creamy tuna garden wedges
directions: Mix baking mix with water.
Pat dough on ungreased 12-inch pizza pan with floured hands, forming 1/2-inch rim around edge. Bake at 450° for 10 minutes.
Cool 10 minutes.

title: apple dumplings
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Melt margarine in a 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish.
In a pot, boil sugar and water until sugar is melted. Make dough and roll out in a round piece about 1/2-inch thick. Put apples and cinnamon on dough and roll into a roll; cut into 2-inch pieces.
Place into dish with melted butter.
Pour sugar water over rolls and bake about 30 minutes.

title: blueberry muffins(diabetic)
directions: Sift together dry ingredients.
Combine egg, milk and oil; stir only enough to combine.
Do not smooth batter.
Add flour mixture; fold together.
Fill lined muffin pans 2/3 full.
Bake at 400° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: chicken pepper pasta
directions: In 12-inch skillet melt margarine.
Stir in onion, peppers and garlic.
Cook over medium-high heat until peppers are crispy-tender (2 to 3 minutes).
Remove vegetables from skillet with slotted spoon and set aside.
Reserve juices in pan.
Add chicken, tarragon, salt and pepper.
Continue cooking, stirring occasionally until chicken is lightly browned and fork-tender (7 to 9 minutes). Prepare vermicelli as directed, drain.
Add vegetables, half and half, Mozzarella and Parmesan cheeses.
Reduce heat, cook until cheese melts (3 to 5 minutes).
Add vermicelli.
Toss gently to coat.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Mix together; after batter is smooth, add nuts.
Pour into Bundt cake pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: three bean salad
directions: Mix and marinate for 24 hours for best flavor.

title: goulash
directions: Cook stew beef in pressure cooker about 15 minutes, then add other ingredients. Cook an additional 5 minutes. Pour all ingredients into a large pot. In a separate cup, mix 1-1/2 teaspoon of flour with water to make a paste. Add paste to large pot of stew beef and cook until thick. Pour goulash over rice and serve.

title: "wet shoo-fly pie"
directions: Combine molasses, syrup and water; stir in soda.
Beat a little of molasses mixture with egg.
Stir egg mixture into mixture.
Mix flour, butter and brown sugar into crumbs.
Mix 1 cup crumbs into the molasses mixture; pour into pie shell.
Top with remaining crumbs.
Bake at 400° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: pumpkin pecan muffins
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Generously grease 18 medium muffin cups or line with paper baking cups.
Combine dry ingredients; add pumpkin, brown sugar, vegetable oil, milk, egg and vanilla, stirring just until moistened.
Fill prepared muffin cups 3/4 full.

title: seven layer dip
directions: Layer in casserole bowl in order.

title: chocolate chip cookies
directions: Cream Crisco and sugar; blend in egg.
Add vanilla and mix well.
Add combined dry ingredients and mix well.
Stir in chocolate pieces and nuts; drop from teaspoon onto ungreased cookie sheets.
Bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: apple pie pudding
directions: Arrange apples in baking dish.
Sprinkle with cinnamon. Arrange strips of bread over apples.
Combine butter, sugar, flour and egg.
Pour over bread.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour or until apples are done and crust is brown.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Boil cranberries in water and sugar until they burst open. Add Jell-O, stirring until dissolved.
Remove from fire.
Add marshmallows and mix until mixture is smooth.
Let cool and add fruit and nuts.
Chill until set.
This salad can be made with sugar-free Jell-O and Sugar Twin (sugar substitute) for diabetics.

title: macaroni casserole
directions: Saute over low heat the first four ingredients in 1/3 cup oil. Stir until macaroni turns slightly yellow.
Heat to boiling the tomato juice.
Add salt, pepper and Worcestershire sauce.
Stir into macaroni mixture.
Pour into 1 1/2-quart baking dish.
Cover. Bake in oven 30 to 40 minutes at 350°.

title: reese's balls
directions: Mix peanut butter, margarine and powdered sugar.
Roll into balls and refrigerate.
Melt chocolate chips and paraffin in double boiler.
Use a toothpick to dip balls into chocolate. Place on wax paper to cool.

title: light banana pudding
directions: Prepare pudding mix according to package instructions using skim milk.
Line individual dessert dishes with 4 vanilla wafers each, add 1/2 slice banana.
Top with vanilla pudding.
Serves 4. Contains 180 calories and 170 mg sodium per serving.

title: broccoli and mushrooms
directions: Place broccoli in a 2-quart casserole.
Dot with 1/4 cup butter, salt and pepper.
Mash mushrooms in 3 tablespoons of butter and saute until golden.
Put mushrooms and butter in casserole. Refrigerate.
When ready to serve, bake for 30 to 40 minutes or until broccoli is tender at 375°.

title: deviled eggs
directions: Place eggs in a pan with enough water to cover about an inch over the eggs. Bring to a boil and boil for 5 minutes. Remove from heat; cover and let stand for 15 minutes. Pour off water and cover eggs with VERY COLD water until the eggs cool.

title: l.b.'s chicken casserole
directions: Cook and debone chicken.
Crush crackers and mix with melted margarine.
Place 3/4 of the cracker mixture in bottom of a 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Place chicken pieces on top.
Mix together soups and sour cream.
Pour over chicken.
Sprinkle remaining cracker mix over top.
Bake 30 to 40 minutes at 325°.
Makes two dishes easily so one can be frozen for later.

title: shrimp creole
directions: Saute onion, bell pepper and celery in bacon drippings until tender.
Add tomatoes, sugar, ketchup, Worcestershire sauce and flour-water mixture.
Stir until smooth and slightly thick.
Add shrimp and seasonings.
Cook 10 minutes more.
Serve over rice.

title: chimichangas
directions: Combine cooked meat with taco seasoning as directed on package. Add refried beans to meat mixture.

Put 1/2 cup meat on tortilla and fold securely. Fry in hot canola oil for 2 to 3 minutes or until brown and crisp. Serve on a bed of shredded lettuce. Cover with shredded Cheddar cheese, chopped olives, chopped onions, sour cream and black olives.
End with chunky salsa.

title: pork chop casserole
directions: In casserole dish sprayed with Pam, layer potatoes, onions, 1/3 can soup (spread over top), green beans, 1/3 can soup, pork chops, remainder of soup, salt and pepper as desired.
Cover and bake at 325° for 1 3/4 hours.
Remove cover and brown for 15 minutes.
Serves 4.

title: clam puffs
directions: Blend cheese and sour cream; mix with clams, Worcestershire sauce, salt and onion.
Spread on toast rounds.
Put under broiler and brown.
Dust tops with paprika.
Mixture may be made 2 days in advance.

title: tomato soup cake
directions: Blend together Crisco and sugar.
Mix flour, cloves, baking powder, nutmeg and cinnamon.
Mix in separate bowl the tomato soup and baking soda.
Blend sugar mixture with soup mixture, then blend in flour mixture.
Add nuts and raisins (optional).
Bake in a small tube or loaf pan at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes.

title: heavenly apple salad
directions: Mix jello and hot water well; add marshmallows and stir well. Add pineapple, nuts, cold water and apples.
Let jell in refrigerator.
Mix cream cheese and powdered sugar; then spread on jello.
Then cover with Dream Whip.

title: treva's marinade
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients, then add remaining ingredients. Mix all of this with your electric mixer just until it is well bended.

title: poppy seed dressing(heart healthy)
directions: In a small bowl, whisk together honey, vinegar, rind and mustard.
Gradually whisk in oil until all is incorporated.
Stir in poppy seed.
(May also be prepared in a blender or food processor.)
Yield:
About 1 3/4 cups.

title: pasta salad
directions: Cook rotini as per directions.
Mix all ingredients together in a large bowl.
Mix one bottle of dressing with salad.
Add other bottle of dressing to salad just before serving.
Makes a large salad.

title: party spread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Combine all ingredients.
Mix well. Spread mixture in 9-inch pie plate.
Bake for 15 minutes.
Garnish with additional almonds if desired.
Serve with assorted crackers or Bagel chips.
Serve warm.

title: fruit pie
directions: Put 1 crust in pie tin.
In saucepan, combine juice from fruit with water to equal 1 cup.
Pour into pan.
Mix sugar and starch. Cook on low heat until thick.
Add fruit, then pour into pie crust.
Place crust number 2 on top.
With knife, cut holes in top crust to vent.
Bake for 35 to 40 minutes in a 375° oven.

title: party hamburger
directions: Brown meat; cut up peppers and onions very fine.
Add to browned meat with tomato sauce; simmer.
Boil noodles; drain.
Get large mixing bowl and mix sour cream, cottage cheese, cream cheese and poppy seed together.
Preheat oven to 400°.
Get a long glass pan; put noodle mix on the bottom, then put the meat sauce on the top.
Let cook about 30 to 40 minutes.

title: pecan pie
directions: Mix all together.
Pour in shell.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 50 minutes.

title: basic meat loaf
directions: Mix together beef, onion, bread crumbs, egg, milk, 2 tablespoons catsup and seasonings.
Mold into a rounded, flat pan. Spread 2 tablespoons catsup over top.
Microwave on High for 15 to 20 minutes.
Let stand 10 minutes before serving.

title: baked chocolate pudding
directions: Sift together 3 times the flour, sugar, baking powder, salt and cocoa.
In a separate bowl, combine the melted butter, vanilla and milk.
Blend the liquid mixture with the dry mixture and add the nuts.
Pour into a square greased baking dish.

title: spaghetti salad
directions: Cook spaghetti; drain and rinse, using warm water.
Add remaining ingredients and mix well.
Will keep refrigerated up to 2 weeks.

title: pork chop pyramids
directions: Flour pork chops and brown lightly in another skillet.
Saute sliced onions until tender.
Prepare rice according to box directions.
Place chops in electric skillet or Dutch oven.
Top chops with green pepper slices, sauteed onions, minced garlic and season to taste.
Pile rice on top in pyramids.
Dilute tomato sauce with equal parts of water and pour around the chops.
Simmer slowly for 2 to 3 hours, basting occasionally.

title: vegetarian chili
directions: Saute crushed tomatoes, picante sauce, cumin, salt and basil leaves.
Cover and simmer 5 minutes.
Add remaining ingredients. Cover and simmer for 15 minutes.

title: root beer slush
directions: Put all ingredients in blender.
Whiz at high speed until slushy.
Serve.

title: pepper steak
directions: Trim any fat and bone from meat.
Cut meat into approximately 1 1/2 x 3-inch pieces.
Grease skillet lightly with fat from meat. Brown meat thoroughly on one side.
Turn.
Sprinkle with 1/4 teaspoon salt.
Brown other side of meat; turn.
Sprinkle with remaining 1/4 teaspoon salt.
Push meat to side of skillet.
Add onion and mushrooms; cook and stir until tender.
Add bouillon, soy sauce and garlic.
Cover and simmer 30 minutes, or until tender.
Add green pepper; cover and simmer 5 minutes.
Blend cornstarch with water; gradually stir into mixture in skillet. Cook, stirring constantly, until mixture thickens; boil 1 minute. Add tomatoes and heat through.
Serve over noodles or rice.

title: easy lemon pie
directions: Thaw lemonade and mix well with Eagle Brand milk in a medium size bowl. Add Cool Whip and mix together well.
Pour evenly into pie crust and set in refrigerator for 3 to 4 hours until firm.

title: coconut pie
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
Makes 2 pies.
Mix first 2 ingredients together; beat in eggs and milk.
Add vanilla and lemon, then coconut.
Pour into pie shells and bake approximately 30 to 35 minutes until barely shaky in center.

title: baked french toast casserole
directions: Slice French bread into 20 slices, 1-inch each. Arrange slices in a generously buttered 9 x 13-inch flat baking dish in two rows, overlapping the slices.

title: five cup salad
directions: Cut up mandarin orange slices; mix all remaining ingredients together and chill overnight.
Garnish with cherries (optional).

title: hearty beef fondue
directions: Cut one loaf French bread into bite-size pieces.
Heat milk in crock-pot on high.
Add cream cheese; stir until cheese is melted. Add mustard, onion and dry beef.
Cook 5 minutes.

title: quick meal - succotash
directions: Brown ground turkey or ground beef in a large pan.
Can stir in some chopped onion.
Add pork and beans.
Drain the can of corn and add.
Stir in tomatoes.
Simmer about 10 minutes.
Serve with French bread.
Preparation time:
20 minutes or less.

title: beef stew
directions: Put everything in a large casserole and cover.
Put in 275° oven for 5 hours.

title: buttermilk salad
directions: Heat pineapple.
Add Jell-O, stir until dissolved.
Cool.
Add Cool Whip and cold buttermilk and nuts.
Chill until firm.

title: party tortillas
directions: Mix the first 6 ingredients; spread on tortillas.
Roll tortillas and refrigerate overnight.
Slice into bite size slices. Serve with picante sauce.

title: all-together apple cake
directions: Sift first 6 ingredients into an 8-inch square pan.
Break eggs into the center of the pile.
Beat or stir with fork.
Add apples and Crisco.
Mix thoroughly; pat level.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Cinnamon and sugar can be sprinkled on top before baking.
Nuts are optional, also.

title: carrot cake and frosting
directions: Mix all but last four ingredients together in mixing bowl. Pour into greased and floured cake pan.
Bake at 300° until done (about 45 minutes).
Cool.
Mix last 4 ingredients together and pour over cooled cake.

title: cowboy stew
directions: Cut beef in 1/2-inch dice; combine with onion, salt and pepper and brown over medium heat in large Dutch oven.
Add potatoes and water to meat and cook until potatoes are tender.
Add remaining ingredients; cover and simmer for 60 to 80 minutes, stirring occasionally.
I add one or two dried cayenne peppers for interest.

title: buttermilk rolls
directions: Mix sugar, salt, soda, baking powder and shortening. Add buttermilk and yeast. Then add flour. Roll and allow to rise until double, about 1 hour. Place remaining dough in covered dish in refrigerator and use as needed. Shape into rolls and place on greased baking sheet. Heat oven to 400°. Bake 12 to 15 minutes.

title: scalloped potato casserole
directions: Mix all together and spread in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Sprinkle corn flakes on top.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: cream of potato soup
directions: Pan boil potatoes.
Melt butter and add onions and cook gently until soft but not browned, 5 minutes.
Stir in flour and seasonings.
Remove from heat and slowly add milk.
Stir until well blended.
Place over heat and cook until smooth and thick, stirring constantly.
Add potatoes, liquid and any other vegetables.

title: zucchini brownies
directions: Beat together all ingredients for 3 minutes.
Pour into greased and floured 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: frozen punch
directions: Boil sugar and water for 3 minutes.
Add jello and 4 cups of cold water and let cool.
Add juice and freeze.
Thaw to slushy before using and add 1 quart of ginger ale for each 1/2 gallon of mix.

title: pina colada fruit dip
directions: In food processor bowl, combine all ingredients.
Cover; refrigerate several hours or overnight.
Serve with fresh fruit. Makes 2 1/2 cups.

title: savory salmon loaf
directions: Combine ingredients in order given.
Pack firmly into buttered loaf pan and bake in a 350° oven for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: banana with lime and tangerines
directions: In a small bowl, combine lime juice and pulp, vanilla and cinnamon (it's best to use a whisk or fork so cinnamon doesn't clump up).
In a large bowl, combine tangerines, bananas and coconut. Pour lime mixture over them and toss well until the fruit is coated.
Serve at room temperature or slightly chilled in small sundae dishes for dessert or breakfast.

title: hot corn bread
directions: Sift dry ingredients.
Add remaining ingredients and mix well. Fill muffin pans half full and bake 15 to 20 minutes at 450°.

title: corn 'n squash pudding
directions: In separate pans cook squash and corn according to package directions.
Drain corn; set vegetables aside.

title: baked beans
directions: Mix together beans, onion, catsup and sugar.
Pour into casserole dish; top with raw bacon.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: pepper steak with rice
directions: Pound steak to 1/4-inch thickness. Cut into 1/4-inch wide strips. Sprinkle meat with paprika. Using a large skillet, brown meat in butter. Add garlic and broth. Cover and simmer 30 minutes. Stir in onions and green peppers. Cover and cook 5 minutes more. Blend cornstarch, water and soy sauce. Stir into meat mixture. Cook, stirring until thick and clear; add tomatoes and stir gently. Serve over bed of rice.

title: velveeta cheese fudge
directions: In a saucepan, melt butter and cheese.
Add vanilla.
Sift together the sugar, cocoa and nuts.
Add the cheese and butter mixture.
Mix well and spread evenly in a greased, long pan.
Cool and cut into pieces.

title: peanut candy bars
directions: In medium saucepan, bring sugar and corn syrup to boiling. Boil, stirring frequently, for exactly 1 minute.
Remove from heat. Blend in peanut butter and vanilla.
Stir in peanuts.
Then spread in a greased 15 x 10-inch sheet pan.
Let stand until cool enough to handle.
Mark off in 24 bars, about 3 inches in length, then with hands, shape into candy bars.
Set on waxed paper.
When all bars are shaped, wrap individually in waxed paper.
Store in a cool place.

title: orange banana bread
directions: In a large bowl, beat together the butter and brown sugar until creamy; add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Beat in banana and orange peel.
Stir together whole wheat flour, all-purpose flour, salt and soda.
Mix into the butter mixture with the orange juice; stir in raisins and granola. Spread batter in a well-greased 9 x 5-inch loaf pan.
Bake in a 350° oven for 1 hour or until a wooden pick inserted in center comes out clean.
Invert bread onto a wire rack to cool before slicing. Makes 1 loaf.

title: wedding cookies
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add vanilla and water.
Add flour, a little at a time.
Add nuts and form into balls about 1 inch in diameter.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake about 20 minutes at 300°.
Roll in additional powdered sugar while warm.

title: moist and creamy coconut cake
directions: Prepare cake mix as directed on package.
Bake in 13 x 9-inch pan.
Cool cake for 15 minutes.
Poke holes in cake with large fork.
Combine sugar, milk and 1/2 of coconut (while cake is cooling) in saucepan.
Bring to a boil, reduce heat and simmer 1 minute.
Spoon evenly over warm cake.
Cool completely.
Fold 1/2 cup coconut into Cool Whip.
Spread over cake.
Sprinkle with remaining coconut.
Chill overnight.
Store in refrigerator.

title: ham ball
directions: Mix together cream cheese and miracle whip.
Fold in remaining ingredients.
Refrigerate 2 to 3 hours.
Form into ball and roll in nuts.

title: banana bread
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs and beat well.
Add mashed bananas, nuts, flour and soda (dissolved in the buttermilk) and flavoring.
Bake in a greased loaf pan in 350° oven for 45 to 50 minutes.
Cool partially in pan.
May use cream cheese topping if desired.

title: easy peanut butter cookies
directions: In large bowl, beat Eagle Brand and peanut butter until smooth.
Add Bisquick and vanilla.
Mix well.
Shape into 1-inch balls.
Roll balls in sugar.
Place 2 inches apart on ungreased baking sheet.
Flatten with fork.
Bake 6 to 8 minutes at 375° or until lightly browned (do not overbake).

title: pfeuserli(swiss pancake dabs)
directions: Melt butter in warm milk and stir in sifted flour to make batter.
Fold in the stiffly beaten egg whites.
Fry in walnut-size pieces in very hot oil.
Excellent with fall vegetables.

title: italian deluxe piselli
directions: Pour 1 to 2 tablespoons olive oil in 7-inch nonstick skillet frypan.
Heat to hot.
Put in scallions and peas.
Cook 5 to 10 minutes.
Add asparagus and cook until tender (10 to 15 minutes). Water may be added during cooking to prevent drying of vegetables. Serve hot as side dish.
Salt and pepper may be added to taste. Season with sprinkle of dried basil, if desired.

title: dumplings
directions: Sift together flour, baking powder and salt.
Stir in milk only until blended.
Drop by spoonfuls onto chicken or meat in boiling meat stock (not in liquid).
Cook 10 minutes with kettle uncovered and 10 minutes tightly covered.

title: frito corn salad
directions: Combine, refrigerate until serving.

title: crab cakes(appetizers and sandwiches)
directions: With your hands, mix together all the ingredients for crab cakes except the oil.
Form into 12 equal patties.
Refrigerate for 30 minutes.

title: 8 layer bean dip
directions: Blend taco seasoning into refried beans.
Spread on large round platter.
Continue layers, guacamole, chilies, sour cream, olives, cheese, tomato and green onions.
You may place tortilla chips around edges to look like a sun.

title: cranberry bread
directions: Sift dry ingredients together.
Cut in butter until mixture resembles coarse meal.
Combine orange rind, orange juice and eggs.
Add to dry ingredients and mix just to moisten.
Fold in berries, nuts and raisins.
Turn into 2 greased and floured 9 x 5-inch loaf pans.
Bake in 350° oven for 55 to 60 minutes.
Cool. Slices better the next day.

title: stuffed mushrooms
directions: Remove stems from mushrooms and chop fine.
Mix mushroom stems with onion, celery and butter.
Microwave on High 2 minutes or until onion is soft.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Fill mushroom caps with stuffing mixture.
Arrange 8 stuffed mushrooms on a paper towel lined dish in a circular pattern.
Microwave on High 1 1/2 minutes, turning dish once.
Repeat with remaining mushrooms.
Makes 36 appetizers.

title: baked spaghetti
directions: Mix first five ingredients together in a large bowl.
Put into 2 lightly buttered casserole dishes.
Spread cheese over top of both casseroles.
Bake at 350° for 1/2 hour, covered, and then uncovered for 1/2 hour.

title: delicate fluff pancakes
directions: Beat egg yolks well.
Beat in buttermilk and soda.
Then add flour, baking powder, salt and sugar (sifted together).
Stir to blend, but do not overmix.
Stir in melted shortening and fold in egg whites, beaten until stiff, but not dry.
Bake on a hot griddle.
Makes about 16 to 18 pancakes, depending on size.

title: chocolate mayonnaise cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease and lightly flour baking pans. Sift together dry ingredients into a large bowl.
Stir in mayonnaise.
Gradually stir in water and vanilla until smooth and well blended.
Pour into prepared pans.
Bake about 30 minutes or until cake springs back when touched.
Cool in pans 10 to 15 minutes.
Remove from pans.
Frost when completely cool.
Makes 3 (8-inch) layers.

title: sausage bread ring
directions: Frozen bread dough is rolled into a rectangle and then wrapped around a spicy sausage filling for a quick and hearty brunch.
You can make the bread several weeks ahead and freeze it or prepare it early in the day of your brunch.

title: 7-up salad
directions: Cook Jell-O, water and 7-Up until thick.
Let stand until cool.
Add pineapple and bananas.
Put in large container (9 x 13-inch).
Mix topping ingredients of pineapple juice, sugar, flour and egg.
Prepare two envelopes Dream Whip and 1 can coconut.
Top with pecans, if desired.

title: blueberry crunch
directions: Grease baking dish.
First spread pineapple, then spread blueberries.
Sprinkle 3/4 of sugar over the blueberries.
Then sprinkle the cake mix (dry) over the top.
Melt butter and spread over the cake mix.
Add chopped nuts and spread remaining 1/4 cup of sugar over mix.
Preheat oven to 350° and cook 40 minutes. After 25 minutes, prick with fork and cook the remaining 15 minutes or until golden brown.

title: basic pie crust
directions: Cut shortening into flour.
Add salt.
Thoroughly mix with fingertips.
Stir in water, one tablespoon at a time, until soft, but not sticky.
Roll half of the dough 1/8-inch thick.
Place in bottom of 9-inch pie plate.
Roll out second half and place on top of pie.
Makes 9-inch double crust.

title: scallop casserole
directions: Place scallops in a buttered casserole dish. Add bread crumbs, crackers, salt and garlic salt.
Combine butter and cream; drizzle over scallops (do not mix).
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: pretzel crumb crust
directions: Combine pretzel crumbs with sugar and melted margarine.
Mix well.
Press evenly into bottom of 9-inch pie pan.
Bake at 350° for 8 minutes.
Cool.

title: eggplant parmesan casserole
directions: Peel eggplant and slice thinly.
Dip in eggs, then in bread crumbs.
In a large skillet, fry eggplant until tender and brown. Drain on paper towels.
Place alternate layers of eggplant, grated cheese and tomato sauce in 2-quart casserole.
Bake at 350° until bubbling hot (about 30 minutes).
Serves 10.

title: heavenly crescent appetizer
directions: Take one package of crescent dinner rolls; do not tear them apart.
Lay in a 9 x 13 x 2-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Mix sour cream, mayonnaise, minced dry onions, seasoned salt and dill weed.
Blend well.
Spread this mixture on top of baked crescent rolls while hot and sprinkle with shredded Cheddar cheese.

title: peanut butter squares
directions: Blend together; place in greased platter.
Set 1 hour and cut in squares.

title: refrigerator bran muffins
directions: Pour boiling water over 1 cup of bran; add raisins, stir and set aside.
In large bowl cream sugar, honey and shortening.
Add eggs and beat well.
Blend in buttermilk.
Add bran and raisin mixture.
Add the 2 cups bran and mix.
Sift flour with soda and salt.
Add to bran mixture and mix well.
Cover tightly and store in refrigerator.
This will keep for 6 weeks.

title: brunch casserole
directions: Saute onion and bell pepper until tender. Mix with remaining ingredients and pour into a greased 9 x 13-inch pan overnight. Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: french silk pie
directions: In a small mixer bowl, cream the sugar and butter (not margarine) about 4 minutes or until light.
Blend in cooled chocolate and vanilla.
Add eggs, beating on medium speed of mixer about 5 minutes.
Scrape sides of bowl constantly.
Turn into baked pastry shell. Cover and chill overnight.

title: cranberry sauce
directions: Add enough sugar to sweeten, probably 2 cups.
Grind cranberries and apples and mix all ingredients.

title: punch bowl cake
directions: Tear cake into bite-size pieces.
Drain pineapple.
Prepare pudding according to package.
Alternate layers of each ingredient. Repeat layers.
Chill.

title: pineapple slush
directions: Dissolve sugar in hot water and combine with pineapple juice and lemon juice.
Freeze.
Before serving, partially thaw and add ginger ale.

title: overnight salad
directions: Layer lettuce, then cauliflower. Spread mayo on top of cauliflower. Sprinkle onion and bacon on top of mayo. Cover with sugar and Parmesan cheese. Let set in the refrigerator overnight. Stir before serving.

title: mexican cornbread
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Pour in buttered pan.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Cook cranberries and water in 3-quart saucepan until berries are soft.
Add sugar, gelatin and juice from pineapple.
Stir until dissolved, then cool until thickened.
Add pineapple, celery and nuts.
Stir until thoroughly mixed.
Pour into 3-quart mold or container.
Chill until firm.
Serves 20 to 24.

title: chicken cordon bleu
directions: Flatten chicken pieces to 1/4-inch thickness. Sprinkle with parsley, oregano, onion salt and black pepper.
Place a ham slice and a cheese slice on each chicken breast. Roll up from short side and secure rolls with wooden picks.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Whip the margarine, softened cream cheese and sugar with mixer until thoroughly smooth. Add peanut butter, vanilla and eggs. Continue mixing until creamy. Fold in Cool Whip.
Pour into a 9-inch pie pan with a graham crust. Chill before serving.

title: broccoli rice casserole
directions: Combine rice with 3 cups water.
Bring to a boil.
Cover and simmer for about 45 minutes until all water is absorbed.
Heat oil in large frying pan.
Saute onion, garlic, dill, thyme and oregano until onion starts to wilt.
Add parsley, mushrooms and green pepper.
Stir 1 minute.
Add broccoli.
Stir often.
As soon as broccoli changes color and becomes tender, but is still crisp, add nuts and remove from heat.

title: pineapple side dish
directions: Grease a large baking dish. Line bottom of dish with pineapple chunks. Mix sugar and flour and sprinkle on top of pineapple. Layer with Ritz crackers. Add grated cheese on top. Pour melted butter over all. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes. Serves 20 people.

title: shrimp creole
directions: Saute celery, onion, green pepper, garlic and parsley.
Add flour, tomato paste, water, thyme, salt, pepper, bay leaves and hot pepper sauce.
Cook for 1 hour at low heat.
Add shrimp and cook until done.
Serve over rice.

title: chiffon cake
directions: Mix 3 cups graham cracker crumbs and 1 cup melted margarine, saving 1 cup for the top.
Press into pan for bottom crust.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Mix oleo, oil, sugar.
Add eggs and vanilla.
Beat well.
Sift flour and cinnamon.
Beat well.
Mix into mixture.
Add nuts and apples.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour in Bundt pan.

title: hominy pie
directions: Brown meat; drain.
Then add flour, tomatoes and seasonings. Simmer.
Brown onion and hominy in hot fat; add to meat mixture. Place in greased casserole; sprinkle with cheese and bake for 30 minutes at 350°.
Serves 8.

title: squash casserole
directions: Slice squash and onion, boil in small amount of water.
Drain and add eggs, milk and almost all of mixture of cheese, crackers and melted margarine.
Salt & pepper to taste.
Pour into baking dish and top with remaining mixture.
Bake 20 minutes at 300°. Put 1/2 of cheese mixture in with squash and put rest on top.

title: zucchini pie squares
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Mix all ingredients.
Spread in pan.
Bake until golden brown, about 25 minutes.

title: refrigerator bread and butter pickles
directions: Combine sugar, salt and vinegar in saucepan and heat, stirring, until sugar and salt are dissolved.
Add celery seed and mustard seed.
Place sliced cucumbers and onions in jars and pour the vinegar mixture over them.
Refrigerate.
They will be ready to eat in a week or two.

title: green beans with mushrooms
directions: In a large pot over high heat, bring 4 cups of water and 1/4 teaspoon salt to a boil.
Add green beans.
Cook until beans are tender, 8 to 10 minutes.

title: b.l.t. sandwich
directions: Cover bread with mayonnaise.
Add bacon, tomatoes and lettuce.

title: irish scone
directions: Set oven to 375°.
Grease and flour a 9-inch round cake pan; set aside.
Mix flour, baking powder and salt.
Rub in the butter, then add sugar and raisins.
Add egg, then buttermilk until mixture is stiff, not runny.
(If too runny, add a little more flour.)

title: pecan pie
directions: Beat eggs and sugar until thick.
Add syrup, nuts and vanilla. Pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake in slow oven (350°) for 1 hour.

title: turkey soak
directions: Cover meat.
Soak in cool place for 4 or 5 days.
Rinse; bake or freeze.
(Turn every day.)

title: mexican tossed salad
directions: Drain and wash beans.
Combine with cheese, pepper, onion, tomatoes and lettuce.
Add dressing.
Just before serving, add crushed Fritos.

title: pineapple upside down cake
directions: Melt butter in pan (9 x 9 x 2-inches).
Add sugar, drain pineapple and add.
Make cake mix as directed on box.
Pour batter over mix.
Bake at 350° about 45 to 50 minutes.

title: kielbasa stir-fry
directions: Cook rice and in a separate skillet cut up vegetables and fry in 2 tablespoons butter until tender.
Cut up kielbasa in small pieces and fry in with vegetables until done.
Add cream of potato soup and 1/4 can of water.
Simmer 10 minutes and serve over rice.
Salt and pepper to taste.

title: easy peach crumble
directions: In a 9-inch pie dish, pour peaches and juice in.
Sprinkle dry cake mix on top.
Slice butter in small pieces.
Place butter on top of cake mix.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until brown.

title: zucchini squash cake
directions: Combine squash, sugar, oil and eggs (leave the peel on the squash and the cake will have a soft green color or you can peel the squash if you want).
Mix in dry ingredients and nuts.
Bake in Bundt pan 1 1/2 hours at 300°.
Can frost or glazed.
Great with cream cheese frosting.

title: fudge ecstasies
directions: In a heavy medium saucepan, heat 1 cup of the chocolate pieces, unsweetened chocolate and butter or margarine until melted, stirring constantly.
Transfer to a large mixer bowl to cool slightly.
Stir together flour, baking powder and salt.
Add eggs, sugar and vanilla to chocolate mixture and beat well.
Add flour mixture and beat until well mixed.
Stir in remaining chocolate pieces and nuts.
Drop by heaping teaspoonfuls onto a lightly greased cookie sheet.
Bake in a 350° oven for 8 to 10 minutes or until edges are firm and surface is dull and cracked. Cool on cookie sheet for 1 minute, then remove and cool thoroughly.
Makes about 36.

title: chocolate dainties
directions: Cook sugar, butter and cocoa together until it hardens on a saucer (or drop a drop in a glass of cold water; it forms a hard ball when it is ready).
Add rest of ingredients to sugar mixture. Stir well and dip out onto waxed paper.

title: ziti
directions: Saute onion in oil.
Add beef and cook.
Add sauce and 1 1/2 cups water.
Bring almost to a boil.
Add seasonings.
Cook down 45 minutes to an hour.
Boil pasta with oil and a lot of salt. Wash pasta.
Mix pasta into sauce.
Add Ricotta cheese.
Enjoy.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Boil chicken 45 minutes.
Allow to cool; break into small pieces.
Mix together in large glass baking dish chicken, sour cream, mushrooms and mushroom soup.
In large bowl, mix stuffing, broth and melted butter.
Spread evenly over chicken.
Bake at 400° for 35 minutes.
Serve with cranberry sauce.

title: celia's pizza
directions: Mix together yeast, salt and sugar.
Place 4 cups of flour in a bowl.
Add oil to yeast mixture.

title: double deck brownies
directions: Start heating oven to 350°.
Sift flour with baking powder and salt.
With hand beater or electric mixer, beat eggs at medium speed, gradually adding sugar.
Stir in melted butter and flour mixture, blending well.
Pour 1/4 batter into small bowl.
Blend in coconut and almond extract.
Blend chocolate into remaining batter.
Spread mixture into a well-greased 8 x 8 x 2-inch pan. Spread coconut batter onto chocolate mixture.
Bake 35 minutes or until done.
Cool and cut into squares.
Makes about 2 dozen.

title: dill bread
directions: Soften yeast in water.
Combine in bowl cottage cheese, sugar, onion, butter, dill seed, salt, soda, egg and yeast.
Add flour in 2 additions, beating well.
Let rise until light and doubled (50 to 60 minutes).
Stir down dough.
Turn into well-greased casserole 8 inches round.
Let rise until light (30 to 40 minutes).
Bake at 350° for 40 to 50 minutes.
Brush with butter and sprinkle with salt.

title: sloppy joe turnovers
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
In large skillet, brown ground beef and onion; drain.
Add salt, garlic powder, catsup and sour cream; mix well.
Separate dough into 10 biscuits.
On ungreased cookie sheet, press or roll each biscuit to a 4 x 4-inch square.
Place approximately 1/4 cup meat mixture on center of square.
Fold over corner of square to form a triangle; seal edges with fork.
Cut 1/2-inch slits on top.
Bake at 375° for 15 to 20 minutes or until golden brown.
Brush with melted margarine, if desired. Yield:
10 turnovers.

title: easy cherry danish
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour a 9 x 13-inch pan. Set aside. Cream the butter and sugar until light. Add vanilla and eggs, one at a time; beat until light and fluffy. Add flour.
Mix until well blended.
Batter will be stiff.
Pour into prepared pan.
Mark off into 20 squares.
Drop spoonfuls of cherry filling onto squares. Bake 35 to 45 minutes. Cool and sprinkle with confectioners sugar.

title: chicken pot pie
directions: Prepare bottom crust in a 9-inch pie pan. Melt margarine on medium heat. Add onion and cook 2 minutes or until tender. Stir in flour, salt and pepper; blend well. Gradually add broth and milk. Cook, stirring constantly, until thick and bubbly. Add chicken and vegetables. Spoon into crust. Top with second crust and flute edges. Cut several slits in crust. Bake 30 to 40 minutes until golden brown. Let stand 5 minutes before serving.

title: van's shrimp etouffee
directions: Peel and wash shrimp.
Set aside.
In food processor, finely chop onion (not green onion) and celery.
Melt butter in large saucepan; saute onion (not green onion), celery, garlic and diced tomatoes.
Add spices and stir.
Add in shrimp; cook until pink. Stir in flour.
Pour in chicken broth, Worcestershire sauce and tomato paste; stir.
Add in green onions.
Simmer over low heat for 20 to 30 minutes.
Serve over rice along with French bread. Serves 6.
Better the next day.

title: christmas pickles
directions: Make syrup.
Boil
together
vinegar,
sugar, cinnamon, water and cloves.
Pack fruit, which
has been drained, into a gallon jar and cover with syrup.
Ready
to
eat
after 2 or 3 days. Store in refrigerator.
Keeps well for several weeks.

title: blueberry delight
directions: Melt butter in a 9 x 13-inch pan or dish in oven.
Add flour and nuts to butter and mix well to make a crust.
Bake in oven until light brown approximately 20 minutes.
Cool.

title: quiche lorraine
directions: Blend together beaten eggs, salt, milk and flour.
Reserve a bit of bacon.
Press the rest of the bacon into the pie crust. Next, add the cheese the same way.
Pour on the egg mixture. Finally, sprinkle with the extra bacon. Put in 400° oven for 10 minutes, then for 30 minutes at 325°.

title: corn flake cookies
directions: Beat egg whites until stiff.
Gradually beat in the rest of the ingredients.
Bake on greased cookie sheet for 10 minutes at 400°.
You may also add peanut butter.

title: peachy lemon pie
directions: Place drained peaches in an unbaked pie shell.
Beat eggs; add remaining ingredients and pour over peaches.
Bake for about 40 minutes or until custard is set at 350°.

title: old fashioned sugar cookies
directions: Cream butter and sugar thoroughly; add egg, vanilla and lemon rind.
Beat until mixture is light and fluffy.
Sift dry ingredients and stir into creamed mixture together with milk.

title: campers concoction cookies
directions: Mix ingredients together in order given. Bake at 325° for 10 minutes.

title: heavenly chocolate ice cream
directions: Combine candy and Eagle Brand milk in a large saucepan.
Cook over low heat, stirring constantly, until candy melts.
Cool, stirring occasionally.

title: cranberry delight
directions: Drain pineapple.
Boil pineapple juice, water and jello, stirring to dissolve it.
Remove from
heat and blend in cranberry sauce.
Add lemon juice and nutmeg.
Chill until mixture thickens slightly.
Blend in sour cream, then pineapple and pecans.
Makes about 2 quarts.
Pour into 9 x 13-inch Pyrex dish or spray mold with Pam for special Thanksgiving or Christmas treat.
Unmold on lettuce-lined serving dish.

title: chicken cacciatore
directions: Coat chicken pieces with flour.
In 12-inch skillet, heat oil; brown chicken on both sides.
Remove from heat.

title: marshmallow sauce
directions: Boil sugar and milk to thread stage.
Cool and beat until thick.
Set in pan of hot water and beat until thin enough to pour.
Dissolve marshmallows in double boiler with water.
Stir until smooth.
Pour syrup over marshmallows; beat.

title: microwave cranberry sauce
directions: Combine ingredients in a 1-quart microwave-safe casserole. Cover and microwave on High power for 4 to 6 minutes or until cranberries pop, stirring every 2 minutes.
Serve warm over sliced turkey, chicken or pork.

title: party fruit punch
directions: In punch bowl combine all ingredients. Stir well. Just before serving add a tray of ice cubes.

title: rumaki
directions: Combine all ingredients except chicken livers and bacon in mixing bowl.
Add livers; stir to coat.
Let stand 20 minutes. Drain, reserving marinade.
Wrap each liver piece in half strip of bacon; secure with toothpicks.
Broil on rack about 2 inches from source of heat about 10 minutes, turning often.
Heat reserved marinade in small saucepan to boil; simmer 2 minutes.
Use as dip for rumaki.

title: ground beef casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together and put in casserole dish.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour.

title: watergate salad
directions: Blend pudding with cottage cheese and pineapple.
When smooth, mix in rest of ingredients.

title: macaroni and cheese
directions: Cook macaroni according to package directions; drain and place in a buttered 1 1/2-quart casserole dish.
Melt butter; stir in flour and blend well.
Gradually add milk and cook over medium heat until thick.
Add salt, pepper and 1 1/2 cups of cheese, stirring to melt cheese.
Gently mix sauce with macaroni. Sprinkle with remaining 1/2 cup of cheese.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 30 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: low cholesterol brownies
directions: Beat sugar into egg substitute.
Mix in oil, cocoa and vanilla.
Add flour and nuts.
Mix completely.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: carrot pineapple cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease and dust a 9 x 12-inch pan with flour.
Mix together the ingredients and bake for 1 hour.

title: zucchini quiche
directions: Mix everything together well.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes, until golden brown.

title: chocolate chip cookies
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Beat margarine, sugar, eggs and vanilla in large bowl. Mix with mixer until fluffy.
Mix in flour, baking soda and salt; stir in chips and nuts.
Drop by teaspoons 2 inches apart onto ungreased cookie sheet. Bake 10 minutes or until golden brown.
Remove from cookie sheet.
Makes 6 dozen.

title: italian sauce
directions: Put olive oil in pot and heat.
Add garlic (chopped) and brown.
Add both cans of tomatoes and sauce.
Fill one can with water to swish the other and pour in pot.
Then add all spices listed.
Bring to boil, then let it boil 1/2 hour.
Turn heat to low and simmer for 3 to 4 hours.
You can brown any kind of meat and add to sauce.
But let it cook in sauce the whole time so it will be tender.
Wala! That's Italian.

title: hershey's doubly chocolate cookies
directions: Beat butter, vanilla, sugar and eggs until light and fluffy. Stir together flour, cocoa, baking soda and salt.
Add to butter mixture.
Stir in chips and nuts.
Drop by teaspoon.
Bake 8 to 10 minutes or until set in oven at 350°.
Cool.

title: strawberry glaze pie
directions: Cut up 1 cup of strawberries.
Mix sugar and cornstarch in 2-quart dish.
Stir in water gradually until smooth.
Add the cup of cut-up berries.
Cook and stir over medium heat until thick and clear.
Stir in food coloring.
Stir in remaining berries except for 1/4 cup for topping.
Pour mixture into pie shell and chill for 3 hours.
Top with whipped cream and berries.

title: rice and mushroom casserole
directions: Melt oleo.
Add soup, water, rice and mushrooms.
Bake 1 hour at 375°.
Serve hot!

title: corn casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Combine undrained corn with remaining ingredients in bowl; mix well.
Spoon into 8 x 12-inch baking dish.
Bake for 45 minutes or until set.
Yields 8 servings.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Pour sugar over apples and let stand at least 2 hours (forms liquid for mix).
Combine all ingredients; mix well.
Pour into 9 x 13-inch pan, greased and floured.
Bake at 325° for 45 minutes or until toothpick comes out clean.

title: kitchens' deputy dogs
directions: You will need paper plates.

title: strawberry jell for fresh strawberry pie
directions: Mix well.
Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly, until thick.
Cool and pour over berries.
Top with Cool Whip, if desired.

title: cheesy potatoes
directions: Melt butter. Add onion; simmer until tender. Add other 3 items.
Mix well.
Place in a 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Cover. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or cook for 5 hours on slow in crock-pot or 3 hours on medium.

title: smith's bulletproof tactical lake forest chili(for 8-quart pot)
directions: Throw everything into pot (use wooden spoon; for class act) and cook slowly for 3 to 4 hours.
Stir bottom frequently to prevent sticking.
(If it sticks and burns, entire pot will taste like h---.)

title: winter lentil soup
directions: Heat butter in large saucepan over medium heat.
Add onions and carrots and cook 5 minutes.
Add beef stock and tomato paste.
Mix well and season.
Stir in lentils, garlic and parsley.
Bring to boil.
Reduce heat to low and cook for 1 1/2 hours, partly covered, over low heat.

title: karen's cheese balls
directions: Mix ingredients, except pecans, by hand.
Put the chipped pecans on wax paper.
Roll cheese mixture on pecans.
Put in refrigerator on top of plastic bag for about an hour, then re-shape into ball form.
Add more chipped nuts and decorate as desired.
Leave out at least 1 hour before serving.

title: quick squash casserole
directions: In a Corning Ware dish, slice 1 layer of yellow squash thin to cover pan.
Add salt, pepper and slices of butter on top.
Next, add a layer of sliced onions on top.
Repeat with salt, pepper and butter.
Add a layer of sliced tomatoes; repeat salt, pepper and butter.
Add a layer of sliced green bell pepper and repeat with salt, pepper and butter.
Bake in a 350° oven until tender.
Add cheese slices on top and put back in oven until cheese melts.

title: fried squirrel
directions: Section squirrel.
Soak in salt water until free of blood. Roll in flour mixed with salt and pepper to taste.
Fry in skillet with enough grease to bubble around each piece of meat. Fry each side until brown.
After meat is browned, turn down heat and add 1 cup water.
Cover and let simmer until tender.

title: caramel corn
directions: Pop the popcorn and put in large roaster pans in oven.
Then combine margarine, sugar, Karo and salt.
Cook and boil to firm ball stage.
Remove from heat and add soda and stir in.
Pour hot syrup over popped corn and nuts.
Stir all until coated.
Return to oven at 250°, stirring every 15 to 20 minutes.
Bake 30 minutes more.
Makes 5 quarts.
Store in airtight container.

title: chicken pot pie
directions: Place
chicken in kettle with water, salt, onion, carrot and celery,
using
only
teaspoon of the salt.
Cook until tender. Strip
meat
from	chicken.
Combine flour,
salts and pepper with 1/2 cup of broth and mix until smooth.
Heat 3 cups broth
to boiling, add flour mixture and cook until thick.
Add chicken. Pour into casserole and cover with pastry; seal well. Make slits in top.
Bake in a 400° oven for 45 minutes or until brown.
May dot crust with butter.

title: cottage cheese salad
directions: Blend Cool Whip and cottage cheese.
Drain fruit and add to Cool Whip mixture.
Fold in orange Jell-O.
Chill.

title: ground beef and rice casserole
directions: Cook meat and onions until done.
Add soups, water and uncooked rice.
Mix well and pour into a greased casserole dish. Bake 1 1/2 hours at 350°.

title: french bread meal
directions: Mix hamburger, onion, green pepper, salt, pepper and parsley in a pan and brown.
Cut bread ends off; take out the middle.
Mix breads, egg and cheese together.
Put hamburger and bread crumb mixtures together; stuff back into bread shell.
Wrap in foil. Bake at 325° for 25 minutes.

title: baked carrots
directions: Place carrots in casserole.
Cream butter, sugar, salt and cinnamon together.
Add water.
Blend well.
Pour over carrots. Cover and bake 1 1/2 hours at 350°.

title: easy peach cobbler
directions: Heat peaches with syrup and butter.
Combine biscuit mix and sugar together; add water until consistency is like thick pancake batter.
Pour batter on bottom of 2-qt. casserole dish and add peach mixture.
Bake at 350 degrees for about 40 minutes or until done.
Good with vanilla ice cream.

title: easy lemon pie
directions: Combine lemonade and Eagle Brand milk.
Mix well.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Pour into graham cracker crust or baked pie shell or use as dessert.
Refrigerate for 2 or 3 hours or overnight.

title: pot pie
directions: Mix the ingredients together; add only enough flour to make a soft dough.
Roll thin and cut in pieces about 1 inch by 2 inches. Drop in broth.

title: baked potato soup
directions: Make roux with butter, flour, milk, salt and pepper.
Add the insides of the potatoes, bacon and cheese to the roux.
Heat thoroughly and garnish with green onions and sour cream.

title: chow-chow
directions: Bring to a boil.
Cook slowly for 1 hour.
Pack in jars and seal.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until done.
Makes 2 loaves

title: zucchini and green rice
directions: Slice zucchini in 1/4 inch rounds.
Steam until done but still firm.
Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix rice with lemon juice, parsley and seasonings.
In a greased casserole make a layer each of rice mixture, cottage cheese and zucchini.
Top with grated cheese. Bake uncovered for 10 to 15 minutes.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.
(You may want to use more cheese than is suggested.)

title: heavenly frosting
directions: Mix flour, salt and milk.
Cook until thick, stirring constantly.
Refrigerate (cover so top will not dry up).
In a mixer, put Crisco and sugar.
Whip until fluffy.
Flavor as desired with vanilla, almond or coconut, etc.

title: broccoli and cauliflower salad
directions: Cut vegetables into bite size pieces.
Mix mayonnaise, oil, vinegar, sugar, salt and pepper together.
Combine with vegetables and refrigerate.

title: clam chowder
directions: Saute bacon in Dutch oven until crisp.
Pour off pan drippings. Set aside. Drain clams; reserve 1 cup juice. Set clams aside. Add clam juice and next 5 ingredients to bacon. Bring to a boil, cover and simmer 15 minutes.

Combine flour and milk in shaker bottle. Add mixture, clams, half and half, hot sauce, salt and pepper to soup mixture. Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly, until well heated. Sprinkle with paprika.
Enjoy.

title: sweet potato cobbler pie
directions: Boil potatoes; peel and slice in even slices.
Prebake one shell; set aside.
Sprinkle the 1/4 cup sugar and spread 1/4 stick butter over while hot.
Using a deep dish pie pan, spread half of the potatoes and liquid on the bottom, 1/2 of the sugar, butter and all spices.
Place the baked pie shell on top of this layer. Repeat the same process with the remaining ingredients.
Place the unbaked pie shell on top of this layer.
Bake in preheated 350° oven until top is golden brown.

title: swiss steak
directions: Mix dry mustard with flour.
Dust or roll into steak.
Season with salt and pepper and brown on both sides.
Place in baking dish.
Cover with onions, peppers, tomatoes, Worcestershire sauce and brown sugar.
Cover and bake at 325° to 350° for 1 1/2 hours or until tender.

title: egg drops for soup
directions: Mix all ingredients together well.
Will be a sticky mixture. If too thick, add 1 tablespoon water.
