Spoon and press through large hole ladle strainer, pressing with the back of a tablespoon. Let drop into 8 to 10 cups boiling chicken broth.
Simmer 5 to 10 minutes.
Serve hot.

title: mexican corn bread
directions: Mix all ingredients together and bake in a greased pan for 45 minutes at 350°.

title: kosher pickles
directions: Directions are for 1 quart of pickles.
Wash a quart canning jar.
Wash pickling cukes.
Pack cucumbers vertically in jar. Pack firmly.
Put in all the spices.
Stuff the head of dill into the top.
Add salt.
Fill to the brim with cold tap water.
Seal. Should be ready to eat in 10 days to 2 weeks if kept in a warm area.
Will keep for years.

title: apple salad
directions: Mix the sugar, mayonnaise and lemon juice.
Beat with a spoon until smooth.
Dice your apples, celery, banana and cherries.
Add in the nuts.
Pour the first mixture over the fruits.
Chill until ready to serve.

title: jon's hot dogs
directions: Slice hot dogs into 1/2-inch rounds.
Add ingredients into medium size saucepan.
Add hot dogs.
Bring to boil.
Reduce to a simmer for 2 to 3 hours.

title: sandwich spread
directions: Grind together tomatoes, peppers and onions; add salt.
Let stand 1 hour, then drain.
Bring to boil the sugar, vinegar, celery seed and turmeric.
Cool 10 minutes, then add flour, mustard and enough water to make paste.
Mix all together.
Bottle while hot.

title: green bean casserole
directions: Brown hamburger, onion and chili powder together.
Drain. Spread in bottom of 8 x 8-inch pan.
Layer on top green beans and mushrooms.
Pour tomato juice evenly over the top.
Bake in a 350° oven for 20 minutes.
Slice Velveeta cheese over the top.
Return to oven and bake until cheese is melted and starting to brown.

title: potato pancakes
directions: Pare and coarsely grate potatoes and onion.
Rinse and use paper towels to pat dry.
Mix with eggs.
Sprinkle flour, salt and pepper over mixture and mix well.
Heat oil in large skillet, drop potato batter by heaping tablespoonfuls into skillet and form pancakes.
Saute until golden brown on both sides.
Serve with applesauce and sour cream.

title: shrimp stir-fry
directions: Put all ingredients except broth and flour in a wok.
Cook on medium heat for a few minutes.
You can also add other vegetables like pea pods, water chestnuts, bean sprouts, etc., if desired. Mix chicken broth and flour.
Add to stir-fry and heat until thickened.
Serve on rice or noodles.

title: peppered steak
directions: Brown meat in hot oil.
Stir in tomatoes and green pepper. Add soy sauce and seasonings.
Cover; cook for 10 minutes.
Blend cornstarch with consomme; stir into meat mixture.
Cover; simmer for 10 minutes.
Serve over hot rice.

title: raised donuts
directions: Mix all ingredients together, working in more flour if needed. Knead at least 10 minutes.
Roll out dough to 1/2-inch thickness and cut into donuts.
Let rise to almost double in size.
Fry in oil at 375° until lightly brown on one side, then turn over and brown other side.
Remove from oil and set on drainer.

title: cowboy potatoes
directions: Peel the potatoes. Cut into thin slices but not all the way through.
Put potatoes in baking dish and fan them slightly. Sprinkle with herbs and salt; dribble with butter.
Bake potatoes at 425° for about 50 minutes.
Sprinkle with the cheeses. Bake for another 10 to 15 minutes until lightly browned, cheeses are melted and potatoes are soft inside.

title: cream cheese gems
directions: Beat margarine, cream cheese, vanilla and egg yolk.
Blend in cake mix 1/3 at a time.
(May need to mix last part by hand.)
If too thick, add 1 tablespoon or so of water.
Mix in raisins, nuts and coconut.
Drop by teaspoons onto cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° about 15 minutes or until lightly browned.
Makes 3 dozen.

title: pasta with chicken and sun-dried tomatoes
directions: Cut chicken into 3-inch strips.
Saute onion and garlic in 2 tablespoons olive oil until wilted.
Add chicken and brown, stirring frequently.
Add basil and sun-dried tomatoes to skillet and saute for 2 minutes.
Cook pasta according to package.
Toss hot pasta and sauce together in serving bowl; add extra oil from tomatoes.
Add salt and pepper to taste.
Serves 4.

title: fresh broccoli salad
directions: Mix together and
let stand overnight in the refrigerator.

title: poinsettia cookies
directions: Cream sugar and butter; add eggs and extracts.
Sift together salt and flour; stir into butter mixture.
Stir in coconut and 3/4 cup of butterscotch chips.
Chill dough until firm.
Roll in 1-inch balls.
Place on cookie sheet.
Flatten with glass dipped in granulated sugar.
Place a butterscotch chip in the center of each cookie.
Place cherry wedges in a circle to resemble a poinsettia. Bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Makes 5 dozen.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Steam broccoli until tender; drain and set aside.
Mix all ingredients.
Pour
cooked broccoli into buttered 10 x 13-inch casserole dish.
Pour soup mixture over top.
Sprinkle cheese and Ritz cracker crumbs over top.
Dot with butter.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: karo pecan pie
directions: Beat eggs thoroughly with sugar, salt, corn syrup and melted oleo.
Add pecan halves.
Pour into 9 in. baked pie shell.
Bake 30 minutes at 350 degrees.

title: easy fruit cobbler
directions: Melt margarine in baking dish.
Combine flour, 1 cup sugar and milk.
Pour over margarine.
Heat fruit with 1/2 cup sugar.
Pour over batter.
Bake at 400° for 30 minutes or until done.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: pineapple jello salad
directions: Mix jello with boiling water and let cool some. Cut marshmallows into small pieces if using large marshmallows and add to jello. Beat cream cheese and pineapple juice together. (If using cottage cheese, put in blender and process before mixing with juice). Add juice mixture to jello and add pineapple and nuts.

title: brenda's cheese ball
directions: Allow cheeses to reach room temperature (approximately 1 1/2 hours).
Mix by hand thoroughly.
Mix in other ingredients.
Shape into ball; let set, covered, until reaches room temperature.

title: breakfast before
directions: Saute sausage; drain (let sit).
Beat eggs with milk, salt and mustard.
Layer bread cubes, sausage and cheese in a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Pour egg mixture on top.
Refrigerate overnight.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: lemon squares
directions: Mix 2 cups sifted flour, powdered sugar and melted oleo.
Press into a 9 x 13-inch greased and floured baking pan.
Bake 20 to 25 minutes in a preheated 350° oven.

title: blueberry beauty
directions: You will need a deep dish pie pan.

title: cajun red beans
directions: Place beans in a large saucepan.
Fry bacon and crumble into beans.
Saute vegetables in bacon drippings until wilted but not brown, stirring frequently.
Add to beans and remaining ingredients.
Cover and simmer about 30 minutes.
Serve over rice. Yields 4 servings.

title: mil slidne's breakfast casserole
directions: Remove crusts from bread and dice into 1-inch squares.
Put in bottom of a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Brown meat; drain off grease and pour meat over bread.
Layer cheese over meat.
Blend eggs and mustard; add milk.
Pour over cheese.
Refrigerate overnight. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: lemon sauce
directions: Combine sugar, cornstarch and water in top of double boiler. Cook over hot water until thickened.
Remove from heat.
Stir in butter, rind and juice.
Good over bread pudding or gingerbread.

title: baked stuffed eggplant
directions: Cut off top of eggplant, about 3-inches down.
Scoop out the eggplant meat as much as possible without breaking shell.
Cook the eggplant meat in salt water until tender.
Drain well, then mash.

title: crunchy celery casserole
directions: Cook celery and onion until almost done.
Drain.
Blend soup and milk.
Add soup, salt and water chestnuts to celery and onion; place in greased casserole.
Combine butter and crackers and sprinkle over top. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: maple fudge
directions: Bring milk, butter and sugar to boil, stirring constantly, to soft ball stage.
Remove from heat.
Add chips and Marshmallow Creme.
Add flavoring and nuts.
Pour into greased pan; cool. Place in refrigerator until ready to slice into squares.

title: hot rolls
directions: In large mixer bowl, combine 4 cups of flour, yeast, sugar and salt.
Combine warm water and oil; add to dry mixture in bowl. Add eggs and beat at medium speed for 3 or 4 minutes.
Stir in enough flour to make a soft dough.
Turn out on lightly floured board and knead until smooth.
Place in greased bowl, turning once to grease top of dough.
Cover and let rise until double.

title: beef stroganoff "modified"
directions: Remove meat fat.
Slice into thin strips.
Combine meat with flour and paprika.
Heat oil in large skillet or Dutch oven.
Over high heat, brown beef, onion, garlic, pepper and mushrooms, about 5 minutes.
Stir in water and beef bouillon.
Stir to dissolve. Cook over low heat about 10 minutes.
Add 1/2 cup evaporated skim milk.
Stir to combine and heat another 3 to 5 minutes.
Serve over hot noodles or rice.
Makes 6 servings.

title: golden punch
directions: Mix all together.
Put in quart container and freeze.
When ready to use, mix 1-quart punch to 1-quart 7-Up.

title: salsa pork chops (or chicken)
directions: Mix all ingredients. Cook at 350° for 1 hour.

title: microwave baked fish
directions: Place fish on microwavable platter or plate.
Season as desired.
Bake in microwave oven for 3 minutes on High.

title: dream pie
directions: Prepare whipped topping mix with 1 cup of the milk and the vanilla as directed on package using a large mixer bowl.
Add remaining milk and the pie filling mix.
Blend, then beat at high speed for 2 minutes, scraping bowl occasionally.
Spoon into pie shell.
Chill at least 4 hours before serving.

title: country gravy
directions: Brown mixture of the first 4 ingredients.
Add the milk; cook until thick.

title: cheese log
directions: Mash together with hands.
Form into 2 logs on foil paper. Roll in chopped pecans.
Wrap in plastic wrap and place in fridge for about 2 hours (better if overnight).

title: gemahlenes fleisch(ground meat gravy)
directions: Brown ground meat and onion; drain.
Stir in flour, salt and pepper.
Add water to make gravy.
Bring to a boil.
Simmer for 10 minutes.

title: raisin bran muffins
directions: Sift together
flour,
sugar, baking soda and salt; put in a large
mixing
bowl.
Stir in cereal; add buttermilk, oil and eggs.
Blend until dry ingredients are moistened.
Bake at 375° for 20 minutes.

title: million dollar fudge
directions: Boil together sugar, salt, butter and milk for 6 minutes. Pour syrup into large bowl over chocolate bits, chocolate and marshmallow cream.
Add nuts.
Beat until chocolate is melted and pour into 13 x 9 x 2-inch buttered pan.
Let stand several hours before cutting.
Store in a tin box.

title: russian-style beef stroganoff
directions: In a heavy skillet; melt half of the butter. Add onion and cook slowly until transparent. Remove from pan and set aside. Raise heat to medium-high, add beef and cook briefly, browning on all sides. Remove from pan and set aside with the onions. Melt remaining half of the butter in the skillet and stir in mushrooms. Cover and cook 3 minutes. Season with pepper and nutmeg. Whisk in sour cream, but do not allow to boil. Return beef and onions to pan and heat through. Serve over egg noodles or rice.

title: chicken a la king
directions: Cook onion and green pepper in butter until tender. Blend in soup and milk. Add chicken, pimento and pepper.
Heat slowly; stir often. Serve over hot biscuits.

title: mexi-chili casserole
directions: Preheat
oven to 375°.
Reserve 1 cup of corn chips and 1/2 cup
of
cheese.
Combine remaining chips and cheese with the chili,
sauces and onion;
pour into a 1 1/2-quart casserole. Bake, uncovered, in a 375° oven for 20 minutes or until thoroughly heated.
Spread top with sour cream.
Sprinkle with reserved cheese and corn chips.
Bake 5 minutes longer.
Makes 6 servings.

title: pineapple sheet cake
directions: Mix together well and
bake in a 350° oven for 30 to 35 minutes.
Use large sheet pan.

title: cheese wafers
directions: Mix all ingredients together. Roll in small balls and flatten with a fork. Bake 10-15 minutes on ungreased cookie sheet at 350 degrees.

title: creamy banana pudding
directions: In a large bowl combine milk and water.
Add pudding mix; beat well.
Chill 5 minutes.
Fold in whipped topping.
Layer the pudding mixture with bananas and wafers.
End with pudding mixture.
Cover and refrigerate.

title: japanese fruit pie
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: fruit salad
directions: Cut all fruit into chunks.
Put chunks ina bowl.
Add pecans and Cool Whip.
Mix together.
Chill for a few minutes.
Serves 8 to 10 people.

title: tenderloin slivers on rosemary crostini
directions: Cook your beef and chill it until ready to assemble your crostini.
Meanwhile, make a rosemary butter by mixing softened butter with snipped rosemary, scallions, salt and a hefty dose of ground pepper.
Spread half a teaspoon of butter on one side of bread slices.
Brown in a saute pan.
Place on a cookie sheet, toasted side up.
Roll the remaining butter into a roll in waxed paper and freeze until ready to assemble.
Preparing the three parts in the morining and allowing them to chill makes assembly easy and keeps the hors d'oeuvre from getting soggy.
Slice cold beef into slivers and place on crostini.
Top beef with a slice of butter.
You can slice through the waxed paper, then pull it off each slice.
Reheat crostini for about 5 minutes at 375° just before serving.

title: corn meal pie(makes 2 pies; old family recipe)
directions: Mix dry ingredients together in a saucepan.
Add milk and water.
Mix well.
Add beaten egg yolks, butter and vanilla.
Cook over low heat until thick (like banana pudding).
Pour into cooked crusts; top with beaten egg whites.
Cook in 350° oven about 10 minutes or until brown.
Best if a little cool.

title: golden glazed ham
directions: Heat oven to 325°.
Score surface of ham.
Cook ham according to label instructions.
Combine remaining ingredients in small saucepan; heat until jelly melts, stirring occasionally.
Spoon over ham during last 30 minutes of baking time.

title: mashed potato bake
directions: Mix all of the ingredients and place in large casserole dish; sprinkle paprika over the top.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: beef burgundy
directions: Put all ingredients in crock-pot.
Do not add any water.
Cook on low all day or at least 8 hours.
Serve over noodles, rice or mashed potatoes.

title: carrot cake
directions: Add all ingredients and mix well.
Put in a well-greased and floured pan.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes or until well done.

title: chili
directions: Dice onion and brown.
Add ground beef and brown.
As you mix together, add tomato sauce and stir.
Add chili spice, salt and pepper to taste.
Serve with French bread.
If time permits, add green pepper.

title: marshmallow salad
directions: Mix eggs, sugar, pineapple juice, flour and vinegar together. Cook until thick.
Dissolve gelatin in boiling water.
Mix with cooked mixture and let cool.
Add whipped cream, pineapple and marshmallows.
Pour into long cake dish and chill.
Serves 12 to 15.

title: suzie's date-nut muffins(low-fat)
directions: In medium bowl, stir together dates, boiling water, oil and vanilla.
In small bowl, mix flours, sugar, walnuts, cinnamon and baking soda.
Add date mixture and stir until moistened.
Makes 12 muffins.
Bake at 375° for 25 minutes.
Freezes well.

title: church special
directions: Cut up fryer.
Salt and pepper each piece.
Put in large buttered baking pan.
Boil enough water to almost cover.
Pour over floured chicken.
Sprinkle with paprika and let brown.
Just before taking out of oven, pour a can of creamed chicken soup over. Let cook enough to mix gravy well.
Serve with rice.
You will be a big success at a church gathering.

title: tuna casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients in a 3 quart sauce pan.
Mix lightly with fork until well blended.
Place in a buttered casserole dish and bake in a 350 degree oven for 35 minutes.
Makes 6 servings.

title: fruit salad with fruit dressing
directions: Divide fruit among serving dishes.

title: whole wheat banana bread
directions: Melt butter and blend in sugar.
Mix in eggs and bananas. Blend until smooth.
Mix flour, salt and soda.
Stir in whole wheat flour.
Add hot water and stir in nuts.
Turn into greased and floured 9 x 5-inch loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 10 minutes.

title: grandma's biscuits
directions: Heat oven to 450°.
Cut shortening into flour until it looks like fine crumbs.
Add milk and stir until dough leaves the sides of the bowl.
Turn dough out onto lightly floured surface.
Knead until smooth.
Roll out about 1/2-inch thick and cut with floured cutter.
Place on lightly greased baking sheet.
Bake 10 to 12 minutes.

title: cookie salad
directions: Mix pudding mix with buttermilk.
Add fruit and Cool Whip. Crush the cookies and fold in, saving some to sprinkle on top just before serving.
Keep refrigerated.

title: chocolate chip cookies
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Combine butter, sugar, milk and vanilla in a large bowl.
Beat at medium speed until creamy.
Beat egg into creamed mixture.
Combine flour, salt and soda and mix into creamed mixture until just blended.
Stir in chocolate chips.

title: microwave caramel corn
directions: Combine brown sugar, oleo, corn syrup and salt in 1 1/2-quart bowl.
Cook on High for 2 minutes or until bubbly.
Cook for 2 more minutes on High; add soda and stir until foamy.
Put popcorn in brown paper bag and pour mixture over it.
Fold top of bag over and shake.
Place bag in microwave and cook 1 1/2 minutes on High. Take out and shake again.
Cook on High for 1 1/2 minutes.
Shake again and pour onto greased cookie sheet or waxed paper.

title: 60 minute rolls
directions: Mix together yeast and warm water and set aside.
Combine remaining ingredients except flour and heat to lukewarm.
Combine yeast and milk mixture.
Add to flour.
Mix well; let stand in warm place for 15 minutes.
Turn onto floured area; knead lightly (about 1 minute).
Cut and shape dough into desired size shape and place onto lightly greased sheet.
Let rise 15 to 20 minutes.
Bake at 375° to 400° for 10 minutes or until golden brown.

title: kuchen
directions: Mix hot roll mix according to directions.
Let set for 15 minutes.
Press 1/2 hot roll mix into 9 x 12-inch greased pan. Use other half of hot roll mix for rolls.
Grease saucepan.
Mix together in saucepan on stove the flour, milk and cornstarch. Cook and stir until the consistency of thick cream.
Add more cornstarch if needed.
Add the eggs, sugar, oleo and half and half to mixture.
Stir until thick.
Pour into pan as prepared. Sprinkle with cinnamon as desired.
Bake at 350° until crust is brown.

title: chicken stretch
directions: Prepare stuffing mix as directed and spread in casserole dish. Place chicken over dressing.
Pour 1 cup cream of chicken soup over chicken.
Melt butter.
Mash up crackers.
Mix together and spread over soup.
Bake at 350° until crackers are brown.

title: mexican cornbread
directions: In mixing bowl, add cornmeal, flour, sugar and cheese.
Put into blender corn, eggs, jalapeno peppers, oil and onion; chop well.
Add this to first 4 ingredients and mix well.
Add buttermilk and blend well.
Pour in muffin pans and cook in 350° oven.
Makes 24 muffins.

title: easy turkey salad
directions: In medium bowl, mix soup and mayonnaise until smooth.
Fold in chopped turkey, celery, onions, red peppers, parsley, and pepper.
Serve mixture on leaf of lettuce.
Refrigerate left-overs.

title: apricot balls
directions: Mix apricots, coconut and milk.
Shape mixture into 1-inch balls.
Roll in nuts.
Let stand until firm.
Makes about 4 dozen.

title: lasagna casserole
directions: Cook noodles in boiling water for 3 minutes.
Drain and toss with drizzle of olive oil and set aside.

title: tomato relish
directions: Mix all and bring to boil and simmer for two hours.
Put in hot jar and seal.

title: apple dip
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients, then add nut topping.
Slice apples to dip.
This is a great recipe; it tastes like caramel apples.

title: apricot dessert
directions: Combine in saucepan and mix very well.
Cook to a full boil, then set aside to cool.
When cooled, whip 2 envelopes Dream Whip and combine with cooled mix.
Pour into pan and top with chopped nuts.
Refrigerate until set.

title: yummy rick chocolate chip cookies
directions: Mix together softened butter, brown sugar, sugar and vanilla. Slightly beat eggs and add to butter and sugar mixture.
Mix well. Add flour, baking powder and salt.
Mix again.
Add chocolate chips, walnuts and coconut and mix well.
Drop by teaspoonfuls onto cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes or until golden brown.
Makes about 7 dozen.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Cream together margarine and peanut butter.
Add remaining ingredients.
Knead well.
Place dough a teaspoon at a time onto cookie sheet, pressing each dab flat with a fork.
Cook at 375° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: plum cornish hens
directions: Wash the Cornish hens and pat dry.
Cover with butter and salt to taste.
Bake at 375° for 30 minutes.
Mix jam and lemon juice and coat the hens.
Bake 45 more minutes.

title: no-bake pumpkin pie
directions: In a small bowl, blend milk, egg, cinnamon, ginger, nutmeg and salt; set aside.
In medium saucepan, sprinkle jello over water and let stand 1 minute.
Stir over low heat until gelatine is completely dissolved, about 2 minutes.
Blend in milk mixture; continue stirring, over low heat, until mix is slightly thickened, about 5 minutes.
Blend in pumpkin and turn into prepared crust. Chill until firm.
Garnish, if desired, with whipped cream.
Makes about 8 servings.

title: spinach dip
directions: Mix together chestnuts, soup mix, onion, margarine and sour cream.
Add spinach to mixture and chill.

title: hawaiian pudding
directions: Mix graham cracker crumbs with melted butter in a square or oblong pan or glass dish.
Place sliced bananas over graham cracker crumbs. Beat eggs and mix in lemon juice.
Then mix with milk.
Pour over bananas.
Pour pineapple over milk and spoon Cool Whip over pineapple.
Top with chopped pecans.
Refrigerate at least 2 hours before serving.
Slice into squares to serve.

title: taco dip
directions: Blend sour cream, cream cheese and taco seasoning with mixer. Spread in deep dish such as quiche dish.
Pour taco sauce on top. Spread over sauce in order given the lettuce, tomatoes and cheese. Serve with Doritos or nacho chips.

title: brittany dressing
directions: 1/2 hour before serving, combine sugar and vinegar and stir into sour cream.
Fry bacon until crisp.
Save all grease.
Dry bacon on paper towel and chop into small pieces.
Put bacon bits and all the grease into the sour cream mixture.

title: peach melba trifle
directions: Cut angel food cake into 1/2 inch cubes.
Peel and slice peaches.
Stem and halve strawberries.
Place a layer of cake in the bottom of a trifle dish.
Ladle 3 tablespoons of yogurt on top of cake.
Top with 4 tablespoons of peach melba sauce.
Add 1/2 of the fresh fruit.
Repeat layers once more.
Refrigerate.
Light and low fat.

title: chicken parmesan
directions: Place chicken in preheated oven at 350°, skin side down, for 1/2 hour; turn and cook 1/2 hour more. Remove from oven.
Pour off fat.
Cook together soup, water, onion, garlic and oregano until steaming.
Pour over chicken.
Arrange Mozzarella over chicken and sauce.
Sprinkle with Parmesan. Bake 30 minutes.

title: heath bar candy
directions: Cook butter and brown sugar over low heat slowly until it comes to a full boil.
Stir constantly with wooden spoon.
Boil and stir until thermometer reaches 290° (hard crack).
Add nuts. Pour onto well-oiled 9 x 13-inch pan.
While warm, place 1/2 of disks on candy.
As it melts, spread with spatula.
Then refrigerate for about 10 minutes until chocolate hardens.
Take from refrigerator and carefully flip over and cover other side with the rest of the disks (melted).
Spread 1/2 cup chopped nuts on top.

title: aunt jennie's apple cake
directions: In large mixing bowl, combine flour, sugar, soda, oil, cinnamon, eggs and vanilla.
Beat at medium speed until well mixed.
Stir in apples and nuts.

title: warm apple cinnamon cobbler
directions: Preheat oven to 375 degrees.
In a large saucepan over medium heat, combine the apples, water, cinnamon, cornstarch and fructose. Cook until apples are soft and mixture is thickened, about 10 minutes.
Pour apple mixture into a casserole dish.
Prepare biscuit dough by combining the whole wheat pastry flour and baking powder.
Add oil and stir until well mixed.
Add honey and buttermilk; stir with a fork until flour mixture is moist.
Add additional milk if necessary.
Drop biscuit dough by tablespoons on top of apples.
Bake for 20 minutes or until biscuits are golden brown.
Serve warm.
Yield:
6 servings.

title: sweet 'n sour shrimp
directions: Heat oil on high in a large skillet.
Add chopped peppers and onions and stir-fry for 4 minutes until crisp-tender.
Add pineapple, shrimp and stir-fry sauce.
Simmer 1 minute, until heated throughout.
Serve on top of cooked rice.
Serves 4.

title: pecan potato chip cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes or until golden brown.

title: easiest ever scalloped potatoes
directions: Scrub and cut potatoes in pieces; cut onion in pieces.
Boil in salted water until tender.
Drain and set aside.
Combine soup and cheese in saucepan; simmer until cheese melts.
Add ham; heat through.
Stir in potatoes and onions; heat through.
Serve immediately.

title: texas caviar
directions: Combine all ingredients except salad dressing; mix well.
Pour salad dressing over mixture; cover and refrigerate to marinate for at least 2 hours.
Drain and serve with tortilla chips.

title: peanut butter balls
directions: Mix first three ingredients; shape into balls.
Let stand in refrigerator for a while.
Melt Hershey bar and wax in top of double boiler and dip balls in chocolate.

title: cheese ball
directions: Mix all ingredients together, roll into ball and roll in chili powder.

title: mom's meat loaf
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Add milk until it feels soft. Grease iron frying pan or 9 x 13-inch pan.
Shape in loaf, patting air out of it.

title: layered salad
directions: Spread lettuce in a large dish or container.
Add onions and celery.
Add peas; spread mayonnaise.
Sprinkle sugar on mayonnaise.
Add bacon.
Top with cheese.
Let sit overnight and serve.

title: sweep steak
directions: Put the meat on a large sheet of foil and sprinkle the onion soup mix on top.
Fold the foil airtight around it.
Put in a baking pan and bake at 300° for 3 hours.

title: buttermilk pie
directions: Cream together sugar and margarine. Add salt and flour.
Beat in eggs and vanilla. Fold in buttermilk.
Pour into pie shell and bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: zippy horseradish dip
directions: Mix ingredients, except veggies.
Chill and serve with veggies.
Yields 1 cup dip.

title: biscochos(very special cookies)
directions: Beat eggs (reserve 4 tablespoons of later use).
Add sugar, then oil and beat well.
Add flour and baking powder, a little at a time, until it forms a smooth dough.
Roll dough into strips about 1/2 inch diameter, then cut in 4-inch lengths.
Bring ends together to form a ring.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet.
Add 1 teaspoon sugar to reserved egg and brush on biscochos.
Bake at 350° for 22 to 25 minutes or until brown.

title: hello dolly cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Melt butter in 9 x 9-inch pan in oven. Sprinkle graham cracker crumbs over melted butter; stir and spread evenly in pan.
Sprinkle coconut over crumbs.
Add chocolate chips and sprinkle pecans over all.
Pour milk on top.
Do not stir. Bake about 30 minutes.
When cool, cut into squares.
Yields 9 squares.

title: tea cakes
directions: Mix all ingredients.
The dough should be soft.
Use only a little flour when rolling dough.
Cut out cookies and bake on cookie sheet for about 12 minutes at 350°.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Mix jello as directed on package.
For second cup of water use pineapple juice that was drained from can.
Add celery, nuts, pineapple and lemon juice.
Mix well and put salad in glass bowl or jello mold that has been oiled.
After jello sets 3 hours, stir to mix fruit and vegetables evenly.
Let set in refrigerator overnight.
Good with chicken or turkey.
Also good with cottage cheese for lunch.

title: sausage balls
directions: Mix all ingredients together. Roll into small balls. Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.

title: bitter chocolate mousse
directions: As a substitute for extra strong coffee use 3 tablespoons instant powdered coffee with 4 tablespoons of hot water; cool.

title: ron's god awful chile
directions: *BLKLIN stop it sticking to the bottom of the saucepan or forming knots.

title: basic pastry - single crust
directions: For Double Crust:
Prepare as directed, doubling ingredients.

title: no bake cookies
directions: Bring first 5 ingredients to a boil in saucepan. Add the peanut butter and oatmeal. Drop quickly by spoonfuls on wax paper.

title: chocolate pizza
directions: Take one square of bark, add oil, put in a microwave cup and microwave until melted. Reserve to put on top of pizza. Microwave chocolate chips and rest of vanilla bark in microwave dish on high stirring every one to two minutes until smooth. Stir in marshmallows, cereal, and peanuts. Put into a 12 inch greased pizza pan. Top with cherries and coconut. Drizzle reserved melted bark over coconut. Green cherries can be used.

title: heirloom relish
directions: Combine first 7 ingredients; let stand overnight.
Drain well; discard brine.
In a 6-quart pan, combine vegetables, vinegar, sugar, mustard and celery seed; simmer 30 minutes.
Combine flour, dry mustard and turmeric, add to relish and cook 10 minutes.
Pack in hot, sterilized jars; process in hot water bath for 10 minutes.
Makes 7 1/2 pints.

title: pineapple casserole
directions: Pour pineapple into baking dish. Mix sugar and flour and sprinkle over pineapple. Add cheese; then top with crackers and butter, mixed together. Bake 30 minutes at 350°. Serve warm.

title: orange crush
directions: Make orange juice according to label.
Put in blender or shaker.
Add remaining ingredients.
Blend or shake until thick and frothy.
Pour into 6 tall glasses.
Garnish with mint.

title: raisin pudding pie
directions: Pour boiling water over raisins.
Let stand for 5 minutes and drain them well.
Prepare filling mix using 2 cups milk.
Chill thoroughly.
Fold in Cool Whip, lemon juice, cinnamon and raisins.
Chill for 3 hours.
Garnish if desired.

title: buttercream frosting
directions: Make thickening by cooking flour and milk.
Cool.
Cream butter and sugar.
Add thickening and vanilla.
Beat well.

title: chocolate fudge
directions: Combine cocoa, sugar and salt in 3-quart saucepan.
Add milk gradually; mix thoroughly.
Bring to bubble boil on high heat. Stir constantly; reduce heat to medium and continue to boil mixture without stirring until soft balls form in cold water.
Add butter and vanilla.
Beat by hand until fudge thickens and loses some of its gloss.
Pour into slightly greased 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: sweet potato bread
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients in a large bowl; set aside. Combine potatoes, sugar, margarine, milk, eggs, orange rind and nuts, beating well. Add to dry ingredients, stirring until just moistened. Pour batter into 9 x 5 x 3 loaf pan coated with vegetable cooking spray. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until wooden toothpick inserted in center comes clean. Cool in pan 10 minutes; remove from pan and cool completely. Yield: 1 loaf, 18 1/2 slices (122 calories per slice).

title: hot asparagus appetizer
directions: Roll bread slices flat with a rolling pin.
Spread 1 teaspoon of cheese spread on flattened bread.
Lay an asparagus spear and roll up like a jelly roll.
Wrap individual roll in waxed paper and chill overnight.
Repeat with remaining asparagus spears.

title: no bake chocolate oatmeal cookies
directions: Mix oatmeal, vanilla and peanut butter in a bowl; set aside. Put everything else in a pan and bring to a rapid boil for 1 minute.
Pour onto the oatmeal and stir.
Put on wax paper and let harden.

title: pumpkin delight
directions: Line 9 x 13-inch pan with waxed paper. Mix pumpkin, milk, sugar, eggs and cinnamon together. Pour into pan. Pour dry yellow cake mix over pumpkin mixture. Pat the chopped nuts on top of cake mix. Pour the 2 sticks of melted oleo over this and bake in 350° oven 50 to 60 minutes. When cool, invert on serving dish. Peel off wax paper. Serve Cool Whip as frosting.

title: artichoke dip
directions: Mix ingredients.
Sprinkle with garlic powder.
Bake for about 20 minutes at 350°.

title: pinto bean pie(mock pecan)
directions: Beat eggs; combine with mashed beans and other ingredients. Bake in uncooked pie shell for 40 minutes at 350°.

title: string bean casserole
directions: Simmer beans for 15 minutes. Drain.
Mix all ingredients except butter well and place in a greased casserole.
Sprinkle top with toasted bread crumbs. Dot with butter.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: millionaires
directions: Melt caramels in milk over low heat.
Add pecans.
Drop by teaspoon onto buttered baking sheets. Chill.
Melt paraffin and chocolate morsels in heavy pan over low heat or in top of double boiler.
Dip candy into chocolate and return to buttered baking sheet.
Chill.
Yields 3 1/2 dozen.

title: angel pie
directions: Beat eggs. Add sugar, salt and juice. Bring to boil (can use double boiler). Pour over jello. Cool. Whip Carnation milk and combine. Pour into pie mix into 2 pans lined with vanilla wafers or graham cracker crust. Save a little wafer/cracker to sprinkle over top of pie.

title: skillet style cabbage
directions: Saute ground beef, then fry cabbage and onion until tender. Add ground beef and tomato paste to cabbage and onion mixture. Simmer approximately 5 additional minutes.

title: italian cream cake
directions: Use an electric mixer and combine all ingredients except coconut and nuts.
Mix well.
Add coconut and nuts.
Spread on cooled cake.

title: turtle cake squares
directions: Melt caramels and 1/4 cup milk in heavy saucepan over low heat, stirring constantly; or melt this mixture in a microwave for 3 minutes, stirring after every minute. Set aside.

title: cream cheese danish
directions: Spray baking mix with vegetable spray. Layer with one can crescent rolls (do not separate, roll out into pan in one piece).

title: chocolate mousse
directions: Put all ingredients into blender, adding milk last.
Blend well.
Pour into bowl and refrigerate overnight.

title: custard pie
directions: Heat milk on stove until it comes to a boil, stirring constantly.
Beat eggs. Add sugar, vanilla and salt to beaten eggs. Add the milk to egg mixture.
Pour into unbaked pie shell. Sprinkle top of pie with nutmeg.
Bake at 425° for 5 minutes, then at 375° for 10 minutes or until done.

title: applesauce cookies
directions: Cream together sugar and butter.
Add egg and applesauce. Sift together flour, baking powder, soda, cinnamon, cloves and salt.
Add to creamed mixture.
Add optional raisins and nuts. Drop by spoonful on greased cookie sheets and bake until light brown at 350°.

title: german potato salad
directions: Fry bacon until crisp.
Crumble.
Add to potatoes, onion, celery and seasoning.
Add vinegar to bacon drippings and simmer 5 minutes.
Stir in flour to thicken.
Pour this over potatoes.
Let set awhile before serving.
You can use boiled eggs, pickle relish, celery seed and mustard.

title: basil tomatoes
directions: Combine oil, vinegar, basil, salt and pepper.
Add tomatoes and evenly coat.
Add garlic powder.
Chill 2 hours.
Serves 4.

title: taco dip
directions: Mix all ingredients together and chill until ready for use.

title: divinity fudge
directions: Mix together sugar, syrup and water.
Cook until it spins thread or soft ball stage. Pour 1/2 of it on the egg whites that have been beaten stiff.
Pour slowly so as not to cook the eggs too quickly.
Cook other half until it will form a hard ball in cold water, then pour it into the other while beating.
Beat until creamy.
Add nuts or coconut.
Pour into buttered pan or onto wax paper.

title: grammie whittemore's apple pie
directions: To make pie crust, use flour, Crisco, salt and water, following standard directions for a two crust pie.

title: lasagna
directions: Brown beef and sausage. Add spaghetti sauce and spices. Simmer.

title: fruit punch
directions: Mix all ingredients, except ginger ale and sherbet.
Chill; add remaining ingredients when ready to serve.

title: spicy fish fillets
directions: Wipe fish with damp cloth.
Place fish in greased shallow baking pan, having covered bottom of dish with bread crumbs.
Mix remaining 6 ingredients and pour over fish.
Garnish with paprika and bake at 450° for 10 to 20 minutes.

title: potato chip cookies
directions: Mix butter and sugar; add flour.
Stir all together until smooth.
Add potato chips, then drop by teaspoon onto ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake until slightly brown at 350°.
Cool and cover with powdered sugar.
Makes 7 dozen.

title: grandmother dunlap's broccoli
directions: Cook broccoli and drain.
Combine rest of ingredients, except crackers, with the broccoli.
Put in greased casserole and sprinkle with crumbled crackers.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes.
Serves 10 to 12.

title: zucchini cake(zucchini isn't just a vegetable.  try it for dessert.)
directions: In a large bowl, mix eggs, oil, sugar, zucchini and vanilla. Add flour and mix.
Add baking powder, baking soda and salt; mix well.
Stir in nutmeg and nuts.
Pour into a greased and lightly floured 9 x 13-inch pan and bake in a 350° oven for 1 hour.
When cool, add Creamy Topping.

title: spicy rice
directions: Mix all ingredients into rice and cook.
After water boils out of rice, let simmer until desired consistency.

title: layered lettuce salad
directions: Mix mayonnaise and sugar and toss together about 15 minutes before serving.

title: strawberry delight
directions: Slice cake thin.
Slice strawberries and mix the glaze and strawberries together.
Mix pudding as directed and add whipped cream, then layer pudding, cake and strawberries.

title: mississippi corn bread
directions: Mix together and bake at 350° until done (about 20 minutes).

title: cheese ball
directions: Mix all together.
Put into refrigerator for 30 minutes. Shape into a ball and roll in chopped nuts. Serve with crackers.

title: choco peanut butter bars
directions: Preheat oven to 374.
Grease 9 X 13 pan.
Mix peanut butter, shortening, sugars, and egg.
Stir in water, flour, baking soda, baking powder, salt, chocolate chips, and peanuts.
Spread in pan. Bake 20 minutes.

title: shrimp dip
directions: Add all together in bowl.
Chill and serve with chips or crackers.
